147class ClipRects : public RefCounted<ClipRects> {
148 WTF_MAKE_FAST_ALLOCATED;
149public:
150 static Ref<ClipRects> create()
151 {
152 return adoptRef(*new ClipRects);
153 }
154
155 static Ref<ClipRects> create(const ClipRects& other)
156 {
157 return adoptRef(*new ClipRects(other));
158 }
159
160 void reset()
161 {
162 m_overflowClipRect.reset();
163 m_fixedClipRect.reset();
164 m_posClipRect.reset();
165 m_fixed = false;
166 }
167
168 const ClipRect& overflowClipRect() const { return m_overflowClipRect; }
169 void setOverflowClipRect(const ClipRect& clipRect) { m_overflowClipRect = clipRect; }
170
171 const ClipRect& fixedClipRect() const { return m_fixedClipRect; }
172 void setFixedClipRect(const ClipRect& clipRect) { m_fixedClipRect = clipRect; }
173
174 const ClipRect& posClipRect() const { return m_posClipRect; }
175 void setPosClipRect(const ClipRect& clipRect) { m_posClipRect = clipRect; }
176
177 bool fixed() const { return m_fixed; }
178 void setFixed(bool fixed) { m_fixed = fixed; }
179
180 void setOverflowClipRectAffectedByRadius() { m_overflowClipRect.setAffectedByRadius(true); }
181
182 bool operator==(const ClipRects& other) const
183 {
184 return m_overflowClipRect == other.overflowClipRect()
185 && m_fixedClipRect == other.fixedClipRect()
186 && m_posClipRect == other.posClipRect()
187 && m_fixed == other.fixed();
188 }
189
190 ClipRects& operator=(const ClipRects& other)
191 {
192 m_overflowClipRect = other.overflowClipRect();
193 m_fixedClipRect = other.fixedClipRect();
194 m_posClipRect = other.posClipRect();
195 m_fixed = other.fixed();
196 return *this;
197 }
198
199private:
200 ClipRects() = default;
201
202 ClipRects(const LayoutRect& clipRect)
203 : m_overflowClipRect(clipRect)
204 , m_fixedClipRect(clipRect)
205 , m_posClipRect(clipRect)
206 {
207 }
208
209 ClipRects(const ClipRects& other)
210 : RefCounted()
211 , m_fixed(other.fixed())
212 , m_overflowClipRect(other.overflowClipRect())
213 , m_fixedClipRect(other.fixedClipRect())
214 , m_posClipRect(other.posClipRect())
215 {
216 }
217
218 bool m_fixed { false };
219 ClipRect m_overflowClipRect;
220 ClipRect m_fixedClipRect;
221 ClipRect m_posClipRect;
222};
223
224class ClipRectsCache {
225 WTF_MAKE_FAST_ALLOCATED;
226public:
227 ClipRectsCache()
228 {
229#if ASSERT_ENABLED
230 for (int i = 0; i < NumCachedClipRectsTypes; ++i) {
231 m_clipRectsRoot[i] = 0;
232 m_scrollbarRelevancy[i] = IgnoreOverlayScrollbarSize;
233 }
234#endif
235 }
236
237 ClipRects* getClipRects(ClipRectsType clipRectsType, ShouldRespectOverflowClip respectOverflow) const
238 {
239 return m_clipRects[getIndex(clipRectsType, respectOverflow)].get();
240 }
241
242 void setClipRects(ClipRectsType clipRectsType, ShouldRespectOverflowClip respectOverflow, RefPtr<ClipRects>&& clipRects)
243 {
244 m_clipRects[getIndex(clipRectsType, respectOverflow)] = WTFMove(clipRects);
245 }
246
247#if ASSERT_ENABLED
248 const RenderLayer* m_clipRectsRoot[NumCachedClipRectsTypes];
249 OverlayScrollbarSizeRelevancy m_scrollbarRelevancy[NumCachedClipRectsTypes];
250#endif
251
252private:
253 unsigned getIndex(ClipRectsType clipRectsType, ShouldRespectOverflowClip respectOverflow) const
254 {
255 unsigned index = static_cast<unsigned>(clipRectsType);
256 if (respectOverflow == RespectOverflowClip)
257 index += static_cast<unsigned>(NumCachedClipRectsTypes);
258 ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(index < NumCachedClipRectsTypes * 2);
259 return index;
260 }
261
262 RefPtr<ClipRects> m_clipRects[NumCachedClipRectsTypes * 2];
263};

266{
267#if !ENABLE(3D_TRANSFORMS)

269 matrix.makeAffine();
270#else

272 matrix.makeAffine();
273#endif
274}

298RenderLayer::RenderLayer(RenderLayerModelObject& rendererLayerModelObject)
299 : m_isRenderViewLayer(rendererLayerModelObject.isRenderView())
300 , m_forcedStackingContext(rendererLayerModelObject.isMedia())
301 , m_isNormalFlowOnly(false)
302 , m_isCSSStackingContext(false)
303 , m_isOpportunisticStackingContext(false)
304 , m_zOrderListsDirty(false)
305 , m_normalFlowListDirty(true)
306 , m_hadNegativeZOrderList(false)
307 , m_inResizeMode(false)
308 , m_hasSelfPaintingLayerDescendant(false)
309 , m_hasSelfPaintingLayerDescendantDirty(false)
310 , m_usedTransparency(false)
311 , m_paintingInsideReflection(false)
312 , m_repaintStatus(NeedsNormalRepaint)
313 , m_visibleContentStatusDirty(true)
314 , m_hasVisibleContent(false)
315 , m_visibleDescendantStatusDirty(false)
316 , m_hasVisibleDescendant(false)
317 , m_isFixedIntersectingViewport(false)
318 , m_behavesAsFixed(false)
319 , m_3DTransformedDescendantStatusDirty(true)
320 , m_has3DTransformedDescendant(false)
321 , m_hasCompositingDescendant(false)
322 , m_hasCompositedNonContainedDescendants(false)
323 , m_hasCompositedScrollingAncestor(false)
324 , m_hasTransformedAncestor(false)
325 , m_has3DTransformedAncestor(false)
326 , m_insideSVGForeignObject(false)
327 , m_indirectCompositingReason(static_cast<unsigned>(IndirectCompositingReason::None))
328 , m_viewportConstrainedNotCompositedReason(NoNotCompositedReason)
329#if ASSERT_ENABLED
330 , m_layerListMutationAllowed(true)
331#endif
332#if ENABLE(CSS_COMPOSITING)
333 , m_blendMode(static_cast<unsigned>(BlendMode::Normal))
334 , m_hasNotIsolatedCompositedBlendingDescendants(false)
335 , m_hasNotIsolatedBlendingDescendants(false)
336 , m_hasNotIsolatedBlendingDescendantsStatusDirty(false)
337#endif
338 , m_repaintRectsValid(false)
339 , m_renderer(rendererLayerModelObject)
340{
341 setIsNormalFlowOnly(shouldBeNormalFlowOnly());
342 setIsCSSStackingContext(shouldBeCSSStackingContext());
343
344 m_isSelfPaintingLayer = shouldBeSelfPaintingLayer();
345
346 if (isRenderViewLayer())
347 m_boxScrollingScope = m_contentsScrollingScope = nextScrollingScope();
348
349 if (!renderer().firstChild()) {
350 m_visibleContentStatusDirty = false;
351 m_hasVisibleContent = renderer().style().visibility() == Visibility::Visible;
352 }
353}
354
355RenderLayer::~RenderLayer()
356{
357 if (inResizeMode())
358 renderer().frame().eventHandler().resizeLayerDestroyed();
359
360 if (m_reflection)
361 removeReflection();
362
363 clearLayerScrollableArea();
364 clearLayerFilters();
365
366 if (paintsIntoProvidedBacking()) {
367 auto* backingProviderLayer = this->backingProviderLayer();
368 if (backingProviderLayer->backing())
369 backingProviderLayer->backing()->removeBackingSharingLayer(*this);
370 }
371
372 // Child layers will be deleted by their corresponding render objects, so
373 // we don't need to delete them ourselves.
374
375 clearBacking(true);
376
377 // Layer and all its children should be removed from the tree before destruction.
378 RELEASE_ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(renderer().renderTreeBeingDestroyed() || !parent());
379 RELEASE_ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(renderer().renderTreeBeingDestroyed() || !firstChild());
380}
381
382void RenderLayer::addChild(RenderLayer& child, RenderLayer* beforeChild)
383{
384 RenderLayer* prevSibling = beforeChild ? beforeChild->previousSibling() : lastChild();
385 if (prevSibling) {
386 child.setPreviousSibling(prevSibling);
387 prevSibling->setNextSibling(&child);
388 ASSERT(prevSibling != &child);
389 } else
390 setFirstChild(&child);
391
392 if (beforeChild) {
393 beforeChild->setPreviousSibling(&child);
394 child.setNextSibling(beforeChild);
395 ASSERT(beforeChild != &child);
396 } else
397 setLastChild(&child);
398
399 child.setParent(this);
400
401 dirtyPaintOrderListsOnChildChange(child);
402
403 child.updateAncestorDependentState();
404 child.updateDescendantDependentFlags();
405 if (child.m_hasVisibleContent || child.m_hasVisibleDescendant)
406 setAncestorChainHasVisibleDescendant();
407
408 if (child.isSelfPaintingLayer() || child.hasSelfPaintingLayerDescendant())
409 setAncestorChainHasSelfPaintingLayerDescendant();
410
411 if (compositor().hasContentCompositingLayers())
412 setDescendantsNeedCompositingRequirementsTraversal();
413
414 if (child.hasDescendantNeedingCompositingRequirementsTraversal() || child.needsCompositingRequirementsTraversal())
415 child.setAncestorsHaveCompositingDirtyFlag(Compositing::HasDescendantNeedingRequirementsTraversal);
416
417 if (child.hasDescendantNeedingUpdateBackingOrHierarchyTraversal() || child.needsUpdateBackingOrHierarchyTraversal())
418 child.setAncestorsHaveCompositingDirtyFlag(Compositing::HasDescendantNeedingBackingOrHierarchyTraversal);
419
420#if ENABLE(CSS_COMPOSITING)
421 if (child.hasBlendMode() || (child.hasNotIsolatedBlendingDescendants() && !child.isolatesBlending()))
422 updateAncestorChainHasBlendingDescendants(); // Why not just dirty?
423#endif
424
425 compositor().layerWasAdded(*this, child);
426}
427
428void RenderLayer::removeChild(RenderLayer& oldChild)
429{
430 if (!renderer().renderTreeBeingDestroyed())
431 compositor().layerWillBeRemoved(*this, oldChild);
432
433 // remove the child
434 if (oldChild.previousSibling())
435 oldChild.previousSibling()->setNextSibling(oldChild.nextSibling());
436 if (oldChild.nextSibling())
437 oldChild.nextSibling()->setPreviousSibling(oldChild.previousSibling());
438
439 if (m_first == &oldChild)
440 m_first = oldChild.nextSibling();
441 if (m_last == &oldChild)
442 m_last = oldChild.previousSibling();
443
444 dirtyPaintOrderListsOnChildChange(oldChild);
445
446 oldChild.setPreviousSibling(nullptr);
447 oldChild.setNextSibling(nullptr);
448 oldChild.setParent(nullptr);
449
450 oldChild.updateDescendantDependentFlags();
451 if (oldChild.m_hasVisibleContent || oldChild.m_hasVisibleDescendant)
452 dirtyAncestorChainVisibleDescendantStatus();
453
454 if (oldChild.isSelfPaintingLayer() || oldChild.hasSelfPaintingLayerDescendant())
455 dirtyAncestorChainHasSelfPaintingLayerDescendantStatus();
456
457 if (compositor().hasContentCompositingLayers())
458 setDescendantsNeedCompositingRequirementsTraversal();
459
460#if ENABLE(CSS_COMPOSITING)
461 if (oldChild.hasBlendMode() || (oldChild.hasNotIsolatedBlendingDescendants() && !oldChild.isolatesBlending()))
462 dirtyAncestorChainHasBlendingDescendants();
463#endif
464}
465
466void RenderLayer::dirtyPaintOrderListsOnChildChange(RenderLayer& child)
467{
468 if (child.isNormalFlowOnly())
469 dirtyNormalFlowList();
470
471 if (!child.isNormalFlowOnly() || child.firstChild()) {
472 // Dirty the z-order list in which we are contained. The stackingContext() can be null in the
473 // case where we're building up generated content layers. This is ok, since the lists will start
474 // off dirty in that case anyway.
475 child.dirtyStackingContextZOrderLists();
476 }
477}
478
479void RenderLayer::insertOnlyThisLayer(LayerChangeTiming timing)
480{
481 if (!m_parent && renderer().parent()) {
482 // We need to connect ourselves when our renderer() has a parent.
483 // Find our enclosingLayer and add ourselves.
484 RenderLayer* parentLayer = renderer().parent()->enclosingLayer();
485 ASSERT(parentLayer);
486 RenderLayer* beforeChild = parentLayer->reflectionLayer() != this ? renderer().parent()->findNextLayer(parentLayer, &renderer()) : nullptr;
487 parentLayer->addChild(*this, beforeChild);
488 }
489
490 // Remove all descendant layers from the hierarchy and add them to the new position.
491 for (auto& child : childrenOfType<RenderElement>(renderer()))
492 child.moveLayers(m_parent, this);
493
494 if (parent()) {
495 if (timing == LayerChangeTiming::StyleChange)
496 renderer().view().layerChildrenChangedDuringStyleChange(*parent());
497 }
498
499 // Clear out all the clip rects.
500 clearClipRectsIncludingDescendants();
501}
502
503void RenderLayer::removeOnlyThisLayer(LayerChangeTiming timing)
504{
505 if (!m_parent)
506 return;
507
508 if (timing == LayerChangeTiming::StyleChange)
509 renderer().view().layerChildrenChangedDuringStyleChange(*parent());
510
511 // Mark that we are about to lose our layer. This makes render tree
512 // walks ignore this layer while we're removing it.
513 renderer().setHasLayer(false);
514
515 compositor().layerWillBeRemoved(*m_parent, *this);
516
517 // Dirty the clip rects.
518 clearClipRectsIncludingDescendants();
519
520 RenderLayer* nextSib = nextSibling();
521
522 // Remove the child reflection layer before moving other child layers.
523 // The reflection layer should not be moved to the parent.
524 if (reflection())
525 removeChild(*reflectionLayer());
526
527 // Now walk our kids and reattach them to our parent.
528 RenderLayer* current = m_first;
529 while (current) {
530 RenderLayer* next = current->nextSibling();
531 removeChild(*current);
532 m_parent->addChild(*current, nextSib);
533 current->setRepaintStatus(NeedsFullRepaint);
534 current = next;
535 }
536
537 // Remove us from the parent.
538 m_parent->removeChild(*this);
539 renderer().destroyLayer();
540}

542static bool canCreateStackingContext(const RenderLayer& layer)
543{
544 auto& renderer = layer.renderer();
545 return renderer.hasTransformRelatedProperty()
546 || renderer.hasClipPath()
547 || renderer.hasFilter()
548 || renderer.hasMask()
549 || renderer.hasBackdropFilter()
550#if ENABLE(CSS_COMPOSITING)
551 || renderer.hasBlendMode()
552#endif
553 || renderer.isTransparent()
554 || renderer.isPositioned() // Note that this only creates stacking context in conjunction with explicit z-index.
555 || renderer.hasReflection()
556 || renderer.style().hasIsolation()
557 || !renderer.style().hasAutoUsedZIndex()
558 || (renderer.style().willChange() && renderer.style().willChange()->canCreateStackingContext());
559}
560
561static void expandScrollRectToVisibleTargetRectToIncludeScrollPadding(RenderBox* renderBox, const LayoutRect& viewRect, LayoutRect& targetRect)
562{
563 if (!renderBox)
564 return;
565 // scroll-padding applies to the scroll container, but expand the rectangle that we want to expose in order
566 // simulate padding the scroll container. This rectangle is passed up the tree of scrolling elements to
567 // ensure that the padding on this scroll container is maintained.
568 targetRect.expand(renderBox->scrollPaddingForViewportRect(viewRect));
569}
570
571bool RenderLayer::shouldBeNormalFlowOnly() const
572{
573 if (canCreateStackingContext(*this))
574 return false;
575
576 return renderer().hasOverflowClip()
577 || renderer().isCanvas()
578 || renderer().isVideo()
579 || renderer().isEmbeddedObject()
580 || renderer().isRenderIFrame()
581 || (renderer().style().specifiesColumns() && !isRenderViewLayer())
582 || renderer().isRenderFragmentedFlow();
583}
584
585bool RenderLayer::shouldBeCSSStackingContext() const
586{
587 return !renderer().style().hasAutoUsedZIndex() || isRenderViewLayer();
588}
589
590bool RenderLayer::setIsNormalFlowOnly(bool isNormalFlowOnly)
591{
592 if (isNormalFlowOnly == m_isNormalFlowOnly)
593 return false;
594
595 m_isNormalFlowOnly = isNormalFlowOnly;
596
597 if (auto* p = parent())
598 p->dirtyNormalFlowList();
599 dirtyStackingContextZOrderLists();
600 return true;
601}
602
603void RenderLayer::isStackingContextChanged()
604{
605 dirtyStackingContextZOrderLists();
606 if (isStackingContext())
607 dirtyZOrderLists();
608 else
609 clearZOrderLists();
610}
611
612bool RenderLayer::setIsOpportunisticStackingContext(bool isStacking)
613{
614 bool wasStacking = isStackingContext();
615 m_isOpportunisticStackingContext = isStacking;
616 if (wasStacking == isStackingContext())
617 return false;
618
619 isStackingContextChanged();
620 return true;
621}
622
623bool RenderLayer::setIsCSSStackingContext(bool isCSSStackingContext)
624{
625 bool wasStacking = isStackingContext();
626 m_isCSSStackingContext = isCSSStackingContext;
627 if (wasStacking == isStackingContext())
628 return false;
629
630 isStackingContextChanged();
631 return true;
632}
633
634void RenderLayer::setParent(RenderLayer* parent)
635{
636 if (parent == m_parent)
637 return;
638
639 if (m_parent && !renderer().renderTreeBeingDestroyed())
640 compositor().layerWillBeRemoved(*m_parent, *this);
641
642 m_parent = parent;
643
644 if (m_parent && !renderer().renderTreeBeingDestroyed())
645 compositor().layerWasAdded(*m_parent, *this);
646}
647
648RenderLayer* RenderLayer::stackingContext() const
649{
650 auto* layer = parent();
651 while (layer && !layer->isStackingContext())
652 layer = layer->parent();
653
654 ASSERT(!layer || layer->isStackingContext());
655 return layer;
656}
657
658void RenderLayer::dirtyZOrderLists()
659{
660 ASSERT(layerListMutationAllowed());
661 ASSERT(isStackingContext());
662
663 if (m_posZOrderList)
664 m_posZOrderList->clear();
665 if (m_negZOrderList)
666 m_negZOrderList->clear();
667 m_zOrderListsDirty = true;
668
669 // FIXME: Ideally, we'd only dirty if the lists changed.
670 if (hasCompositingDescendant())
671 setNeedsCompositingPaintOrderChildrenUpdate();
672}
673
674void RenderLayer::dirtyStackingContextZOrderLists()
675{
676 if (auto* sc = stackingContext())
677 sc->dirtyZOrderLists();
678}
679
680void RenderLayer::dirtyNormalFlowList()
681{
682 ASSERT(layerListMutationAllowed());
683
684 if (m_normalFlowList)
685 m_normalFlowList->clear();
686 m_normalFlowListDirty = true;
687
688 if (hasCompositingDescendant())
689 setNeedsCompositingPaintOrderChildrenUpdate();
690}
691
692void RenderLayer::updateNormalFlowList()
693{
694 if (!m_normalFlowListDirty)
695 return;
696
697 ASSERT(layerListMutationAllowed());
698
699 for (RenderLayer* child = firstChild(); child; child = child->nextSibling()) {
700 // Ignore non-overflow layers and reflections.
701 if (child->isNormalFlowOnly() && !isReflectionLayer(*child)) {
702 if (!m_normalFlowList)
703 m_normalFlowList = makeUnique<Vector<RenderLayer*>>();
704 m_normalFlowList->append(child);
705 }
706 }
707
708 if (m_normalFlowList)
709 m_normalFlowList->shrinkToFit();
710
711 m_normalFlowListDirty = false;
712}
713
714void RenderLayer::rebuildZOrderLists()
715{
716 ASSERT(layerListMutationAllowed());
717 ASSERT(isDirtyStackingContext());
718
719 OptionSet<Compositing> childDirtyFlags;
720 rebuildZOrderLists(m_posZOrderList, m_negZOrderList, childDirtyFlags);
721 m_zOrderListsDirty = false;
722
723 bool hasNegativeZOrderList = m_negZOrderList && m_negZOrderList->size();
724 // Having negative z-order lists affect whether a compositing layer needs a foreground layer.
725 // Ideally we'd only trigger this when having z-order children changes, but we blow away the old z-order
726 // lists on dirtying so we don't know the old state.
727 if (hasNegativeZOrderList != m_hadNegativeZOrderList) {
728 m_hadNegativeZOrderList = hasNegativeZOrderList;
729 if (isComposited())
730 setNeedsCompositingConfigurationUpdate();
731 }
732
733 // Building lists may have added layers with dirty flags, so make sure we propagate dirty bits up the tree.
734 if (m_compositingDirtyBits.containsAll({ Compositing::DescendantsNeedRequirementsTraversal, Compositing::DescendantsNeedBackingAndHierarchyTraversal }))
735 return;
736
737 if (childDirtyFlags.containsAny(computeCompositingRequirementsFlags()))
738 setDescendantsNeedCompositingRequirementsTraversal();
739
740 if (childDirtyFlags.containsAny(updateBackingOrHierarchyFlags()))
741 setDescendantsNeedUpdateBackingAndHierarchyTraversal();
742}
743
744void RenderLayer::rebuildZOrderLists(std::unique_ptr<Vector<RenderLayer*>>& posZOrderList, std::unique_ptr<Vector<RenderLayer*>>& negZOrderList, OptionSet<Compositing>& accumulatedDirtyFlags)
745{
746 bool includeHiddenLayers = compositor().usesCompositing();
747 for (RenderLayer* child = firstChild(); child; child = child->nextSibling()) {
748 if (!isReflectionLayer(*child))
749 child->collectLayers(includeHiddenLayers, posZOrderList, negZOrderList, accumulatedDirtyFlags);
750 }
751
752 auto compareZIndex = [] (const RenderLayer* first, const RenderLayer* second) -> bool {
753 return first->zIndex() < second->zIndex();
754 };
755
756 // Sort the two lists.
757 if (posZOrderList) {
758 std::stable_sort(posZOrderList->begin(), posZOrderList->end(), compareZIndex);
759 posZOrderList->shrinkToFit();
760 }
761
762 if (negZOrderList) {
763 std::stable_sort(negZOrderList->begin(), negZOrderList->end(), compareZIndex);
764 negZOrderList->shrinkToFit();
765 }
766}
767
768void RenderLayer::collectLayers(bool includeHiddenLayers, std::unique_ptr<Vector<RenderLayer*>>& positiveZOrderList, std::unique_ptr<Vector<RenderLayer*>>& negativeZOrderList, OptionSet<Compositing>& accumulatedDirtyFlags)
769{
770 updateDescendantDependentFlags();
771
772 bool isStacking = isStackingContext();
773 // Overflow layers are just painted by their enclosing layers, so they don't get put in zorder lists.
774 bool includeHiddenLayer = includeHiddenLayers || (m_hasVisibleContent || (m_hasVisibleDescendant && isStacking));
775 if (includeHiddenLayer && !isNormalFlowOnly()) {
776 auto& layerList = (zIndex() >= 0) ? positiveZOrderList : negativeZOrderList;
777 if (!layerList)
778 layerList = makeUnique<Vector<RenderLayer*>>();
779 layerList->append(this);
780 accumulatedDirtyFlags.add(m_compositingDirtyBits);
781 }
782
783 // Recur into our children to collect more layers, but only if we don't establish
784 // a stacking context/container.
785 if ((includeHiddenLayers || m_hasVisibleDescendant) && !isStacking) {
786 for (RenderLayer* child = firstChild(); child; child = child->nextSibling()) {
787 // Ignore reflections.
788 if (!isReflectionLayer(*child))
789 child->collectLayers(includeHiddenLayers, positiveZOrderList, negativeZOrderList, accumulatedDirtyFlags);
790 }
791 }
792}

798 break;
799 layer->m_compositingDirtyBits.add(flag);

861OptionSet<RenderLayer::UpdateLayerPositionsFlag> RenderLayer::flagsForUpdateLayerPositions(RenderLayer& startingLayer)
862{
863 OptionSet<UpdateLayerPositionsFlag> flags = { CheckForRepaint };
864
865 if (auto* parent = startingLayer.parent()) {
866 if (parent->hasTransformedAncestor() || parent->transform())
867 flags.add(SeenTransformedLayer);
868
869 if (parent->has3DTransformedAncestor() || (parent->transform() && !parent->transform()->isAffine()))
870 flags.add(Seen3DTransformedLayer);
871
872 if (parent->behavesAsFixed() || (parent->renderer().isFixedPositioned() && !parent->hasTransformedAncestor()))
873 flags.add(SeenFixedLayer);
874
875 if (parent->hasCompositedScrollingAncestor() || parent->hasCompositedScrollableOverflow())
876 flags.add(SeenCompositedScrollingLayer);
877 }
878
879 return flags;
880}

883{

885}
886
887void RenderLayer::updateLayerPositionsAfterLayout(bool isRelayoutingSubtree, bool didFullRepaint)
888{
889 auto updateLayerPositionFlags = [&](bool isRelayoutingSubtree, bool didFullRepaint) {
890 auto flags = flagsForUpdateLayerPositions(*this);
891 if (didFullRepaint) {
892 flags.remove(RenderLayer::CheckForRepaint);
893 flags.add(RenderLayer::NeedsFullRepaintInBacking);
894 }
895 if (isRelayoutingSubtree && enclosingPaginationLayer(RenderLayer::IncludeCompositedPaginatedLayers))
896 flags.add(RenderLayer::UpdatePagination);
897 return flags;
898 };
899
900 LOG(Compositing, "RenderLayer %p updateLayerPositionsAfterLayout", this);
901 RenderGeometryMap geometryMap(UseTransforms);
902 if (!isRenderViewLayer())
903 geometryMap.pushMappingsToAncestor(parent(), nullptr);
904
905 updateLayerPositions(&geometryMap, updateLayerPositionFlags(isRelayoutingSubtree, didFullRepaint));
906}
907
908void RenderLayer::updateLayerPositions(RenderGeometryMap* geometryMap, OptionSet<UpdateLayerPositionsFlag> flags)
909{
910 updateLayerPosition(&flags);
911 if (m_scrollableArea)
912 m_scrollableArea->applyPostLayoutScrollPositionIfNeeded();
913
914 if (geometryMap)
915 geometryMap->pushMappingsToAncestor(this, parent());
916
917 // Clear our cached clip rect information.
918 clearClipRects();
919
920 if (m_scrollableArea && m_scrollableArea->hasOverflowControls()) {
921 LayoutSize offsetFromRoot;
922 if (geometryMap)
923 offsetFromRoot = LayoutSize(toFloatSize(geometryMap->absolutePoint(FloatPoint())));
924 else {
925 // FIXME: It looks suspicious to call convertToLayerCoords here
926 // as canUseOffsetFromAncestor may be true for an ancestor layer.
927 offsetFromRoot = offsetFromAncestor(root());
928 }
929 m_scrollableArea->positionOverflowControls(roundedIntSize(offsetFromRoot));
930 }
931
932 updateDescendantDependentFlags();
933
934 if (flags & UpdatePagination)
935 updatePagination();
936 else
937 m_enclosingPaginationLayer = nullptr;
938
939 if (m_hasVisibleContent) {
940 // FIXME: Paint offset cache does not work with RenderLayers as there is not a 1-to-1
941 // mapping between them and the RenderObjects. It would be neat to enable
942 // LayoutState outside the layout() phase and use it here.
943 ASSERT(!renderer().view().frameView().layoutContext().isPaintOffsetCacheEnabled());
944
945 RenderLayerModelObject* repaintContainer = renderer().containerForRepaint();
946
947 auto oldRects = repaintRects();
948 computeRepaintRects(repaintContainer, geometryMap);
949
950 auto newRects = repaintRects();
951
952 // FIXME: Should ASSERT that value calculated for m_outlineBox using the cached offset is the same
953 // as the value not using the cached offset, but we can't due to https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=37048
954 if ((flags & CheckForRepaint) && newRects) {
955 if (!renderer().view().printing()) {
956 if (m_repaintStatus & NeedsFullRepaint) {
957 if (oldRects)
958 renderer().repaintUsingContainer(repaintContainer, oldRects->clippedOverflowRect);
959
960 if (!oldRects || newRects->clippedOverflowRect != oldRects->clippedOverflowRect)
961 renderer().repaintUsingContainer(repaintContainer, newRects->clippedOverflowRect);
962
963 } else if (shouldRepaintAfterLayout()) {
964 // FIXME: We will convert this to just take the old and new RepaintLayoutRects once
965 // we change other callers to use RepaintLayoutRects.
966 auto resolvedOldRects = oldRects.value_or(LayerRepaintRects { });
967 renderer().repaintAfterLayoutIfNeeded(repaintContainer, resolvedOldRects.clippedOverflowRect, resolvedOldRects.outlineBoundsRect,
968 &newRects->clippedOverflowRect, &newRects->outlineBoundsRect);
969 }
970 }
971 }
972 } else
973 clearRepaintRects();
974
975 m_repaintStatus = NeedsNormalRepaint;
976 m_hasTransformedAncestor = flags.contains(SeenTransformedLayer);
977 m_has3DTransformedAncestor = flags.contains(Seen3DTransformedLayer);
978 m_behavesAsFixed = flags.contains(SeenFixedLayer);
979 setHasCompositedScrollingAncestor(flags.contains(SeenCompositedScrollingLayer));
980
981 // Update the reflection's position and size.
982 if (m_reflection)
983 m_reflection->layout();
984
985 if (renderer().isRenderFragmentedFlow()) {
986 updatePagination();
987 flags.add(UpdatePagination);
988 }
989
990 if (transform()) {
991 flags.add(SeenTransformedLayer);
992 if (!transform()->isAffine())
993 flags.add(Seen3DTransformedLayer);
994 }
995
996 // Fixed inside transform behaves like absolute (per spec).
997 if (renderer().isFixedPositioned() && !m_hasTransformedAncestor) {
998 m_behavesAsFixed = true;
999 flags.add(SeenFixedLayer);
1000 }
1001
1002 if (hasCompositedScrollableOverflow())
1003 flags.add(SeenCompositedScrollingLayer);
1004
1005 for (RenderLayer* child = firstChild(); child; child = child->nextSibling())
1006 child->updateLayerPositions(geometryMap, flags);
1007
1008 if (m_scrollableArea)
1009 m_scrollableArea->updateMarqueePosition();
1010
1011 if (renderer().isFixedPositioned() && renderer().settings().acceleratedCompositingForFixedPositionEnabled()) {
1012 bool intersectsViewport = compositor().fixedLayerIntersectsViewport(*this);
1013 if (intersectsViewport != m_isFixedIntersectingViewport) {
1014 m_isFixedIntersectingViewport = intersectsViewport;
1015 setNeedsPostLayoutCompositingUpdate();
1016 }
1017 }
1018
1019 if (isComposited())
1020 backing()->updateAfterLayout(flags.contains(ContainingClippingLayerChangedSize), flags.contains(NeedsFullRepaintInBacking));
1021
1022 if (geometryMap)
1023 geometryMap->popMappingsToAncestor(parent());
1024
1025 renderer().document().markers().invalidateRectsForAllMarkers();
1026}

1028LayoutRect RenderLayer::repaintRectIncludingNonCompositingDescendants() const
1029{
1030 LayoutRect repaintRect;
1031 if (m_repaintRectsValid)
1032 repaintRect = m_repaintRects.clippedOverflowRect;
1033 for (RenderLayer* child = firstChild(); child; child = child->nextSibling()) {
1034 // Don't include repaint rects for composited child layers; they will paint themselves and have a different origin.
1035 if (child->isComposited())
1036 continue;
1037
1038 repaintRect.uniteIfNonZero(child->repaintRectIncludingNonCompositingDescendants());
1039 }
1040 return repaintRect;
1041}

1103
1104void RenderLayer::updateLayerPositionsAfterScroll(RenderGeometryMap* geometryMap, OptionSet<UpdateLayerPositionsAfterScrollFlag> flags)
1105{
1106 // FIXME: This shouldn't be needed, but there are some corner cases where
1107 // these flags are still dirty. Update so that the check below is valid.
1108 updateDescendantDependentFlags();
1109
1110 // If we have no visible content and no visible descendants, there is no point recomputing
1111 // our rectangles as they will be empty. If our visibility changes, we are expected to
1112 // recompute all our positions anyway.
1113 if (!m_hasVisibleDescendant && !m_hasVisibleContent)
1114 return;
1115
1116 bool positionChanged = updateLayerPosition();
1117 if (positionChanged)
1118 flags.add(HasChangedAncestor);
1119
1120 if (flags.containsAny({ HasChangedAncestor, HasSeenViewportConstrainedAncestor, IsOverflowScroll }))
1121 clearClipRects();
1122
1123 if (renderer().style().hasViewportConstrainedPosition())
1124 flags.add(HasSeenViewportConstrainedAncestor);
1125
1126 if (renderer().hasOverflowClip())
1127 flags.add(HasSeenAncestorWithOverflowClip);
1128
1129 bool shouldComputeRepaintRects = (flags.contains(HasSeenViewportConstrainedAncestor) || flags.containsAll({ IsOverflowScroll, HasSeenAncestorWithOverflowClip })) && isSelfPaintingLayer();
1130 bool isVisuallyEmpty = !isVisuallyNonEmpty();
1131 bool shouldPushAndPopMappings = geometryMap && ((shouldComputeRepaintRects && !isVisuallyEmpty) || firstChild());
1132 if (shouldPushAndPopMappings)
1133 geometryMap->pushMappingsToAncestor(this, parent());
1134
1135 if (shouldComputeRepaintRects) {
1136 // When scrolling, we don't compute repaint rects for visually non-empty layers.
1137 if (isVisuallyEmpty)
1138 clearRepaintRects();
1139 else // FIXME: We could track the repaint container as we walk down the tree.
1140 computeRepaintRects(renderer().containerForRepaint(), geometryMap);
1141 } else if (!renderer().view().frameView().platformWidget()) {
1142 // When ScrollView's m_paintsEntireContents flag flips due to layer backing changes, the repaint area transitions from
1143 // visual to layout overflow. When this happens the cached repaint rects become invalid and they need to be recomputed (see webkit.org/b/188121).
1144 // Check that our cached rects are correct.
1145 ASSERT_IMPLIES(m_repaintRectsValid, m_repaintRects.clippedOverflowRect == renderer().clippedOverflowRectForRepaint(renderer().containerForRepaint()));
1146 ASSERT_IMPLIES(m_repaintRectsValid, m_repaintRects.outlineBoundsRect == renderer().outlineBoundsForRepaint(renderer().containerForRepaint()));
1147 }
1148
1149 for (RenderLayer* child = firstChild(); child; child = child->nextSibling())
1150 child->updateLayerPositionsAfterScroll(geometryMap, flags);
1151
1152 // We don't update our reflection as scrolling is a translation which does not change the size()
1153 // of an object, thus RenderReplica will still repaint itself properly as the layer position was
1154 // updated above.
1155
1156 if (m_scrollableArea)
1157 m_scrollableArea->updateMarqueePosition();
1158
1159 if (shouldPushAndPopMappings)
1160 geometryMap->popMappingsToAncestor(parent());
1161
1162 renderer().document().markers().invalidateRectsForAllMarkers();
1163}

1216static inline LayoutRect computeReferenceRectFromBox(const RenderBox& box, CSSBoxType boxType, const LayoutSize& offsetFromRoot)
1217{
1218 auto referenceBox = box.referenceBox(boxType);
1219 referenceBox.move(offsetFromRoot);
1220 return referenceBox;
1221}
1222
1223static inline LayoutRect computeReferenceBox(const RenderObject& renderer, CSSBoxType boxType, const LayoutSize& offsetFromRoot, const LayoutRect& rootRelativeBounds)
1224{
1225 // FIXME: Support different reference boxes for inline content.
1226 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=129047
1227 if (!renderer.isBox())
1228 return rootRelativeBounds;
1229
1230 return computeReferenceRectFromBox(downcast<RenderBox>(renderer), boxType, offsetFromRoot);
1231}
1232
1233static inline CSSBoxType transformBoxToCSSBoxType(TransformBox transformBox)
1234{
1235 switch (transformBox) {
1236 case TransformBox::StrokeBox:
1237 return CSSBoxType::StrokeBox;
1238 case TransformBox::ContentBox:
1239 return CSSBoxType::ContentBox;
1240 case TransformBox::BorderBox:
1241 return CSSBoxType::BorderBox;
1242 case TransformBox::FillBox:
1243 return CSSBoxType::FillBox;
1244 case TransformBox::ViewBox:
1245 return CSSBoxType::ViewBox;
1246 default:
1247 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1248 return CSSBoxType::BorderBox;
1249 }
1250}
1251
1252void RenderLayer::updateTransform()
1253{
1254 bool hasTransform = renderer().hasTransform();
1255 bool had3DTransform = has3DTransform();
1256
1257 bool hadTransform = !!m_transform;
1258 if (hasTransform != hadTransform) {
1259 if (hasTransform)
1260 m_transform = makeUnique<TransformationMatrix>();
1261 else
1262 m_transform = nullptr;
1263
1264 // Layers with transforms act as clip rects roots, so clear the cached clip rects here.
1265 clearClipRectsIncludingDescendants();
1266 }
1267
1268 if (hasTransform) {
1269 auto& renderBox = downcast<RenderBox>(renderer());
1270 m_transform->makeIdentity();
1271 renderBox.style().applyTransform(*m_transform, snapRectToDevicePixels(renderBox.referenceBox(transformBoxToCSSBoxType(renderBox.style().transformBox())), renderBox.document().deviceScaleFactor()));
1272 makeMatrixRenderable(*m_transform, canRender3DTransforms());
1273 }
1274
1275 if (had3DTransform != has3DTransform()) {
1276 dirty3DTransformedDescendantStatus();
1277 // Having a 3D transform affects whether enclosing perspective and preserve-3d layers composite, so trigger an update.
1278 setNeedsPostLayoutCompositingUpdateOnAncestors();
1279 }
1280}
1281
1282TransformationMatrix RenderLayer::currentTransform(OptionSet<RenderStyle::TransformOperationOption> options) const
1283{
1284 if (!m_transform)
1285 return { };
1286
1287 if (!is<RenderBox>(renderer()))
1288 return { };
1289
1290 auto& renderBox = downcast<RenderBox>(renderer());
1291
1292 if (auto* timeline = renderer().documentTimeline()) {
1293 if (timeline->isRunningAcceleratedAnimationOnRenderer(renderer(), CSSPropertyTransform)) {
1294 TransformationMatrix currTransform;
1295 std::unique_ptr<RenderStyle> style = renderer().animatedStyle();
1296 FloatRect pixelSnappedBorderRect = snapRectToDevicePixels(renderBox.referenceBox(transformBoxToCSSBoxType(style->transformBox())), renderBox.document().deviceScaleFactor());
1297 style->applyTransform(currTransform, pixelSnappedBorderRect, options);
1298 makeMatrixRenderable(currTransform, canRender3DTransforms());
1299 return currTransform;
1300 }
1301 }
1302
1303 // m_transform includes transform-origin, so we need to recompute the transform here.
1304 if (!options.contains(RenderStyle::TransformOperationOption::TransformOrigin)) {
1305 TransformationMatrix currTransform;
1306 std::unique_ptr<RenderStyle> style = renderer().animatedStyle();
1307 FloatRect pixelSnappedBorderRect = snapRectToDevicePixels(renderBox.referenceBox(transformBoxToCSSBoxType(style->transformBox())), renderBox.document().deviceScaleFactor());
1308 renderBox.style().applyTransform(currTransform, pixelSnappedBorderRect, RenderStyle::individualTransformOperations);
1309 makeMatrixRenderable(currTransform, canRender3DTransforms());
1310 return currTransform;
1311 }
1312
1313 return *m_transform;
1314}
1315
1316TransformationMatrix RenderLayer::renderableTransform(OptionSet<PaintBehavior> paintBehavior) const
1317{
1318 if (!m_transform)
1319 return TransformationMatrix();
1320
1321 if (paintBehavior & PaintBehavior::FlattenCompositingLayers) {
1322 TransformationMatrix matrix = *m_transform;
1323 makeMatrixRenderable(matrix, false /* flatten 3d */);
1324 return matrix;
1325 }
1326
1327 return *m_transform;
1328}
1329
1330RenderLayer* RenderLayer::enclosingOverflowClipLayer(IncludeSelfOrNot includeSelf) const
1331{
1332 const RenderLayer* layer = (includeSelf == IncludeSelf) ? this : parent();
1333 while (layer) {
1334 if (layer->renderer().hasOverflowClip())
1335 return const_cast<RenderLayer*>(layer);
1336
1337 layer = layer->parent();
1338 }
1339 return nullptr;
1340}
1341
1342// FIXME: This is terrible. Bring back a cached bit for this someday. This crawl is going to slow down all
1343// painting of content inside paginated layers.
1344bool RenderLayer::hasCompositedLayerInEnclosingPaginationChain() const
1345{
1346 // No enclosing layer means no compositing in the chain.
1347 if (!m_enclosingPaginationLayer)
1348 return false;
1349
1350 // If the enclosing layer is composited, we don't have to check anything in between us and that
1351 // layer.
1352 if (m_enclosingPaginationLayer->isComposited())
1353 return true;
1354
1355 // If we are the enclosing pagination layer, then we can't be composited or we'd have passed the
1356 // previous check.
1357 if (m_enclosingPaginationLayer == this)
1358 return false;
1359
1360 // The enclosing paginated layer is our ancestor and is not composited, so we have to check
1361 // intermediate layers between us and the enclosing pagination layer. Start with our own layer.
1362 if (isComposited())
1363 return true;
1364
1365 // For normal flow layers, we can recur up the layer tree.
1366 if (isNormalFlowOnly())
1367 return parent()->hasCompositedLayerInEnclosingPaginationChain();
1368
1369 // Otherwise we have to go up the containing block chain. Find the first enclosing
1370 // containing block layer ancestor, and check that.
1371 for (const auto* containingBlock = renderer().containingBlock(); containingBlock && !is<RenderView>(*containingBlock); containingBlock = containingBlock->containingBlock()) {
1372 if (containingBlock->hasLayer())
1373 return containingBlock->layer()->hasCompositedLayerInEnclosingPaginationChain();
1374 }
1375 return false;
1376}
1377
1378void RenderLayer::updatePagination()
1379{
1380 m_enclosingPaginationLayer = nullptr;
1381
1382 if (!parent())
1383 return;
1384
1385 // Each layer that is inside a multicolumn flow thread has to be checked individually and
1386 // genuinely know if it is going to have to split itself up when painting only its contents (and not any other descendant
1387 // layers). We track an enclosingPaginationLayer instead of using a simple bit, since we want to be able to get back
1388 // to that layer easily.
1389 if (renderer().isRenderFragmentedFlow()) {
1390 m_enclosingPaginationLayer = makeWeakPtr(*this);
1391 return;
1392 }
1393
1394 if (isNormalFlowOnly()) {
1395 // Content inside a transform is not considered to be paginated, since we simply
1396 // paint the transform multiple times in each column, so we don't have to use
1397 // fragments for the transformed content.
1398 if (parent()->hasTransform())
1399 m_enclosingPaginationLayer = nullptr;
1400 else
1401 m_enclosingPaginationLayer = makeWeakPtr(parent()->enclosingPaginationLayer(IncludeCompositedPaginatedLayers));
1402 return;
1403 }
1404
1405 // For the new columns code, we want to walk up our containing block chain looking for an enclosing layer. Once
1406 // we find one, then we just check its pagination status.
1407 for (const auto* containingBlock = renderer().containingBlock(); containingBlock && !is<RenderView>(*containingBlock); containingBlock = containingBlock->containingBlock()) {
1408 if (containingBlock->hasLayer()) {
1409 // Content inside a transform is not considered to be paginated, since we simply
1410 // paint the transform multiple times in each column, so we don't have to use
1411 // fragments for the transformed content.
1412 if (containingBlock->layer()->hasTransform())
1413 m_enclosingPaginationLayer = nullptr;
1414 else
1415 m_enclosingPaginationLayer = makeWeakPtr(containingBlock->layer()->enclosingPaginationLayer(IncludeCompositedPaginatedLayers));
1416 return;
1417 }
1418 }
1419}

1421void RenderLayer::setHasVisibleContent()
1422{
1423 if (m_hasVisibleContent && !m_visibleContentStatusDirty) {
1424 ASSERT(!parent() || parent()->hasVisibleDescendant());
1425 return;
1426 }
1427
1428 m_visibleContentStatusDirty = false;
1429 m_hasVisibleContent = true;
1430 computeRepaintRects(renderer().containerForRepaint());
1431 if (!isNormalFlowOnly()) {
1432 // We don't collect invisible layers in z-order lists if we are not in compositing mode.
1433 // As we became visible, we need to dirty our stacking containers ancestors to be properly
1434 // collected. FIXME: When compositing, we could skip this dirtying phase.
1435 for (RenderLayer* sc = stackingContext(); sc; sc = sc->stackingContext()) {
1436 sc->dirtyZOrderLists();
1437 if (sc->hasVisibleContent())
1438 break;
1439 }
1440 }
1441
1442 if (parent())
1443 parent()->setAncestorChainHasVisibleDescendant();
1444}

1446void RenderLayer::dirtyVisibleContentStatus()
1447{
1448 m_visibleContentStatusDirty = true;
1449 if (parent())
1450 parent()->dirtyAncestorChainVisibleDescendantStatus();
1451}

1455 for (RenderLayer* layer = this; layer; layer = layer->parent()) {
1456 if (layer->m_visibleDescendantStatusDirty)
1457 break;
1458
1459 layer->m_visibleDescendantStatusDirty = true;
1460 }
1461}

1463void RenderLayer::setAncestorChainHasVisibleDescendant()
1464{

1466 if (!layer->m_visibleDescendantStatusDirty && layer->hasVisibleDescendant())
1467 break;
1468
1469 layer->m_hasVisibleDescendant = true;
1470 layer->m_visibleDescendantStatusDirty = false;
1471 }

1474void RenderLayer::updateAncestorDependentState()
1475{
1476 bool insideSVGForeignObject = renderer().document().mayHaveRenderedSVGForeignObjects() && ancestorsOfType<RenderSVGForeignObject>(renderer()).first();
1477 if (insideSVGForeignObject == m_insideSVGForeignObject)
1478 return;
1479
1480 m_insideSVGForeignObject = insideSVGForeignObject;
1481 updateSelfPaintingLayer();
1482}
1483
1484void RenderLayer::updateDescendantDependentFlags()
1485{
1486 if (m_visibleDescendantStatusDirty || m_hasSelfPaintingLayerDescendantDirty || hasNotIsolatedBlendingDescendantsStatusDirty()) {
1487 bool hasVisibleDescendant = false;
1488 bool hasSelfPaintingLayerDescendant = false;
1489#if ENABLE(CSS_COMPOSITING)
1490 bool hasNotIsolatedBlendingDescendants = false;
1491#endif
1492
1493 for (RenderLayer* child = firstChild(); child; child = child->nextSibling()) {
1494 child->updateDescendantDependentFlags();
1495
1496 hasVisibleDescendant |= child->m_hasVisibleContent || child->m_hasVisibleDescendant;
1497 hasSelfPaintingLayerDescendant |= child->isSelfPaintingLayer() || child->hasSelfPaintingLayerDescendant();
1498#if ENABLE(CSS_COMPOSITING)
1499 hasNotIsolatedBlendingDescendants |= child->hasBlendMode() || (child->hasNotIsolatedBlendingDescendants() && !child->isolatesBlending());
1500#endif
1501
1502 bool allFlagsSet = hasVisibleDescendant && hasSelfPaintingLayerDescendant;
1503#if ENABLE(CSS_COMPOSITING)
1504 allFlagsSet &= hasNotIsolatedBlendingDescendants;
1505#endif
1506 if (allFlagsSet)
1507 break;
1508 }
1509
1510 m_hasVisibleDescendant = hasVisibleDescendant;
1511 m_visibleDescendantStatusDirty = false;
1512 m_hasSelfPaintingLayerDescendant = hasSelfPaintingLayerDescendant;
1513 m_hasSelfPaintingLayerDescendantDirty = false;
1514
1515#if ENABLE(CSS_COMPOSITING)
1516 m_hasNotIsolatedBlendingDescendants = hasNotIsolatedBlendingDescendants;
1517 if (m_hasNotIsolatedBlendingDescendantsStatusDirty) {
1518 m_hasNotIsolatedBlendingDescendantsStatusDirty = false;
1519 updateSelfPaintingLayer();
1520 }
1521#endif
1522 }
1523
1524 if (m_visibleContentStatusDirty) {
1525 if (renderer().style().visibility() == Visibility::Visible)
1526 m_hasVisibleContent = true;
1527 else {
1528 // layer may be hidden but still have some visible content, check for this
1529 m_hasVisibleContent = false;
1530 RenderObject* r = renderer().firstChild();
1531 while (r) {
1532 if (r->style().visibility() == Visibility::Visible && !r->hasLayer()) {
1533 m_hasVisibleContent = true;
1534 break;
1535 }
1536 RenderObject* child = nullptr;
1537 if (!r->hasLayer() && (child = r->firstChildSlow()))
1538 r = child;
1539 else if (r->nextSibling())
1540 r = r->nextSibling();
1541 else {
1542 do {
1543 r = r->parent();
1544 if (r == &renderer())
1545 r = nullptr;
1546 } while (r && !r->nextSibling());
1547 if (r)
1548 r = r->nextSibling();
1549 }
1550 }
1551 }
1552 m_visibleContentStatusDirty = false;
1553 }
1554}

1556void RenderLayer::dirty3DTransformedDescendantStatus()
1557{
1558 RenderLayer* curr = stackingContext();
1559 if (curr)
1560 curr->m_3DTransformedDescendantStatusDirty = true;
1561
1562 // This propagates up through preserve-3d hierarchies to the enclosing flattening layer.
1563 // Note that preserves3D() creates stacking context, so we can just run up the stacking containers.
1564 while (curr && curr->preserves3D()) {
1565 curr->m_3DTransformedDescendantStatusDirty = true;
1566 curr = curr->stackingContext();
1567 }
1568}
1569
1570// Return true if this layer or any preserve-3d descendants have 3d.
1571bool RenderLayer::update3DTransformedDescendantStatus()
1572{
1573 if (m_3DTransformedDescendantStatusDirty) {
1574 m_has3DTransformedDescendant = false;
1575
1576 updateZOrderLists();
1577
1578 // Transformed or preserve-3d descendants can only be in the z-order lists, not
1579 // in the normal flow list, so we only need to check those.
1580 for (auto* layer : positiveZOrderLayers())
1581 m_has3DTransformedDescendant |= layer->update3DTransformedDescendantStatus();
1582
1583 // Now check our negative z-index children.
1584 for (auto* layer : negativeZOrderLayers())
1585 m_has3DTransformedDescendant |= layer->update3DTransformedDescendantStatus();
1586
1587 m_3DTransformedDescendantStatusDirty = false;
1588 }
1589
1590 // If we live in a 3d hierarchy, then the layer at the root of that hierarchy needs
1591 // the m_has3DTransformedDescendant set.
1592 if (preserves3D())
1593 return has3DTransform() || m_has3DTransformedDescendant;
1594
1595 return has3DTransform();
1596}
1597
1598bool RenderLayer::updateLayerPosition(OptionSet<UpdateLayerPositionsFlag>* flags)
1599{
1600 LayoutPoint localPoint;
1601 LayoutSize inlineBoundingBoxOffset; // We don't put this into the RenderLayer x/y for inlines, so we need to subtract it out when done.
1602 if (renderer().isInline() && is<RenderInline>(renderer())) {
1603 auto& inlineFlow = downcast<RenderInline>(renderer());
1604 IntRect lineBox = inlineFlow.linesBoundingBox();
1605 setSize(lineBox.size());
1606 inlineBoundingBoxOffset = toLayoutSize(lineBox.location());
1607 localPoint += inlineBoundingBoxOffset;
1608 } else if (RenderBox* box = renderBox()) {
1609 // FIXME: Is snapping the size really needed here for the RenderBox case?
1610 auto newSize = snappedIntRect(box->frameRect()).size();
1611 if (newSize != size()) {
1612 if (is<RenderWidget>(*box) && downcast<RenderWidget>(*box).requiresAcceleratedCompositing()) {
1613 // Trigger RenderLayerCompositor::requiresCompositingForFrame() which depends on the contentBoxRect size.
1614 setNeedsPostLayoutCompositingUpdate();
1615 }
1616
1617 if (flags && renderer().hasOverflowClip())
1618 flags->add(ContainingClippingLayerChangedSize);
1619
1620 setSize(newSize);
1621 }
1622
1623 box->applyTopLeftLocationOffset(localPoint);
1624 }
1625
1626 if (!renderer().isOutOfFlowPositioned()) {
1627 auto* ancestor = renderer().parent();
1628 // We must adjust our position by walking up the render tree looking for the
1629 // nearest enclosing object with a layer.
1630 while (ancestor && !ancestor->hasLayer()) {
1631 if (is<RenderBox>(*ancestor) && !is<RenderTableRow>(*ancestor)) {
1632 // Rows and cells share the same coordinate space (that of the section).
1633 // Omit them when computing our xpos/ypos.
1634 localPoint += downcast<RenderBox>(*ancestor).topLeftLocationOffset();
1635 }
1636 ancestor = ancestor->parent();
1637 }
1638 if (is<RenderTableRow>(ancestor)) {
1639 // Put ourselves into the row coordinate space.
1640 localPoint -= downcast<RenderTableRow>(*ancestor).topLeftLocationOffset();
1641 }
1642 }
1643
1644 // Subtract our parent's scroll offset.
1645 RenderLayer* positionedParent;
1646 if (renderer().isOutOfFlowPositioned() && (positionedParent = enclosingAncestorForPosition(renderer().style().position()))) {
1647 // For positioned layers, we subtract out the enclosing positioned layer's scroll offset.
1648 if (positionedParent->renderer().hasOverflowClip()) {
1649 if (auto* positionedParentScrollableArea = positionedParent->scrollableArea())
1650 localPoint -= toLayoutSize(positionedParentScrollableArea->scrollPosition());
1651 }
1652
1653 if (positionedParent->renderer().isInFlowPositioned() && is<RenderInline>(positionedParent->renderer())) {
1654 LayoutSize offset = downcast<RenderInline>(positionedParent->renderer()).offsetForInFlowPositionedInline(&downcast<RenderBox>(renderer()));
1655 localPoint += offset;
1656 }
1657
1658 ASSERT(positionedParent->contentsScrollingScope());
1659 m_boxScrollingScope = positionedParent->contentsScrollingScope();
1660 } else if (auto* parentLayer = parent()) {
1661 if (parentLayer->renderer().hasOverflowClip()) {
1662 if (auto* parentLayerScrollableArea = parentLayer->scrollableArea())
1663 localPoint -= toLayoutSize(parentLayerScrollableArea->scrollPosition());
1664 }
1665
1666 ASSERT(parentLayer->contentsScrollingScope());
1667 m_boxScrollingScope = parentLayer->contentsScrollingScope();
1668 }
1669
1670 if (hasCompositedScrollableOverflow()) {
1671 if (!m_contentsScrollingScope || m_contentsScrollingScope == m_boxScrollingScope)
1672 m_contentsScrollingScope = nextScrollingScope();
1673 } else if (!m_contentsScrollingScope || m_contentsScrollingScope != m_boxScrollingScope)
1674 m_contentsScrollingScope = m_boxScrollingScope;
1675
1676 bool positionOrOffsetChanged = false;
1677 if (renderer().isInFlowPositioned()) {
1678 LayoutSize newOffset = downcast<RenderBoxModelObject>(renderer()).offsetForInFlowPosition();
1679 positionOrOffsetChanged = newOffset != m_offsetForInFlowPosition;
1680 m_offsetForInFlowPosition = newOffset;
1681 localPoint.move(m_offsetForInFlowPosition);
1682 } else {
1683 m_offsetForInFlowPosition = LayoutSize();
1684 }
1685
1686 // FIXME: We'd really like to just get rid of the concept of a layer rectangle and rely on the renderers.
1687 localPoint -= inlineBoundingBoxOffset;
1688
1689 positionOrOffsetChanged |= location() != localPoint;
1690 setLocation(localPoint);
1691
1692 if (positionOrOffsetChanged && compositor().hasContentCompositingLayers()) {
1693 if (isComposited())
1694 setNeedsCompositingGeometryUpdate();
1695 // This layer's position can affect the location of a composited descendant (which may be a sibling in z-order),
1696 // so trigger a descendant walk from the paint-order parent.
1697 if (auto* paintParent = paintOrderParent())
1698 paintParent->setDescendantsNeedUpdateBackingAndHierarchyTraversal();
1699 }
1700
1701 return positionOrOffsetChanged;
1702}
1703
1704TransformationMatrix RenderLayer::perspectiveTransform(const LayoutRect& layerRect) const
1705{
1706 if (!is<RenderBox>(renderer()))
1707 return { };
1708
1709 auto& renderBox = downcast<RenderBox>(renderer());
1710 if (!renderBox.hasTransformRelatedProperty())
1711 return { };
1712
1713 const auto& style = renderBox.style();
1714 if (!style.hasPerspective())
1715 return { };
1716
1717 auto deviceScaleFactor = renderBox.document().deviceScaleFactor();
1718 auto referenceBox = renderBox.referenceBox(transformBoxToCSSBoxType(style.transformBox()));
1719 auto pixelSnappedReferenceBox = snapRectToDevicePixels(referenceBox, deviceScaleFactor);
1720 auto snappedLayerRect = snapRectToDevicePixels(layerRect, deviceScaleFactor);
1721
1722 auto perspectiveOrigin = pixelSnappedReferenceBox.location() - toFloatSize(snappedLayerRect.location()) + floatPointForLengthPoint(style.perspectiveOrigin(), pixelSnappedReferenceBox.size());
1723
1724 // A perspective origin of 0,0 makes the vanishing point in the center of the element.
1725 // We want it to be in the top-left, so subtract half the height and width.
1726 perspectiveOrigin -= snappedLayerRect.size() / 2.0f;
1727
1728 TransformationMatrix t;
1729 t.translate(perspectiveOrigin.x(), perspectiveOrigin.y());
1730 t.applyPerspective(style.perspective());
1731 t.translate(-perspectiveOrigin.x(), -perspectiveOrigin.y());
1732
1733 return t;
1734}
1735
1736FloatPoint RenderLayer::perspectiveOrigin() const
1737{
1738 if (!renderer().hasTransformRelatedProperty())
1739 return { };
1740
1741 auto borderBox = downcast<RenderBox>(renderer()).borderBoxRect();
1742 return floatPointForLengthPoint(renderer().style().perspectiveOrigin(), borderBox.size());
1743}

1746{

1748 case PositionType::Fixed:

1751 case PositionType::Absolute:

1753
1754 default:

1756 return false;
1757 }

1760bool RenderLayer::ancestorLayerIsInContainingBlockChain(const RenderLayer& ancestor, const RenderLayer* checkLimit) const
1761{
1762 if (&ancestor == this)
1763 return true;
1764
1765 for (const auto* currentBlock = renderer().containingBlock(); currentBlock && !is<RenderView>(*currentBlock); currentBlock = currentBlock->containingBlock()) {
1766 auto* currLayer = currentBlock->layer();
1767 if (currLayer == &ancestor)
1768 return true;
1769
1770 if (currLayer && currLayer == checkLimit)
1771 return false;
1772 }
1773
1774 return false;
1775}

1820RenderLayer* RenderLayer::enclosingScrollableLayer(IncludeSelfOrNot includeSelf, CrossFrameBoundaries crossFrameBoundaries) const
1821{
1822 RenderTreeMutationDisallowedScope renderTreeMutationDisallowedScope;
1823
1824 auto isConsideredScrollable = [](const RenderLayer& layer) {
1825 return is<RenderBox>(layer.renderer()) && downcast<RenderBox>(layer.renderer()).canBeScrolledAndHasScrollableArea();
1826 };
1827
1828 if (includeSelf == IncludeSelfOrNot::IncludeSelf && isConsideredScrollable(*this))
1829 return const_cast<RenderLayer*>(this);
1830
1831 for (auto* nextLayer = enclosingContainingBlockLayer(crossFrameBoundaries); nextLayer; nextLayer = nextLayer->enclosingContainingBlockLayer(crossFrameBoundaries)) {
1832 if (isConsideredScrollable(*nextLayer))
1833 return nextLayer;
1834 }
1835
1836 return nullptr;
1837}

1849{

1851 return true;

1854 // layout, don't need to be repainted. They just need to be recomposited.

1902 return const_cast<RenderLayer*>(&layer);

1907 return nullptr;
1908 };

1942// FIXME: This needs a better name.
1943void RenderLayer::setFilterBackendNeedsRepaintingInRect(const LayoutRect& rect)
1944{
1945 ASSERT(requiresFullLayerImageForFilters());
1946 ASSERT(m_filters);
1947
1948 if (rect.isEmpty())
1949 return;
1950
1951 LayoutRect rectForRepaint = rect;
1952 rectForRepaint += filterOutsets();
1953
1954 m_filters->expandDirtySourceRect(rectForRepaint);
1955
1956 RenderLayer* parentLayer = enclosingFilterRepaintLayer();
1957 ASSERT(parentLayer);
1958 FloatQuad repaintQuad(rectForRepaint);
1959 LayoutRect parentLayerRect = renderer().localToContainerQuad(repaintQuad, &parentLayer->renderer()).enclosingBoundingBox();
1960
1961 if (parentLayer->isComposited()) {
1962 if (!parentLayer->backing()->paintsIntoWindow()) {
1963 parentLayer->setBackingNeedsRepaintInRect(parentLayerRect);
1964 return;
1965 }
1966 // If the painting goes to window, redirect the painting to the parent RenderView.
1967 parentLayer = renderer().view().layer();
1968 parentLayerRect = renderer().localToContainerQuad(repaintQuad, &parentLayer->renderer()).enclosingBoundingBox();
1969 }
1970
1971 if (parentLayer->paintsWithFilters()) {
1972 parentLayer->setFilterBackendNeedsRepaintingInRect(parentLayerRect);
1973 return;
1974 }
1975
1976 if (parentLayer->isRenderViewLayer()) {
1977 downcast<RenderView>(parentLayer->renderer()).repaintViewRectangle(parentLayerRect);
1978 return;
1979 }
1980
1981 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1982}

1993RenderLayer* RenderLayer::clippingRootForPainting() const
1994{
1995 if (isComposited())
1996 return const_cast<RenderLayer*>(this);
1997
1998 if (paintsIntoProvidedBacking())
1999 return backingProviderLayer();
2000
2001 const RenderLayer* current = this;
2002 while (current) {
2003 if (current->isRenderViewLayer())
2004 return const_cast<RenderLayer*>(current);
2005
2006 current = current->paintOrderParent();
2007 ASSERT(current);
2008 if (current->transform() || compositedWithOwnBackingStore(*current))
2009 return const_cast<RenderLayer*>(current);
2010
2011 if (current->paintsIntoProvidedBacking())
2012 return current->backingProviderLayer();
2013 }
2014
2015 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
2016 return nullptr;
2017}

2048enum TransparencyClipBoxBehavior {
2049 PaintingTransparencyClipBox,
2050 HitTestingTransparencyClipBox
2051};
2052
2053enum TransparencyClipBoxMode {
2054 DescendantsOfTransparencyClipBox,
2055 RootOfTransparencyClipBox
2056};
2057
2058static LayoutRect transparencyClipBox(const RenderLayer&, const RenderLayer* rootLayer, TransparencyClipBoxBehavior, TransparencyClipBoxMode, OptionSet<PaintBehavior> = { });
2059
2060static void expandClipRectForDescendantsAndReflection(LayoutRect& clipRect, const RenderLayer& layer, const RenderLayer* rootLayer,
2061 TransparencyClipBoxBehavior transparencyBehavior, OptionSet<PaintBehavior> paintBehavior)
2062{
2063 // If we have a mask, then the clip is limited to the border box area (and there is
2064 // no need to examine child layers).
2065 if (!layer.renderer().hasMask()) {
2066 // Note: we don't have to walk z-order lists since transparent elements always establish
2067 // a stacking container. This means we can just walk the layer tree directly.
2068 for (RenderLayer* curr = layer.firstChild(); curr; curr = curr->nextSibling()) {
2069 if (!layer.isReflectionLayer(*curr))
2070 clipRect.unite(transparencyClipBox(*curr, rootLayer, transparencyBehavior, DescendantsOfTransparencyClipBox, paintBehavior));
2071 }
2072 }
2073
2074 // If we have a reflection, then we need to account for that when we push the clip. Reflect our entire
2075 // current transparencyClipBox to catch all child layers.
2076 // FIXME: Accelerated compositing will eventually want to do something smart here to avoid incorporating this
2077 // size into the parent layer.
2078 if (layer.renderer().hasReflection()) {
2079 LayoutSize delta = layer.offsetFromAncestor(rootLayer);
2080 clipRect.move(-delta);
2081 clipRect.unite(layer.renderBox()->reflectedRect(clipRect));
2082 clipRect.move(delta);
2083 }
2084}
2085
2086static LayoutRect transparencyClipBox(const RenderLayer& layer, const RenderLayer* rootLayer, TransparencyClipBoxBehavior transparencyBehavior,
2087 TransparencyClipBoxMode transparencyMode, OptionSet<PaintBehavior> paintBehavior)
2088{
2089 // FIXME: Although this function completely ignores CSS-imposed clipping, we did already intersect with the
2090 // paintDirtyRect, and that should cut down on the amount we have to paint. Still it
2091 // would be better to respect clips.
2092
2093 if (rootLayer != &layer && ((transparencyBehavior == PaintingTransparencyClipBox && layer.paintsWithTransform(paintBehavior))
2094 || (transparencyBehavior == HitTestingTransparencyClipBox && layer.hasTransform()))) {
2095 // The best we can do here is to use enclosed bounding boxes to establish a "fuzzy" enough clip to encompass
2096 // the transformed layer and all of its children.
2097 RenderLayer::PaginationInclusionMode mode = transparencyBehavior == HitTestingTransparencyClipBox ? RenderLayer::IncludeCompositedPaginatedLayers : RenderLayer::ExcludeCompositedPaginatedLayers;
2098 const RenderLayer* paginationLayer = transparencyMode == DescendantsOfTransparencyClipBox ? layer.enclosingPaginationLayer(mode) : nullptr;
2099 const RenderLayer* rootLayerForTransform = paginationLayer ? paginationLayer : rootLayer;
2100 LayoutSize delta = layer.offsetFromAncestor(rootLayerForTransform);
2101
2102 TransformationMatrix transform;
2103 transform.translate(delta.width(), delta.height());
2104 transform.multiply(*layer.transform());
2105
2106 // We don't use fragment boxes when collecting a transformed layer's bounding box, since it always
2107 // paints unfragmented.
2108 LayoutRect clipRect = layer.boundingBox(&layer);
2109 expandClipRectForDescendantsAndReflection(clipRect, layer, &layer, transparencyBehavior, paintBehavior);
2110 clipRect += layer.filterOutsets();
2111 LayoutRect result = transform.mapRect(clipRect);
2112 if (!paginationLayer)
2113 return result;
2114
2115 // We have to break up the transformed extent across our columns.
2116 // Split our box up into the actual fragment boxes that render in the columns/pages and unite those together to
2117 // get our true bounding box.
2118 auto& enclosingFragmentedFlow = downcast<RenderFragmentedFlow>(paginationLayer->renderer());
2119 result = enclosingFragmentedFlow.fragmentsBoundingBox(result);
2120 result.move(paginationLayer->offsetFromAncestor(rootLayer));
2121 return result;
2122 }
2123
2124 LayoutRect clipRect = layer.boundingBox(rootLayer, layer.offsetFromAncestor(rootLayer), transparencyBehavior == HitTestingTransparencyClipBox ? RenderLayer::UseFragmentBoxesIncludingCompositing : RenderLayer::UseFragmentBoxesExcludingCompositing);
2125 expandClipRectForDescendantsAndReflection(clipRect, layer, rootLayer, transparencyBehavior, paintBehavior);
2126 clipRect += layer.filterOutsets();
2127
2128 return clipRect;
2129}

2131static LayoutRect paintingExtent(const RenderLayer& currentLayer, const RenderLayer* rootLayer, const LayoutRect& paintDirtyRect, OptionSet<PaintBehavior> paintBehavior)
2132{
2133 return intersection(transparencyClipBox(currentLayer, rootLayer, PaintingTransparencyClipBox, RootOfTransparencyClipBox, paintBehavior), paintDirtyRect);

2136void RenderLayer::beginTransparencyLayers(GraphicsContext& context, const LayerPaintingInfo& paintingInfo, const LayoutRect& dirtyRect)
2137{
2138 if (context.paintingDisabled() || (paintsWithTransparency(paintingInfo.paintBehavior) && m_usedTransparency))
2139 return;
2140
2141 RenderLayer* ancestor = transparentPaintingAncestor();
2142 if (ancestor)
2143 ancestor->beginTransparencyLayers(context, paintingInfo, dirtyRect);
2144
2145 if (paintsWithTransparency(paintingInfo.paintBehavior)) {
2146 ASSERT(isCSSStackingContext());
2147 m_usedTransparency = true;
2148 context.save();
2149 LayoutRect adjustedClipRect = paintingExtent(*this, paintingInfo.rootLayer, dirtyRect, paintingInfo.paintBehavior);
2150 adjustedClipRect.move(paintingInfo.subpixelOffset);
2151 FloatRect pixelSnappedClipRect = snapRectToDevicePixels(adjustedClipRect, renderer().document().deviceScaleFactor());

2153
2154#if ENABLE(CSS_COMPOSITING)

2156 if (usesCompositeOperation)

2158#endif
2159
2160 context.beginTransparencyLayer(renderer().opacity());
2161
2162#if ENABLE(CSS_COMPOSITING)
2163 if (usesCompositeOperation)
2164 context.setCompositeOperation(context.compositeOperation(), BlendMode::Normal);
2165#endif
2166
2167#ifdef REVEAL_TRANSPARENCY_LAYERS
2168 context.setFillColor(SRGBA<uint8_t> { 0, 0, 128, 51 });
2169 context.fillRect(pixelSnappedClipRect);
2170#endif
2171 }

2217
2218// Returns the layer reached on the walk up towards the ancestor.
2219static inline const RenderLayer* accumulateOffsetTowardsAncestor(const RenderLayer* layer, const RenderLayer* ancestorLayer, LayoutPoint& location, RenderLayer::ColumnOffsetAdjustment adjustForColumns)
2220{
2221 ASSERT(ancestorLayer != layer);
2222
2223 const RenderLayerModelObject& renderer = layer->renderer();
2224 auto position = renderer.style().position();
2225
2226 // FIXME: Special casing RenderFragmentedFlow so much for fixed positioning here is not great.
2227 RenderFragmentedFlow* fixedFragmentedFlowContainer = position == PositionType::Fixed ? renderer.enclosingFragmentedFlow() : nullptr;
2228 if (fixedFragmentedFlowContainer && !fixedFragmentedFlowContainer->isOutOfFlowPositioned())
2229 fixedFragmentedFlowContainer = nullptr;
2230
2231 // FIXME: Positioning of out-of-flow(fixed, absolute) elements collected in a RenderFragmentedFlow
2232 // may need to be revisited in a future patch.
2233 // If the fixed renderer is inside a RenderFragmentedFlow, we should not compute location using localToAbsolute,
2234 // since localToAbsolute maps the coordinates from named flow to regions coordinates and regions can be
2235 // positioned in a completely different place in the viewport (RenderView).
2236 if (position == PositionType::Fixed && !fixedFragmentedFlowContainer && (!ancestorLayer || ancestorLayer == renderer.view().layer())) {
2237 // If the fixed layer's container is the root, just add in the offset of the view. We can obtain this by calling
2238 // localToAbsolute() on the RenderView.
2239 FloatPoint absPos = renderer.localToAbsolute(FloatPoint(), IsFixed);
2240 location += LayoutSize(absPos.x(), absPos.y());
2241 return ancestorLayer;
2242 }
2243
2244 // For the fixed positioned elements inside a render flow thread, we should also skip the code path below
2245 // Otherwise, for the case of ancestorLayer == rootLayer and fixed positioned element child of a transformed
2246 // element in render flow thread, we will hit the fixed positioned container before hitting the ancestor layer.
2247 if (position == PositionType::Fixed && !fixedFragmentedFlowContainer) {
2248 // For a fixed layers, we need to walk up to the root to see if there's a fixed position container
2249 // (e.g. a transformed layer). It's an error to call offsetFromAncestor() across a layer with a transform,
2250 // so we should always find the ancestor at or before we find the fixed position container.
2251 RenderLayer* fixedPositionContainerLayer = nullptr;
2252 bool foundAncestor = false;
2253 for (RenderLayer* currLayer = layer->parent(); currLayer; currLayer = currLayer->parent()) {
2254 if (currLayer == ancestorLayer)
2255 foundAncestor = true;
2256
2257 if (isContainerForPositioned(*currLayer, PositionType::Fixed)) {
2258 fixedPositionContainerLayer = currLayer;
2259 ASSERT_UNUSED(foundAncestor, foundAncestor);
2260 break;
2261 }
2262 }
2263
2264 ASSERT(fixedPositionContainerLayer); // We should have hit the RenderView's layer at least.
2265
2266 if (fixedPositionContainerLayer != ancestorLayer) {
2267 LayoutSize fixedContainerCoords = layer->offsetFromAncestor(fixedPositionContainerLayer);
2268 LayoutSize ancestorCoords = ancestorLayer->offsetFromAncestor(fixedPositionContainerLayer);
2269 location += (fixedContainerCoords - ancestorCoords);
2270 return ancestorLayer;
2271 }
2272 }
2273
2274 if (position == PositionType::Fixed && fixedFragmentedFlowContainer) {
2275 ASSERT(ancestorLayer);
2276 if (ancestorLayer == renderer.view().layer()) {
2277 // Add location in flow thread coordinates.
2278 location += toLayoutSize(layer->location());
2279
2280 // Add flow thread offset in view coordinates since the view may be scrolled.
2281 FloatPoint absPos = renderer.view().localToAbsolute(FloatPoint(), IsFixed);
2282 location += LayoutSize(absPos.x(), absPos.y());
2283 return ancestorLayer;
2284 }
2285 }
2286
2287 RenderLayer* parentLayer;
2288 if (position == PositionType::Absolute || position == PositionType::Fixed) {
2289 // Do what enclosingAncestorForPosition() does, but check for ancestorLayer along the way.
2290 parentLayer = layer->parent();
2291 bool foundAncestorFirst = false;
2292 while (parentLayer) {
2293 // RenderFragmentedFlow is a positioned container, child of RenderView, positioned at (0,0).
2294 // This implies that, for out-of-flow positioned elements inside a RenderFragmentedFlow,
2295 // we are bailing out before reaching root layer.
2296 if (isContainerForPositioned(*parentLayer, position))
2297 break;
2298
2299 if (parentLayer == ancestorLayer) {
2300 foundAncestorFirst = true;
2301 break;
2302 }
2303
2304 parentLayer = parentLayer->parent();
2305 }
2306
2307 // We should not reach RenderView layer past the RenderFragmentedFlow layer for any
2308 // children of the RenderFragmentedFlow.
2309 if (renderer.enclosingFragmentedFlow())
2310 ASSERT(parentLayer != renderer.view().layer());
2311
2312 if (foundAncestorFirst) {
2313 // Found ancestorLayer before the abs. positioned container, so compute offset of both relative
2314 // to enclosingAncestorForPosition and subtract.
2315 RenderLayer* positionedAncestor = parentLayer->enclosingAncestorForPosition(position);
2316 LayoutSize thisCoords = layer->offsetFromAncestor(positionedAncestor);
2317 LayoutSize ancestorCoords = ancestorLayer->offsetFromAncestor(positionedAncestor);
2318 location += (thisCoords - ancestorCoords);
2319 return ancestorLayer;
2320 }
2321 } else
2322 parentLayer = layer->parent();
2323
2324 if (!parentLayer)
2325 return nullptr;
2326
2327 location += toLayoutSize(layer->location());
2328
2329 if (adjustForColumns == RenderLayer::AdjustForColumns) {
2330 auto* parentLayer = layer->parent();
2331 if (parentLayer && parentLayer != ancestorLayer) {
2332 if (is<RenderMultiColumnFlow>(parentLayer->renderer())) {
2333 if (auto* fragment = downcast<RenderMultiColumnFlow>(parentLayer->renderer()).physicalTranslationFromFlowToFragment(location))
2334 location.moveBy(fragment->topLeftLocation() + -parentLayer->renderBox()->topLeftLocation());
2335 }
2336 }
2337 }
2338
2339 return parentLayer;
2340}
2341
2342LayoutPoint RenderLayer::convertToLayerCoords(const RenderLayer* ancestorLayer, const LayoutPoint& location, ColumnOffsetAdjustment adjustForColumns) const
2343{
2344 if (ancestorLayer == this)
2345 return location;
2346
2347 const RenderLayer* currLayer = this;
2348 LayoutPoint locationInLayerCoords = location;
2349 while (currLayer && currLayer != ancestorLayer)
2350 currLayer = accumulateOffsetTowardsAncestor(currLayer, ancestorLayer, locationInLayerCoords, adjustForColumns);
2351 return locationInLayerCoords;
2352}
2353
2354LayoutSize RenderLayer::offsetFromAncestor(const RenderLayer* ancestorLayer, ColumnOffsetAdjustment adjustForColumns) const
2355{
2356 return toLayoutSize(convertToLayerCoords(ancestorLayer, LayoutPoint(), adjustForColumns));
2357}
