2359static inline bool frameElementAndViewPermitScroll(HTMLFrameElementBase* frameElementBase, FrameView& frameView)
2360{
2361 // If scrollbars aren't explicitly forbidden, permit scrolling.
2362 if (frameElementBase && frameElementBase->scrollingMode() != ScrollbarAlwaysOff)
2363 return true;
2364
2365 // If scrollbars are forbidden, user initiated scrolls should obviously be ignored.
2366 if (frameView.wasScrolledByUser())
2367 return false;
2368
2369 // Forbid autoscrolls when scrollbars are off, but permits other programmatic scrolls,
2370 // like navigation to an anchor.
2371 return !frameView.frame().eventHandler().autoscrollInProgress();
2372}
2373
2374bool RenderLayer::allowsCurrentScroll() const
2375{
2376 if (!renderer().hasOverflowClip())
2377 return false;
2378
2379 // Don't scroll to reveal an overflow layer that is restricted by the -webkit-line-clamp property.
2380 // FIXME: Is this still needed? It used to be relevant for Safari RSS.
2381 if (renderer().parent() && !renderer().parent()->style().lineClamp().isNone())
2382 return false;
2383
2384 RenderBox* box = renderBox();
2385 ASSERT(box); // Only boxes can have overflowClip set.
2386
2387 if (renderer().frame().eventHandler().autoscrollInProgress()) {
2388 // The "programmatically" here is misleading; this asks whether the box has scrollable overflow,
2389 // or is a special case like a form control.
2390 return box->canBeProgramaticallyScrolled();
2391 }
2392
2393 // Programmatic scrolls can scroll overflow:hidden.
2394 return box->hasHorizontalOverflow() || box->hasVerticalOverflow();
2395}
2396
2397void RenderLayer::scrollRectToVisible(const LayoutRect& absoluteRect, bool insideFixed, const ScrollRectToVisibleOptions& options)
2398{
2399 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Scrolling, stream << "Layer " << this << " scrollRectToVisible " << absoluteRect);
2400
2401 LayoutRect newRect = absoluteRect;
2402 FrameView& frameView = renderer().view().frameView();
2403 auto* parentLayer = enclosingContainingBlockLayer(CrossFrameBoundaries::No);
2404
2405 auto scrollPositionChangeOptionsForElement = [this, options](Element* element)
2406 {
2407 auto scrollPositionOptions = ScrollPositionChangeOptions::createProgrammatic();
2408 if (!renderer().frame().eventHandler().autoscrollInProgress() && element && useSmoothScrolling(options.behavior, element, options.overrideFeatureEnablement))
2409 scrollPositionOptions.animated = AnimatedScroll::Yes;
2410 return scrollPositionOptions;
2411 };
2412
2413 if (allowsCurrentScroll()) {
2414 auto* scrollableArea = ensureLayerScrollableArea();
2415
2416 // Don't scroll to reveal an overflow layer that is restricted by the -webkit-line-clamp property.
2417 // This will prevent us from revealing text hidden by the slider in Safari RSS.
2418 RenderBox* box = renderBox();
2419 ASSERT(box);
2420 LayoutRect localExposeRect(box->absoluteToLocalQuad(FloatQuad(FloatRect(absoluteRect))).boundingBox());
2421
2422 // localExposedRect is now the absolute rect in local coordinates, but relative to the
2423 // border edge. Make the rectangle relative to the scrollable area.
2424 localExposeRect.moveBy(-LayoutPoint(box->borderLeft(), box->borderTop()));
2425
2426 if (box->shouldPlaceVerticalScrollbarOnLeft()) {
2427 // For `direction: rtl; writing-mode: horizontal-{tb,bt}` and `writing-mode: vertical-rl`
2428 // boxes, the scroll bar is on the left side. The visible rect starts from the right side
2429 // of the scroll bar. So the x of localExposeRect should start from the same position too.
2430 localExposeRect.moveBy(LayoutPoint(-scrollableArea->verticalScrollbarWidth(), 0));
2431 }
2432 LayoutRect layerBounds(0_lu, 0_lu, box->clientWidth(), box->clientHeight());
2433 expandScrollRectToVisibleTargetRectToIncludeScrollPadding(box, layerBounds, localExposeRect);
2434 LayoutRect revealRect = getRectToExpose(layerBounds, localExposeRect, insideFixed, options.alignX, options.alignY);
2435
2436 if (auto result = scrollableArea->updateScrollPosition(scrollPositionChangeOptionsForElement(box->element()), revealRect, localExposeRect))
2437 newRect = result.value();
2438 } else if (!parentLayer) {
2439 HTMLFrameOwnerElement* ownerElement = renderer().document().ownerElement();
2440
2441 if (ownerElement && ownerElement->renderer()) {
2442 HTMLFrameElementBase* frameElementBase = nullptr;
2443
2444 if (is<HTMLFrameElementBase>(*ownerElement))
2445 frameElementBase = downcast<HTMLFrameElementBase>(ownerElement);
2446
2447 if (frameElementAndViewPermitScroll(frameElementBase, frameView)) {
2448 // If this assertion fires we need to protect the ownerElement from being destroyed.
2449 ScriptDisallowedScope::InMainThread scriptDisallowedScope;
2450
2451 LayoutRect viewRect = frameView.visibleContentRect(ScrollableArea::LegacyIOSDocumentVisibleRect);
2452
2453 auto* element = ownerElement->contentDocument() ? ownerElement->contentDocument()->documentElement() : nullptr;
2454 RenderBox* renderer = element ? element->renderBox() : nullptr;
2455 expandScrollRectToVisibleTargetRectToIncludeScrollPadding(renderer, viewRect, newRect);
2456
2457 LayoutRect exposeRect = getRectToExpose(viewRect, newRect, insideFixed, options.alignX, options.alignY);
2458 IntPoint scrollPosition(roundedIntPoint(exposeRect.location()));
2459
2460 // Adjust offsets if they're outside of the allowable range.
2461 scrollPosition = scrollPosition.constrainedBetween(IntPoint(), IntPoint(frameView.contentsSize()));
2462
2463 // FIXME: Should we use contentDocument()->scrollingElement()?
2464 // See https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=205059
2465 frameView.setScrollPosition(scrollPosition, scrollPositionChangeOptionsForElement(element));
2466
2467 if (options.shouldAllowCrossOriginScrolling == ShouldAllowCrossOriginScrolling::Yes || frameView.safeToPropagateScrollToParent()) {
2468 if (auto* enclosingLayer = ownerElement->renderer()->enclosingLayer())
2469 parentLayer = enclosingLayer->enclosingScrollableLayer(IncludeSelfOrNot::IncludeSelf, CrossFrameBoundaries::No);
2470 // Convert the rect into the coordinate space of the parent frame's document.
2471 newRect = frameView.contentsToContainingViewContents(enclosingIntRect(newRect));
2472 insideFixed = false; // FIXME: ideally need to determine if this <iframe> is inside position:fixed.
2473 } else
2474 parentLayer = nullptr;
2475 }
2476 } else {
2477 if (options.revealMode == SelectionRevealMode::RevealUpToMainFrame && frameView.frame().isMainFrame())
2478 return;
2479
2480 auto minScrollPosition = frameView.minimumScrollPosition();
2481 auto maxScrollPosition = frameView.maximumScrollPosition();
2482
2483#if !PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
2484 LayoutRect viewRect = frameView.visibleContentRect();
2485#else
2486 // FIXME: ContentInsets should be taken care of in UI process side. webkit.org/b/199682
2487 // To do that, getRectToExpose needs to return the additional scrolling to do beyond content rect.
2488 LayoutRect viewRect = frameView.viewRectExpandedByContentInsets();
2489
2490 // FIXME: webkit.org/b/199683 FrameView::visibleContentRect is wrong when content insets are present
2491 maxScrollPosition = frameView.scrollPositionFromOffset(ScrollPosition(frameView.totalContentsSize() - flooredIntSize(viewRect.size())));
2492
2493 auto contentInsets = page().contentInsets();
2494 minScrollPosition.move(-contentInsets.left(), -contentInsets.top());
2495 maxScrollPosition.move(contentInsets.right(), contentInsets.bottom());
2496#endif
2497 // Move the target rect into "scrollView contents" coordinates.
2498 LayoutRect targetRect = absoluteRect;
2499 targetRect.move(0, frameView.headerHeight());
2500
2501 auto* element = frameView.frame().document() ? frameView.frame().document()->documentElement() : nullptr;
2502 RenderBox* renderer = element ? element->renderBox() : nullptr;
2503 expandScrollRectToVisibleTargetRectToIncludeScrollPadding(renderer, viewRect, targetRect);
2504
2505 LayoutRect revealRect = getRectToExpose(viewRect, targetRect, insideFixed, options.alignX, options.alignY);
2506 // Avoid scrolling to the rounded value of revealRect.location() if we don't actually need to scroll
2507 if (revealRect != viewRect) {
2508 // FIXME: Should we use document()->scrollingElement()?
2509 // See https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=205059
2510 ScrollOffset clampedScrollPosition = roundedIntPoint(revealRect.location()).constrainedBetween(minScrollPosition, maxScrollPosition);
2511 frameView.setScrollPosition(clampedScrollPosition, scrollPositionChangeOptionsForElement(element));
2512 }
2513
2514 // This is the outermost view of a web page, so after scrolling this view we
2515 // scroll its container by calling Page::scrollRectIntoView.
2516 // This only has an effect on the Mac platform in applications
2517 // that put web views into scrolling containers, such as Mac OS X Mail.
2518 // The canAutoscroll function in EventHandler also knows about this.
2519 page().chrome().scrollRectIntoView(snappedIntRect(absoluteRect));
2520 }
2521 }
2522
2523 if (parentLayer)
2524 parentLayer->scrollRectToVisible(newRect, insideFixed, options);
2525}
2526
2527LayoutRect RenderLayer::getRectToExpose(const LayoutRect& visibleRect, const LayoutRect& exposeRect, bool insideFixed, const ScrollAlignment& alignX, const ScrollAlignment& alignY) const
2528{
2529 FrameView& frameView = renderer().view().frameView();
2530 if (renderer().isRenderView() && insideFixed) {
2531 // If the element is inside position:fixed and we're not scaled, no amount of scrolling is going to move things around.
2532 if (frameView.frameScaleFactor() == 1)
2533 return visibleRect;
2534
2535 if (renderer().settings().visualViewportEnabled()) {
2536 // exposeRect is in absolute coords, affected by page scale. Unscale it.
2537 LayoutRect unscaledExposeRect = exposeRect;
2538 unscaledExposeRect.scale(1 / frameView.frameScaleFactor());
2539 unscaledExposeRect.move(0, -frameView.headerHeight());
2540
2541 // These are both in unscaled coordinates.
2542 LayoutRect layoutViewport = frameView.layoutViewportRect();
2543 LayoutRect visualViewport = frameView.visualViewportRect();
2544
2545 // The rect to expose may be partially offscreen, which we can't do anything about with position:fixed.
2546 unscaledExposeRect.intersect(layoutViewport);
2547 // Make sure it's not larger than the visual viewport; if so, we'll just move to the top left.
2548 unscaledExposeRect.setSize(unscaledExposeRect.size().shrunkTo(visualViewport.size()));
2549
2550 // Compute how much we have to move the visualViewport to reveal the part of the layoutViewport that contains exposeRect.
2551 LayoutRect requiredVisualViewport = getRectToExpose(visualViewport, unscaledExposeRect, false, alignX, alignY);
2552 // Scale it back up.
2553 requiredVisualViewport.scale(frameView.frameScaleFactor());
2554 requiredVisualViewport.move(0, frameView.headerHeight());
2555 return requiredVisualViewport;
2556 }
2557 }
2558
2559 // Determine the appropriate X behavior.
2560 ScrollAlignment::Behavior scrollX;
2561 LayoutRect exposeRectX(exposeRect.x(), visibleRect.y(), exposeRect.width(), visibleRect.height());
2562 LayoutUnit intersectWidth = intersection(visibleRect, exposeRectX).width();
2563 if (intersectWidth == exposeRect.width() || intersectWidth >= MIN_INTERSECT_FOR_REVEAL)
2564 // If the rectangle is fully visible, use the specified visible behavior.
2565 // If the rectangle is partially visible, but over a certain threshold,
2566 // then treat it as fully visible to avoid unnecessary horizontal scrolling
2567 scrollX = ScrollAlignment::getVisibleBehavior(alignX);
2568 else if (intersectWidth == visibleRect.width()) {
2569 // If the rect is bigger than the visible area, don't bother trying to center. Other alignments will work.
2570 scrollX = ScrollAlignment::getVisibleBehavior(alignX);
2571 if (scrollX == ScrollAlignment::Behavior::AlignCenter)
2572 scrollX = ScrollAlignment::Behavior::NoScroll;
2573 } else if (intersectWidth > 0)
2574 // If the rectangle is partially visible, but not above the minimum threshold, use the specified partial behavior
2575 scrollX = ScrollAlignment::getPartialBehavior(alignX);
2576 else
2577 scrollX = ScrollAlignment::getHiddenBehavior(alignX);
2578 // If we're trying to align to the closest edge, and the exposeRect is further right
2579 // than the visibleRect, and not bigger than the visible area, then align with the right.
2580 if (scrollX == ScrollAlignment::Behavior::AlignToClosestEdge && exposeRect.maxX() > visibleRect.maxX() && exposeRect.width() < visibleRect.width())
2581 scrollX = ScrollAlignment::Behavior::AlignRight;
2582
2583 // Given the X behavior, compute the X coordinate.
2584 LayoutUnit x;
2585 if (scrollX == ScrollAlignment::Behavior::NoScroll)
2586 x = visibleRect.x();
2587 else if (scrollX == ScrollAlignment::Behavior::AlignRight)
2588 x = exposeRect.maxX() - visibleRect.width();
2589 else if (scrollX == ScrollAlignment::Behavior::AlignCenter)
2590 x = exposeRect.x() + (exposeRect.width() - visibleRect.width()) / 2;
2591 else
2592 x = exposeRect.x();
2593
2594 // Determine the appropriate Y behavior.
2595 ScrollAlignment::Behavior scrollY;
2596 LayoutRect exposeRectY(visibleRect.x(), exposeRect.y(), visibleRect.width(), exposeRect.height());
2597 LayoutUnit intersectHeight = intersection(visibleRect, exposeRectY).height();
2598 if (intersectHeight == exposeRect.height())
2599 // If the rectangle is fully visible, use the specified visible behavior.
2600 scrollY = ScrollAlignment::getVisibleBehavior(alignY);
2601 else if (intersectHeight == visibleRect.height()) {
2602 // If the rect is bigger than the visible area, don't bother trying to center. Other alignments will work.
2603 scrollY = ScrollAlignment::getVisibleBehavior(alignY);
2604 if (scrollY == ScrollAlignment::Behavior::AlignCenter)
2605 scrollY = ScrollAlignment::Behavior::NoScroll;
2606 } else if (intersectHeight > 0)
2607 // If the rectangle is partially visible, use the specified partial behavior
2608 scrollY = ScrollAlignment::getPartialBehavior(alignY);
2609 else
2610 scrollY = ScrollAlignment::getHiddenBehavior(alignY);
2611 // If we're trying to align to the closest edge, and the exposeRect is further down
2612 // than the visibleRect, and not bigger than the visible area, then align with the bottom.
2613 if (scrollY == ScrollAlignment::Behavior::AlignToClosestEdge && exposeRect.maxY() > visibleRect.maxY() && exposeRect.height() < visibleRect.height())
2614 scrollY = ScrollAlignment::Behavior::AlignBottom;
2615
2616 // Given the Y behavior, compute the Y coordinate.
2617 LayoutUnit y;
2618 if (scrollY == ScrollAlignment::Behavior::NoScroll)
2619 y = visibleRect.y();
2620 else if (scrollY == ScrollAlignment::Behavior::AlignBottom)
2621 y = exposeRect.maxY() - visibleRect.height();
2622 else if (scrollY == ScrollAlignment::Behavior::AlignCenter)
2623 y = exposeRect.y() + (exposeRect.height() - visibleRect.height()) / 2;
2624 else
2625 y = exposeRect.y();
2626
2627 return LayoutRect(LayoutPoint(x, y), visibleRect.size());
2628}

2639 // hasOverflowClip(). However, they do "implicitly" clip their contents, so
2640 // we want to allow resizing them also.

2643
2644void RenderLayer::resize(const PlatformMouseEvent& evt, const LayoutSize& oldOffset)
2645{
2646 // FIXME: This should be possible on generated content but is not right now.
2647 if (!inResizeMode() || !canResize() || !renderer().element())
2648 return;
2649
2650 // FIXME: The only case where renderer->element()->renderer() != renderer is with continuations. Do they matter here?
2651 // If they do it would still be better to deal with them explicitly.
2652 Element* element = renderer().element();
2653 auto* renderer = downcast<RenderBox>(element->renderer());
2654
2655 Document& document = element->document();
2656 if (!document.frame()->eventHandler().mousePressed())
2657 return;
2658
2659 float zoomFactor = renderer->style().effectiveZoom();
2660
2661 auto absolutePoint = document.view()->windowToContents(evt.position());
2662 auto localPoint = roundedIntPoint(absoluteToContents(absolutePoint));
2663
2664 LayoutSize newOffset = offsetFromResizeCorner(localPoint);
2665 newOffset.setWidth(newOffset.width() / zoomFactor);
2666 newOffset.setHeight(newOffset.height() / zoomFactor);
2667
2668 LayoutSize currentSize = LayoutSize(renderer->width() / zoomFactor, renderer->height() / zoomFactor);
2669 LayoutSize minimumSize = element->minimumSizeForResizing().shrunkTo(currentSize);
2670 element->setMinimumSizeForResizing(minimumSize);
2671
2672 LayoutSize adjustedOldOffset = LayoutSize(oldOffset.width() / zoomFactor, oldOffset.height() / zoomFactor);
2673 if (renderer->shouldPlaceVerticalScrollbarOnLeft()) {
2674 newOffset.setWidth(-newOffset.width());
2675 adjustedOldOffset.setWidth(-adjustedOldOffset.width());
2676 }
2677
2678 LayoutSize difference = (currentSize + newOffset - adjustedOldOffset).expandedTo(minimumSize) - currentSize;
2679
2680 StyledElement* styledElement = downcast<StyledElement>(element);
2681 bool isBoxSizingBorder = renderer->style().boxSizing() == BoxSizing::BorderBox;
2682
2683 Resize resize = renderer->style().resize();
2684 if (resize != Resize::Vertical && difference.width()) {
2685 if (is<HTMLFormControlElement>(*element)) {
2686 // Make implicit margins from the theme explicit (see <http://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=9547>).
2687 styledElement->setInlineStyleProperty(CSSPropertyMarginLeft, renderer->marginLeft() / zoomFactor, CSSUnitType::CSS_PX);
2688 styledElement->setInlineStyleProperty(CSSPropertyMarginRight, renderer->marginRight() / zoomFactor, CSSUnitType::CSS_PX);
2689 }
2690 LayoutUnit baseWidth = renderer->width() - (isBoxSizingBorder ? 0_lu : renderer->horizontalBorderAndPaddingExtent());
2691 baseWidth = baseWidth / zoomFactor;
2692 styledElement->setInlineStyleProperty(CSSPropertyWidth, roundToInt(baseWidth + difference.width()), CSSUnitType::CSS_PX);
2693 }
2694
2695 if (resize != Resize::Horizontal && difference.height()) {
2696 if (is<HTMLFormControlElement>(*element)) {
2697 // Make implicit margins from the theme explicit (see <http://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=9547>).
2698 styledElement->setInlineStyleProperty(CSSPropertyMarginTop, renderer->marginTop() / zoomFactor, CSSUnitType::CSS_PX);
2699 styledElement->setInlineStyleProperty(CSSPropertyMarginBottom, renderer->marginBottom() / zoomFactor, CSSUnitType::CSS_PX);
2700 }
2701 LayoutUnit baseHeight = renderer->height() - (isBoxSizingBorder ? 0_lu : renderer->verticalBorderAndPaddingExtent());
2702 baseHeight = baseHeight / zoomFactor;
2703 styledElement->setInlineStyleProperty(CSSPropertyHeight, roundToInt(baseHeight + difference.height()), CSSUnitType::CSS_PX);
2704 }
2705
2706 document.updateLayout();
2707
2708 // FIXME (Radar 4118564): We should also autoscroll the window as necessary to keep the point under the cursor in view.
2709}

2720RenderLayer::OverflowControlRects RenderLayer::overflowControlsRects() const
2721{
2722 if (m_scrollableArea)
2723 return m_scrollableArea->overflowControlsRects();
2724
2725 ASSERT(is<RenderBox>(renderer()));
2726 auto& renderBox = downcast<RenderBox>(renderer());
2727 // Scrollbars sit inside the border box.
2728 auto overflowControlsPositioningRect = snappedIntRect(renderBox.paddingBoxRectIncludingScrollbar());
2729
2730 bool placeVerticalScrollbarOnTheLeft = renderBox.shouldPlaceVerticalScrollbarOnLeft();
2731 bool haveResizer = renderer().style().resize() != Resize::None;
2732
2733 OverflowControlRects result;
2734 auto cornerRect = [&](IntSize cornerSize) {
2735 if (placeVerticalScrollbarOnTheLeft) {
2736 auto bottomLeftCorner = overflowControlsPositioningRect.minXMaxYCorner();
2737 return IntRect { { bottomLeftCorner.x(), bottomLeftCorner.y() - cornerSize.height(), }, cornerSize };
2738 }
2739 return IntRect { overflowControlsPositioningRect.maxXMaxYCorner() - cornerSize, cornerSize };
2740 };
2741
2742 if (haveResizer) {
2743 auto scrollbarThickness = ScrollbarTheme::theme().scrollbarThickness();
2744 result.resizer = cornerRect({ scrollbarThickness, scrollbarThickness });
2745 }
2746
2747 return result;
2748}

2864void RenderLayer::clipToRect(GraphicsContext& context, const LayerPaintingInfo& paintingInfo, OptionSet<PaintBehavior> paintBehavior, const ClipRect& clipRect, BorderRadiusClippingRule rule)
2865{
2866 float deviceScaleFactor = renderer().document().deviceScaleFactor();
2867 bool needsClipping = !clipRect.isInfinite() && clipRect.rect() != paintingInfo.paintDirtyRect;
2868 if (needsClipping || clipRect.affectedByRadius())
2869 context.save();
2870
2871 if (needsClipping) {
2872 LayoutRect adjustedClipRect = clipRect.rect();
2873 adjustedClipRect.move(paintingInfo.subpixelOffset);
2874 auto snappedClipRect = snapRectToDevicePixels(adjustedClipRect, deviceScaleFactor);
2875 context.clip(snappedClipRect);
2876
2877 if (paintingInfo.eventRegionContext)
2878 paintingInfo.eventRegionContext->pushClip(enclosingIntRect(snappedClipRect));
2879 }
2880
2881 if (clipRect.affectedByRadius()) {
2882 // If the clip rect has been tainted by a border radius, then we have to walk up our layer chain applying the clips from
2883 // any layers with overflow. The condition for being able to apply these clips is that the overflow object be in our
2884 // containing block chain so we check that also.
2885 for (RenderLayer* layer = rule == IncludeSelfForBorderRadius ? this : parent(); layer; layer = layer->parent()) {
2886 if (paintBehavior.contains(PaintBehavior::CompositedOverflowScrollContent) && layer->usesCompositedScrolling())
2887 break;
2888
2889 if (layer->renderer().hasOverflowClip() && layer->renderer().style().hasBorderRadius() && ancestorLayerIsInContainingBlockChain(*layer)) {
2890 LayoutRect adjustedClipRect = LayoutRect(toLayoutPoint(layer->offsetFromAncestor(paintingInfo.rootLayer, AdjustForColumns)), layer->size());
2891 adjustedClipRect.move(paintingInfo.subpixelOffset);
2892 FloatRoundedRect roundedRect = layer->renderer().style().getRoundedInnerBorderFor(adjustedClipRect).pixelSnappedRoundedRectForPainting(deviceScaleFactor);
2893 if (roundedRect.intersectionIsRectangular(paintingInfo.paintDirtyRect))
2894 context.clip(snapRectToDevicePixels(intersection(paintingInfo.paintDirtyRect, adjustedClipRect), deviceScaleFactor));
2895 else
2896 context.clipRoundedRect(roundedRect);
2897 }
2898
2899 if (layer == paintingInfo.rootLayer)
2900 break;
2901 }
2902 }
2903}

2907 bool needsClipping = !clipRect.isInfinite() && clipRect.rect() != paintingInfo.paintDirtyRect;
2908 if (needsClipping || clipRect.affectedByRadius())
2909 context.restore();
2910
2911 if (needsClipping && paintingInfo.eventRegionContext)
2912 paintingInfo.eventRegionContext->popClip();
2913}

2915static void performOverlapTests(OverlapTestRequestMap& overlapTestRequests, const RenderLayer* rootLayer, const RenderLayer* layer)
2916{
2917 if (overlapTestRequests.isEmpty())
2918 return;
2919
2920 Vector<OverlapTestRequestClient*> overlappedRequestClients;
2921 LayoutRect boundingBox = layer->boundingBox(rootLayer, layer->offsetFromAncestor(rootLayer));
2922 for (auto& request : overlapTestRequests) {
2923 if (!boundingBox.intersects(request.value))
2924 continue;
2925
2926 request.key->setOverlapTestResult(true);
2927 overlappedRequestClients.append(request.key);
2928 }
2929 for (auto* client : overlappedRequestClients)
2930 overlapTestRequests.remove(client);
2931}

2956void RenderLayer::paintLayer(GraphicsContext& context, const LayerPaintingInfo& paintingInfo, OptionSet<PaintLayerFlag> paintFlags)
2957{
2958 auto shouldContinuePaint = [&] () {
2959 return backing()->paintsIntoWindow()
2960 || backing()->paintsIntoCompositedAncestor()
2961 || shouldDoSoftwarePaint(this, paintFlags.contains(PaintLayerFlag::PaintingReflection))
2962 || paintForFixedRootBackground(this, paintFlags);
2963 };
2964
2965 auto paintsIntoDifferentCompositedDestination = [&]() {
2966 if (paintsIntoProvidedBacking())
2967 return true;
2968
2969 if (isComposited() && !shouldContinuePaint())
2970 return true;
2971
2972 return false;
2973 };
2974
2975 if (paintsIntoDifferentCompositedDestination()) {
2976 if (!context.performingPaintInvalidation() && !(paintingInfo.paintBehavior & PaintBehavior::FlattenCompositingLayers))
2977 return;
2978
2979 paintFlags.add(PaintLayerFlag::TemporaryClipRects);
2980 }
2981
2982 if (viewportConstrainedNotCompositedReason() == NotCompositedForBoundsOutOfView) {
2983 // Don't paint out-of-view viewport constrained layers (when doing prepainting) because they will never be visible
2984 // unless their position or viewport size is changed.
2985 ASSERT(renderer().isFixedPositioned());
2986 return;
2987 }
2988
2989 paintLayerWithEffects(context, paintingInfo, paintFlags);
2990}
2991
2992void RenderLayer::paintLayerWithEffects(GraphicsContext& context, const LayerPaintingInfo& paintingInfo, OptionSet<PaintLayerFlag> paintFlags)
2993{
2994 // Non self-painting leaf layers don't need to be painted as their renderer() should properly paint itself.
2995 if (!isSelfPaintingLayer() && !hasSelfPaintingLayerDescendant())
2996 return;
2997
2998 if (shouldSuppressPaintingLayer(this))
2999 return;
3000
3001 // If this layer is totally invisible then there is nothing to paint.
3002 if (!renderer().opacity())
3003 return;
3004
3005 if (paintsWithTransparency(paintingInfo.paintBehavior))
3006 paintFlags.add(PaintLayerFlag::HaveTransparency);
3007
3008 // PaintLayerFlag::AppliedTransform is used in RenderReplica, to avoid applying the transform twice.
3009 if (paintsWithTransform(paintingInfo.paintBehavior) && !(paintFlags & PaintLayerFlag::AppliedTransform)) {
3010 TransformationMatrix layerTransform = renderableTransform(paintingInfo.paintBehavior);
3011 // If the transform can't be inverted, then don't paint anything.
3012 if (!layerTransform.isInvertible())
3013 return;
3014
3015 // If we have a transparency layer enclosing us and we are the root of a transform, then we need to establish the transparency
3016 // layer from the parent now, assuming there is a parent
3017 if (paintFlags & PaintLayerFlag::HaveTransparency) {
3018 if (parent())
3019 parent()->beginTransparencyLayers(context, paintingInfo, paintingInfo.paintDirtyRect);
3020 else
3021 beginTransparencyLayers(context, paintingInfo, paintingInfo.paintDirtyRect);
3022 }
3023
3024 if (enclosingPaginationLayer(ExcludeCompositedPaginatedLayers)) {
3025 paintTransformedLayerIntoFragments(context, paintingInfo, paintFlags);
3026 return;
3027 }
3028
3029 // Make sure the parent's clip rects have been calculated.
3030 ClipRect clipRect = paintingInfo.paintDirtyRect;
3031 if (parent()) {
3032 ClipRectsContext clipRectsContext(paintingInfo.rootLayer, (paintFlags & PaintLayerFlag::TemporaryClipRects) ? TemporaryClipRects : PaintingClipRects,
3033 IgnoreOverlayScrollbarSize, (paintFlags & PaintLayerFlag::PaintingOverflowContents) ? IgnoreOverflowClip : RespectOverflowClip);
3034 clipRect = backgroundClipRect(clipRectsContext);
3035 clipRect.intersect(paintingInfo.paintDirtyRect);
3036
3037 OptionSet<PaintBehavior> paintBehavior = PaintBehavior::Normal;
3038 if (paintFlags.contains(PaintLayerFlag::PaintingOverflowContents))
3039 paintBehavior.add(PaintBehavior::CompositedOverflowScrollContent);
3040
3041 // Push the parent coordinate space's clip.
3042 parent()->clipToRect(context, paintingInfo, paintBehavior, clipRect);
3043 }
3044
3045 paintLayerByApplyingTransform(context, paintingInfo, paintFlags);
3046
3047 // Restore the clip.
3048 if (parent())
3049 parent()->restoreClip(context, paintingInfo, clipRect);
3050
3051 return;
3052 }
3053
3054 paintLayerContentsAndReflection(context, paintingInfo, paintFlags);
3055}
3056
3057void RenderLayer::paintLayerContentsAndReflection(GraphicsContext& context, const LayerPaintingInfo& paintingInfo, OptionSet<PaintLayerFlag> paintFlags)
3058{
3059 ASSERT(isSelfPaintingLayer() || hasSelfPaintingLayerDescendant());
3060
3061 auto localPaintFlags = paintFlags - PaintLayerFlag::AppliedTransform;
3062
3063 // Paint the reflection first if we have one.
3064 if (m_reflection && !m_paintingInsideReflection) {
3065 // Mark that we are now inside replica painting.
3066 m_paintingInsideReflection = true;
3067 reflectionLayer()->paintLayer(context, paintingInfo, localPaintFlags | PaintLayerFlag::PaintingReflection);
3068 m_paintingInsideReflection = false;
3069 }
3070
3071 localPaintFlags.add(paintLayerPaintingCompositingAllPhasesFlags());
3072 paintLayerContents(context, paintingInfo, localPaintFlags);
3073}

3077 if (context.paintingDisabled())
3078 return false;
3079
3080 bool scrollingOnMainThread = true;
3081#if ENABLE(ASYNC_SCROLLING)

3089 bool isZooming = !page().chrome().client().hasStablePageScaleFactor();

3098Path RenderLayer::computeClipPath(const LayoutSize& offsetFromRoot, LayoutRect& rootRelativeBounds, WindRule& windRule) const
3099{
3100 const RenderStyle& style = renderer().style();
3101 float deviceSaleFactor = renderer().document().deviceScaleFactor();
3102
3103 if (is<ShapeClipPathOperation>(*style.clipPath())) {
3104 auto& clipPath = downcast<ShapeClipPathOperation>(*style.clipPath());
3105
3106 LayoutRect referenceBox;
3107 if (is<RenderBox>(renderer())) {
3108 referenceBox = downcast<RenderBox>(renderer()).referenceBox(clipPath.referenceBox());
3109 referenceBox.move(offsetFromRoot);
3110 } else
3111 referenceBox = rootRelativeBounds;
3112
3113 FloatRect snappedReferenceBox = snapRectToDevicePixels(referenceBox, deviceSaleFactor);
3114
3115 windRule = clipPath.windRule();
3116 return clipPath.pathForReferenceRect(snappedReferenceBox);
3117 }
3118
3119 if (is<BoxClipPathOperation>(*style.clipPath()) && is<RenderBox>(renderer())) {
3120 auto& clipPath = downcast<BoxClipPathOperation>(*style.clipPath());
3121
3122 FloatRoundedRect shapeRect = computeRoundedRectForBoxShape(clipPath.referenceBox(), downcast<RenderBox>(renderer())).pixelSnappedRoundedRectForPainting(deviceSaleFactor);
3123 shapeRect.move(offsetFromRoot);
3124
3125 windRule = WindRule::NonZero;
3126 return clipPath.pathForReferenceRect(shapeRect);
3127 }
3128
3129 return Path();
3130}

3132bool RenderLayer::setupClipPath(GraphicsContext& context, const LayerPaintingInfo& paintingInfo, const LayoutSize& offsetFromRoot)
3133{
3134 if (!renderer().hasClipPath() || context.paintingDisabled() || paintingInfo.paintDirtyRect.isEmpty())
3135 return false;
3136
3137 // SVG elements get clipped in SVG code.
3138 if (is<RenderSVGRoot>(renderer()))
3139 return false;
3140
3141 // It's not clear that this geometry is correct: https://github.com/w3c/csswg-drafts/issues/5786
3142 auto rootRelativeBounds = calculateLayerBounds(paintingInfo.rootLayer, offsetFromRoot, { UseLocalClipRectIfPossible });
3143
3144 auto& style = renderer().style();
3145 LayoutSize paintingOffsetFromRoot = LayoutSize(snapSizeToDevicePixel(offsetFromRoot + paintingInfo.subpixelOffset, LayoutPoint(), renderer().document().deviceScaleFactor()));
3146 ASSERT(style.clipPath());
3147 if (is<ShapeClipPathOperation>(*style.clipPath()) || (is<BoxClipPathOperation>(*style.clipPath()) && is<RenderBox>(renderer()))) {
3148 WindRule windRule;
3149 Path path = computeClipPath(paintingOffsetFromRoot, rootRelativeBounds, windRule);
3150 context.save();
3151 context.clipPath(path, windRule);
3152 return true;
3153 }
3154
3155 if (style.clipPath()->type() == ClipPathOperation::Reference) {
3156 ReferenceClipPathOperation* referenceClipPathOperation = static_cast<ReferenceClipPathOperation*>(style.clipPath());
3157 Element* element = renderer().document().getElementById(referenceClipPathOperation->fragment());
3158 if (element && element->renderer() && is<RenderSVGResourceClipper>(element->renderer())) {
3159 context.save();
3160 auto referenceBox = snapRectToDevicePixels(rootRelativeBounds, renderer().document().deviceScaleFactor());
3161 auto offset = referenceBox.location();
3162 context.translate(offset);
3163 FloatRect svgReferenceBox { {}, referenceBox.size() };
3164 downcast<RenderSVGResourceClipper>(*element->renderer()).applyClippingToContext(renderer(), svgReferenceBox, context);
3165 context.translate(-offset);
3166 return true;
3167 }
3168 }
3169
3170 return false;
3171}

3226void RenderLayer::paintLayerContents(GraphicsContext& context, const LayerPaintingInfo& paintingInfo, OptionSet<PaintLayerFlag> paintFlags)
3227{
3228 ASSERT(isSelfPaintingLayer() || hasSelfPaintingLayerDescendant());
3229
3230 if (context.detectingContentfulPaint() && context.contenfulPaintDetected())
3231 return;
3232
3233 auto localPaintFlags = paintFlags - PaintLayerFlag::AppliedTransform;
3234
3235 bool haveTransparency = localPaintFlags.contains(PaintLayerFlag::HaveTransparency);
3236 bool isPaintingOverlayScrollbars = localPaintFlags.contains(PaintLayerFlag::PaintingOverlayScrollbars);
3237 bool isPaintingScrollingContent = localPaintFlags.contains(PaintLayerFlag::PaintingCompositingScrollingPhase);
3238 bool isPaintingCompositedForeground = localPaintFlags.contains(PaintLayerFlag::PaintingCompositingForegroundPhase);
3239 bool isPaintingCompositedBackground = localPaintFlags.contains(PaintLayerFlag::PaintingCompositingBackgroundPhase);
3240 bool isPaintingOverflowContents = localPaintFlags.contains(PaintLayerFlag::PaintingOverflowContents);
3241 bool isCollectingEventRegion = localPaintFlags.contains(PaintLayerFlag::CollectingEventRegion);
3242
3243 bool isSelfPaintingLayer = this->isSelfPaintingLayer();
3244
3245 // Outline always needs to be painted even if we have no visible content. Also,
3246 // the outline is painted in the background phase during composited scrolling.
3247 // If it were painted in the foreground phase, it would move with the scrolled
3248 // content. When not composited scrolling, the outline is painted in the
3249 // foreground phase. Since scrolled contents are moved by repainting in this
3250 // case, the outline won't get 'dragged along'.
3251 bool shouldPaintOutline = isSelfPaintingLayer && !isPaintingOverlayScrollbars && !isCollectingEventRegion
3252 && (renderer().view().printing() || renderer().view().hasRenderersWithOutline())
3253 && ((isPaintingScrollingContent && isPaintingCompositedBackground)
3254 || (!isPaintingScrollingContent && isPaintingCompositedForeground));
3255 bool shouldPaintContent = m_hasVisibleContent && isSelfPaintingLayer && !isPaintingOverlayScrollbars && !isCollectingEventRegion;
3256
3257 if (localPaintFlags.contains(PaintLayerFlag::PaintingRootBackgroundOnly) && !renderer().isRenderView() && !renderer().isDocumentElementRenderer()) {
3258 // If beginTransparencyLayers was called prior to this, ensure the transparency state is cleaned up before returning.
3259 if (haveTransparency && m_usedTransparency && !m_paintingInsideReflection) {
3260 context.endTransparencyLayer();
3261 context.restore();
3262 m_usedTransparency = false;
3263 }
3264
3265 return;
3266 }
3267
3268 updateLayerListsIfNeeded();
3269
3270 LayoutSize offsetFromRoot = offsetFromAncestor(paintingInfo.rootLayer);
3271
3272 // FIXME: We shouldn't have to disable subpixel quantization for overflow clips or subframes once we scroll those
3273 // things on the scrolling thread.
3274 bool didQuantizeFonts = true;
3275 bool needToAdjustSubpixelQuantization = setupFontSubpixelQuantization(context, didQuantizeFonts);
3276
3277 // Apply clip-path to context.
3278 LayoutSize columnAwareOffsetFromRoot = offsetFromRoot;
3279 if (renderer().enclosingFragmentedFlow() && (renderer().hasClipPath() || filtersForPainting(context, paintFlags)))
3280 columnAwareOffsetFromRoot = toLayoutSize(convertToLayerCoords(paintingInfo.rootLayer, LayoutPoint(), AdjustForColumns));
3281
3282 bool hasClipPath = false;
3283 if (shouldApplyClipPath(paintingInfo.paintBehavior, localPaintFlags))
3284 hasClipPath = setupClipPath(context, paintingInfo, columnAwareOffsetFromRoot);
3285
3286 bool selectionAndBackgroundsOnly = paintingInfo.paintBehavior.contains(PaintBehavior::SelectionAndBackgroundsOnly);
3287 bool selectionOnly = paintingInfo.paintBehavior.contains(PaintBehavior::SelectionOnly);
3288
3289 SinglePaintFrequencyTracking singlePaintFrequencyTracking(m_paintFrequencyTracker, page().lastRenderingUpdateTimestamp());
3290
3291 LayerFragments layerFragments;
3292 RenderObject* subtreePaintRootForRenderer = nullptr;
3293
3294 auto paintBehavior = [&]() {
3295 constexpr OptionSet<PaintBehavior> flagsToCopy = { PaintBehavior::FlattenCompositingLayers, PaintBehavior::Snapshotting, PaintBehavior::ExcludeSelection };
3296 OptionSet<PaintBehavior> paintBehavior = paintingInfo.paintBehavior & flagsToCopy;
3297
3298 if (localPaintFlags.contains(PaintLayerFlag::PaintingSkipRootBackground))
3299 paintBehavior.add(PaintBehavior::SkipRootBackground);
3300 else if (localPaintFlags.contains(PaintLayerFlag::PaintingRootBackgroundOnly))
3301 paintBehavior.add(PaintBehavior::RootBackgroundOnly);
3302
3303 // FIXME: This seems wrong. We should retain the TileFirstPaint flag for all RenderLayers painted into the root tile cache.
3304 if ((paintingInfo.paintBehavior & PaintBehavior::TileFirstPaint) && isRenderViewLayer())
3305 paintBehavior.add(PaintBehavior::TileFirstPaint);
3306
3307 if (isPaintingOverflowContents)
3308 paintBehavior.add(PaintBehavior::CompositedOverflowScrollContent);
3309
3310 if (isCollectingEventRegion) {
3311 paintBehavior = paintBehavior & PaintBehavior::CompositedOverflowScrollContent;
3312 if (isPaintingCompositedForeground)
3313 paintBehavior.add(PaintBehavior::EventRegionIncludeForeground);
3314 if (isPaintingCompositedBackground)
3315 paintBehavior.add(PaintBehavior::EventRegionIncludeBackground);
3316 }
3317
3318 return paintBehavior;
3319 }();
3320
3321 { // Scope for filter-related state changes.
3322 LayerPaintingInfo localPaintingInfo(paintingInfo);
3323 GraphicsContext* filterContext = setupFilters(context, localPaintingInfo, paintFlags, columnAwareOffsetFromRoot);
3324 if (filterContext && haveTransparency) {
3325 // If we have a filter and transparency, we have to eagerly start a transparency layer here, rather than risk a child layer lazily starts one with the wrong context.
3326 beginTransparencyLayers(context, localPaintingInfo, paintingInfo.paintDirtyRect);
3327 }
3328 GraphicsContext& currentContext = filterContext ? *filterContext : context;
3329
3330 // If this layer's renderer is a child of the subtreePaintRoot, we render unconditionally, which
3331 // is done by passing a nil subtreePaintRoot down to our renderer (as if no subtreePaintRoot was ever set).
3332 // Otherwise, our renderer tree may or may not contain the subtreePaintRoot root, so we pass that root along
3333 // so it will be tested against as we descend through the renderers.
3334 if (localPaintingInfo.subtreePaintRoot && !renderer().isDescendantOf(localPaintingInfo.subtreePaintRoot))
3335 subtreePaintRootForRenderer = localPaintingInfo.subtreePaintRoot;
3336
3337 if (localPaintingInfo.overlapTestRequests && isSelfPaintingLayer)
3338 performOverlapTests(*localPaintingInfo.overlapTestRequests, localPaintingInfo.rootLayer, this);
3339
3340 LayoutRect paintDirtyRect = localPaintingInfo.paintDirtyRect;
3341 if (shouldPaintContent || shouldPaintOutline || isPaintingOverlayScrollbars || isCollectingEventRegion) {
3342 // Collect the fragments. This will compute the clip rectangles and paint offsets for each layer fragment, as well as whether or not the content of each
3343 // fragment should paint. If the parent's filter dictates full repaint to ensure proper filter effect,
3344 // use the overflow clip as dirty rect, instead of no clipping. It maintains proper clipping for overflow::scroll.
3345 if (!localPaintingInfo.clipToDirtyRect && renderer().hasOverflowClip()) {
3346 // We can turn clipping back by requesting full repaint for the overflow area.
3347 localPaintingInfo.clipToDirtyRect = true;
3348 paintDirtyRect = clipRectRelativeToAncestor(localPaintingInfo.rootLayer, offsetFromRoot, LayoutRect::infiniteRect());
3349 }
3350 collectFragments(layerFragments, localPaintingInfo.rootLayer, paintDirtyRect, ExcludeCompositedPaginatedLayers,
3351 (localPaintFlags & PaintLayerFlag::TemporaryClipRects) ? TemporaryClipRects : PaintingClipRects, IgnoreOverlayScrollbarSize,
3352 (isPaintingOverflowContents) ? IgnoreOverflowClip : RespectOverflowClip, offsetFromRoot);
3353 updatePaintingInfoForFragments(layerFragments, localPaintingInfo, localPaintFlags, shouldPaintContent, offsetFromRoot);
3354 }
3355
3356 if (isPaintingCompositedBackground) {
3357 // Paint only the backgrounds for all of the fragments of the layer.
3358 if (shouldPaintContent && !selectionOnly) {
3359 paintBackgroundForFragments(layerFragments, currentContext, context, paintingInfo.paintDirtyRect, haveTransparency,
3360 localPaintingInfo, paintBehavior, subtreePaintRootForRenderer);
3361 }
3362 }
3363
3364 // Now walk the sorted list of children with negative z-indices.
3365 if ((isPaintingScrollingContent && isPaintingOverflowContents) || (!isPaintingScrollingContent && isPaintingCompositedBackground))
3366 paintList(negativeZOrderLayers(), currentContext, localPaintingInfo, localPaintFlags);
3367
3368 if (isPaintingCompositedForeground) {
3369 if (shouldPaintContent) {
3370 paintForegroundForFragments(layerFragments, currentContext, context, paintingInfo.paintDirtyRect, haveTransparency,
3371 localPaintingInfo, paintBehavior, subtreePaintRootForRenderer);
3372 }
3373 }
3374
3375 if (isCollectingEventRegion)
3376 collectEventRegionForFragments(layerFragments, currentContext, localPaintingInfo, paintBehavior);
3377
3378 if (shouldPaintOutline)
3379 paintOutlineForFragments(layerFragments, currentContext, localPaintingInfo, paintBehavior, subtreePaintRootForRenderer);
3380
3381 if (isPaintingCompositedForeground) {
3382 // Paint any child layers that have overflow.
3383 paintList(normalFlowLayers(), currentContext, localPaintingInfo, localPaintFlags);
3384
3385 // Now walk the sorted list of children with positive z-indices.
3386 paintList(positiveZOrderLayers(), currentContext, localPaintingInfo, localPaintFlags);
3387 }
3388
3389 if (m_scrollableArea) {
3390 if (isPaintingOverlayScrollbars && m_scrollableArea->hasScrollbars())
3391 paintOverflowControlsForFragments(layerFragments, currentContext, localPaintingInfo);
3392 }
3393
3394 if (filterContext) {
3395 // When we called collectFragments() last time, paintDirtyRect was reset to represent the filter bounds.
3396 // Now we need to compute the backgroundRect uncontaminated by filters, in order to clip the filtered result.
3397 // Note that we also use paintingInfo here, not localPaintingInfo which filters also contaminated.
3398 LayerFragments layerFragments;
3399 collectFragments(layerFragments, paintingInfo.rootLayer, paintingInfo.paintDirtyRect, ExcludeCompositedPaginatedLayers,
3400 (localPaintFlags & PaintLayerFlag::TemporaryClipRects) ? TemporaryClipRects : PaintingClipRects, IgnoreOverlayScrollbarSize,
3401 (isPaintingOverflowContents) ? IgnoreOverflowClip : RespectOverflowClip, offsetFromRoot);
3402 updatePaintingInfoForFragments(layerFragments, paintingInfo, localPaintFlags, shouldPaintContent, offsetFromRoot);
3403
3404 applyFilters(context, paintingInfo, paintBehavior, layerFragments);
3405 }
3406 }
3407
3408 if (shouldPaintContent && !(selectionOnly || selectionAndBackgroundsOnly)) {
3409 if (shouldPaintMask(paintingInfo.paintBehavior, localPaintFlags)) {
3410 // Paint the mask for the fragments.
3411 paintMaskForFragments(layerFragments, context, paintingInfo, paintBehavior, subtreePaintRootForRenderer);
3412 }
3413
3414 if (!(paintFlags & PaintLayerFlag::PaintingCompositingMaskPhase) && (paintFlags & PaintLayerFlag::PaintingCompositingClipPathPhase)) {
3415 // Re-use paintChildClippingMaskForFragments to paint black for the compositing clipping mask.
3416 paintChildClippingMaskForFragments(layerFragments, context, paintingInfo, paintBehavior, subtreePaintRootForRenderer);
3417 }
3418
3419 if (localPaintFlags & PaintLayerFlag::PaintingChildClippingMaskPhase) {
3420 // Paint the border radius mask for the fragments.
3421 paintChildClippingMaskForFragments(layerFragments, context, paintingInfo, paintBehavior, subtreePaintRootForRenderer);
3422 }
3423 }
3424
3425 // End our transparency layer
3426 if (haveTransparency && m_usedTransparency && !m_paintingInsideReflection) {
3427 context.endTransparencyLayer();
3428 context.restore();
3429 m_usedTransparency = false;
3430 }
3431
3432 // Re-set this to whatever it was before we painted the layer.
3433 if (needToAdjustSubpixelQuantization)
3434 context.setShouldSubpixelQuantizeFonts(didQuantizeFonts);
3435
3436 if (hasClipPath)
3437 context.restore();
3438}

3440void RenderLayer::paintLayerByApplyingTransform(GraphicsContext& context, const LayerPaintingInfo& paintingInfo, OptionSet<PaintLayerFlag> paintFlags, const LayoutSize& translationOffset)
3441{
3442 // This involves subtracting out the position of the layer in our current coordinate space, but preserving
3443 // the accumulated error for sub-pixel layout.
3444 float deviceScaleFactor = renderer().document().deviceScaleFactor();
3445 LayoutSize offsetFromParent = offsetFromAncestor(paintingInfo.rootLayer);
3446 offsetFromParent += translationOffset;
3447 TransformationMatrix transform(renderableTransform(paintingInfo.paintBehavior));
3448 // Add the subpixel accumulation to the current layer's offset so that we can always snap the translateRight value to where the renderer() is supposed to be painting.
3449 LayoutSize offsetForThisLayer = offsetFromParent + paintingInfo.subpixelOffset;
3450 FloatSize devicePixelSnappedOffsetForThisLayer = toFloatSize(roundPointToDevicePixels(toLayoutPoint(offsetForThisLayer), deviceScaleFactor));
3451 // We handle accumulated subpixels through nested layers here. Since the context gets translated to device pixels,
3452 // all we need to do is add the delta to the accumulated pixels coming from ancestor layers.
3453 // Translate the graphics context to the snapping position to avoid off-device-pixel positing.
3454 transform.translateRight(devicePixelSnappedOffsetForThisLayer.width(), devicePixelSnappedOffsetForThisLayer.height());
3455 // Apply the transform.
3456 auto oldTransform = context.getCTM();
3457 auto affineTransform = transform.toAffineTransform();
3458 context.concatCTM(affineTransform);
3459
3460 if (paintingInfo.eventRegionContext)
3461 paintingInfo.eventRegionContext->pushTransform(affineTransform);
3462
3463 // Now do a paint with the root layer shifted to be us.
3464 LayoutSize adjustedSubpixelOffset = offsetForThisLayer - LayoutSize(devicePixelSnappedOffsetForThisLayer);
3465 LayerPaintingInfo transformedPaintingInfo(paintingInfo);
3466 transformedPaintingInfo.rootLayer = this;
3467 transformedPaintingInfo.paintDirtyRect = LayoutRect(encloseRectToDevicePixels(transform.inverse().value_or(AffineTransform()).mapRect(paintingInfo.paintDirtyRect), deviceScaleFactor));
3468 transformedPaintingInfo.subpixelOffset = adjustedSubpixelOffset;
3469 paintLayerContentsAndReflection(context, transformedPaintingInfo, paintFlags);
3470
3471 if (paintingInfo.eventRegionContext)
3472 paintingInfo.eventRegionContext->popTransform();
3473
3474 context.setCTM(oldTransform);
3475}

3477void RenderLayer::paintList(LayerList layerIterator, GraphicsContext& context, const LayerPaintingInfo& paintingInfo, OptionSet<PaintLayerFlag> paintFlags)
3478{
3479 if (layerIterator.begin() == layerIterator.end())
3480 return;
3481
3482 if (!hasSelfPaintingLayerDescendant())
3483 return;
3484
3485#if ASSERT_ENABLED
3486 LayerListMutationDetector mutationChecker(*this);
3487#endif
3488
3489 for (auto* childLayer : layerIterator)
3490 childLayer->paintLayer(context, paintingInfo, paintFlags);
3491}

3493RenderLayer* RenderLayer::enclosingPaginationLayerInSubtree(const RenderLayer* rootLayer, PaginationInclusionMode mode) const
3494{
3495 // If we don't have an enclosing layer, or if the root layer is the same as the enclosing layer,
3496 // then just return the enclosing pagination layer (it will be 0 in the former case and the rootLayer in the latter case).
3497 RenderLayer* paginationLayer = enclosingPaginationLayer(mode);
3498 if (!paginationLayer || rootLayer == paginationLayer)
3499 return paginationLayer;
3500
3501 // Walk up the layer tree and see which layer we hit first. If it's the root, then the enclosing pagination
3502 // layer isn't in our subtree and we return nullptr. If we hit the enclosing pagination layer first, then
3503 // we can return it.
3504 for (const RenderLayer* layer = this; layer; layer = layer->parent()) {
3505 if (layer == rootLayer)
3506 return nullptr;
3507 if (layer == paginationLayer)
3508 return paginationLayer;
3509 }
3510
3511 // This should never be reached, since an enclosing layer should always either be the rootLayer or be
3512 // our enclosing pagination layer.
3513 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
3514 return nullptr;
3515}
3516
3517void RenderLayer::collectFragments(LayerFragments& fragments, const RenderLayer* rootLayer, const LayoutRect& dirtyRect, PaginationInclusionMode inclusionMode,
3518 ClipRectsType clipRectsType, OverlayScrollbarSizeRelevancy inOverlayScrollbarSizeRelevancy, ShouldRespectOverflowClip respectOverflowClip, const LayoutSize& offsetFromRoot,
3519 const LayoutRect* layerBoundingBox, ShouldApplyRootOffsetToFragments applyRootOffsetToFragments)
3520{
3521 RenderLayer* paginationLayer = enclosingPaginationLayerInSubtree(rootLayer, inclusionMode);
3522 if (!paginationLayer || hasTransform()) {
3523 // For unpaginated layers, there is only one fragment.
3524 LayerFragment fragment;
3525 ClipRectsContext clipRectsContext(rootLayer, clipRectsType, inOverlayScrollbarSizeRelevancy, respectOverflowClip);
3526 calculateRects(clipRectsContext, dirtyRect, fragment.layerBounds, fragment.backgroundRect, fragment.foregroundRect, offsetFromRoot);
3527 fragments.append(fragment);
3528 return;
3529 }
3530
3531 // Compute our offset within the enclosing pagination layer.
3532 LayoutSize offsetWithinPaginatedLayer = offsetFromAncestor(paginationLayer);
3533
3534 // Calculate clip rects relative to the enclosingPaginationLayer. The purpose of this call is to determine our bounds clipped to intermediate
3535 // layers between us and the pagination context. It's important to minimize the number of fragments we need to create and this helps with that.
3536 ClipRectsContext paginationClipRectsContext(paginationLayer, clipRectsType, inOverlayScrollbarSizeRelevancy, respectOverflowClip);
3537 LayoutRect layerBoundsInFragmentedFlow;
3538 ClipRect backgroundRectInFragmentedFlow;
3539 ClipRect foregroundRectInFragmentedFlow;
3540 calculateRects(paginationClipRectsContext, LayoutRect::infiniteRect(), layerBoundsInFragmentedFlow, backgroundRectInFragmentedFlow, foregroundRectInFragmentedFlow,
3541 offsetWithinPaginatedLayer);
3542
3543 // Take our bounding box within the flow thread and clip it.
3544 LayoutRect layerBoundingBoxInFragmentedFlow = layerBoundingBox ? *layerBoundingBox : boundingBox(paginationLayer, offsetWithinPaginatedLayer);
3545 layerBoundingBoxInFragmentedFlow.intersect(backgroundRectInFragmentedFlow.rect());
3546
3547 auto& enclosingFragmentedFlow = downcast<RenderFragmentedFlow>(paginationLayer->renderer());
3548 RenderLayer* parentPaginationLayer = paginationLayer->parent()->enclosingPaginationLayerInSubtree(rootLayer, inclusionMode);
3549 LayerFragments ancestorFragments;
3550 if (parentPaginationLayer) {
3551 // Compute a bounding box accounting for fragments.
3552 LayoutRect layerFragmentBoundingBoxInParentPaginationLayer = enclosingFragmentedFlow.fragmentsBoundingBox(layerBoundingBoxInFragmentedFlow);
3553
3554 // Convert to be in the ancestor pagination context's coordinate space.
3555 LayoutSize offsetWithinParentPaginatedLayer = paginationLayer->offsetFromAncestor(parentPaginationLayer);
3556 layerFragmentBoundingBoxInParentPaginationLayer.move(offsetWithinParentPaginatedLayer);
3557
3558 // Now collect ancestor fragments.
3559 parentPaginationLayer->collectFragments(ancestorFragments, rootLayer, dirtyRect, inclusionMode, clipRectsType, inOverlayScrollbarSizeRelevancy, respectOverflowClip,
3560 offsetFromAncestor(rootLayer), &layerFragmentBoundingBoxInParentPaginationLayer, ApplyRootOffsetToFragments);
3561
3562 if (ancestorFragments.isEmpty())
3563 return;
3564
3565 for (auto& ancestorFragment : ancestorFragments) {
3566 // Shift the dirty rect into flow thread coordinates.
3567 LayoutRect dirtyRectInFragmentedFlow(dirtyRect);
3568 dirtyRectInFragmentedFlow.move(-offsetWithinParentPaginatedLayer - ancestorFragment.paginationOffset);
3569
3570 size_t oldSize = fragments.size();
3571
3572 // Tell the flow thread to collect the fragments. We pass enough information to create a minimal number of fragments based off the pages/columns
3573 // that intersect the actual dirtyRect as well as the pages/columns that intersect our layer's bounding box.
3574 enclosingFragmentedFlow.collectLayerFragments(fragments, layerBoundingBoxInFragmentedFlow, dirtyRectInFragmentedFlow);
3575
3576 size_t newSize = fragments.size();
3577
3578 if (oldSize == newSize)
3579 continue;
3580
3581 for (size_t i = oldSize; i < newSize; ++i) {
3582 LayerFragment& fragment = fragments.at(i);
3583
3584 // Set our four rects with all clipping applied that was internal to the flow thread.
3585 fragment.setRects(layerBoundsInFragmentedFlow, backgroundRectInFragmentedFlow, foregroundRectInFragmentedFlow, layerBoundingBoxInFragmentedFlow);
3586
3587 // Shift to the root-relative physical position used when painting the flow thread in this fragment.
3588 fragment.moveBy(toLayoutPoint(ancestorFragment.paginationOffset + fragment.paginationOffset + offsetWithinParentPaginatedLayer));
3589
3590 // Intersect the fragment with our ancestor's background clip so that e.g., columns in an overflow:hidden block are
3591 // properly clipped by the overflow.
3592 fragment.intersect(ancestorFragment.paginationClip);
3593
3594 // Now intersect with our pagination clip. This will typically mean we're just intersecting the dirty rect with the column
3595 // clip, so the column clip ends up being all we apply.
3596 fragment.intersect(fragment.paginationClip);
3597
3598 if (applyRootOffsetToFragments == ApplyRootOffsetToFragments)
3599 fragment.paginationOffset = fragment.paginationOffset + offsetWithinParentPaginatedLayer;
3600 }
3601 }
3602
3603 return;
3604 }
3605
3606 // Shift the dirty rect into flow thread coordinates.
3607 LayoutSize offsetOfPaginationLayerFromRoot = enclosingPaginationLayer(inclusionMode)->offsetFromAncestor(rootLayer);
3608 LayoutRect dirtyRectInFragmentedFlow(dirtyRect);
3609 dirtyRectInFragmentedFlow.move(-offsetOfPaginationLayerFromRoot);
3610
3611 // Tell the flow thread to collect the fragments. We pass enough information to create a minimal number of fragments based off the pages/columns
3612 // that intersect the actual dirtyRect as well as the pages/columns that intersect our layer's bounding box.
3613 enclosingFragmentedFlow.collectLayerFragments(fragments, layerBoundingBoxInFragmentedFlow, dirtyRectInFragmentedFlow);
3614
3615 if (fragments.isEmpty())
3616 return;
3617
3618 // Get the parent clip rects of the pagination layer, since we need to intersect with that when painting column contents.
3619 ClipRect ancestorClipRect = dirtyRect;
3620 if (paginationLayer->parent()) {
3621 ClipRectsContext clipRectsContext(rootLayer, clipRectsType, inOverlayScrollbarSizeRelevancy, respectOverflowClip);
3622 ancestorClipRect = paginationLayer->backgroundClipRect(clipRectsContext);
3623 ancestorClipRect.intersect(dirtyRect);
3624 }
3625
3626 for (auto& fragment : fragments) {
3627 // Set our four rects with all clipping applied that was internal to the flow thread.
3628 fragment.setRects(layerBoundsInFragmentedFlow, backgroundRectInFragmentedFlow, foregroundRectInFragmentedFlow, layerBoundingBoxInFragmentedFlow);
3629
3630 // Shift to the root-relative physical position used when painting the flow thread in this fragment.
3631 fragment.moveBy(toLayoutPoint(fragment.paginationOffset + offsetOfPaginationLayerFromRoot));
3632
3633 // Intersect the fragment with our ancestor's background clip so that e.g., columns in an overflow:hidden block are
3634 // properly clipped by the overflow.
3635 fragment.intersect(ancestorClipRect);
3636
3637 // Now intersect with our pagination clip. This will typically mean we're just intersecting the dirty rect with the column
3638 // clip, so the column clip ends up being all we apply.
3639 fragment.intersect(fragment.paginationClip);
3640
3641 if (applyRootOffsetToFragments == ApplyRootOffsetToFragments)
3642 fragment.paginationOffset = fragment.paginationOffset + offsetOfPaginationLayerFromRoot;
3643 }
3644}

3646void RenderLayer::updatePaintingInfoForFragments(LayerFragments& fragments, const LayerPaintingInfo& localPaintingInfo, OptionSet<PaintLayerFlag> localPaintFlags,
3647 bool shouldPaintContent, const LayoutSize& offsetFromRoot)
3648{
3649 for (auto& fragment : fragments) {
3650 fragment.shouldPaintContent = shouldPaintContent;
3651 if (this != localPaintingInfo.rootLayer || !(localPaintFlags & PaintLayerFlag::PaintingOverflowContents)) {
3652 LayoutSize newOffsetFromRoot = offsetFromRoot + fragment.paginationOffset;
3653 fragment.shouldPaintContent &= intersectsDamageRect(fragment.layerBounds, fragment.backgroundRect.rect(), localPaintingInfo.rootLayer, newOffsetFromRoot, fragment.boundingBox);
3654 }

3658void RenderLayer::paintTransformedLayerIntoFragments(GraphicsContext& context, const LayerPaintingInfo& paintingInfo, OptionSet<PaintLayerFlag> paintFlags)
3659{
3660 LayerFragments enclosingPaginationFragments;
3661 LayoutSize offsetOfPaginationLayerFromRoot;
3662 RenderLayer* paginatedLayer = enclosingPaginationLayer(ExcludeCompositedPaginatedLayers);
3663 LayoutRect transformedExtent = transparencyClipBox(*this, paginatedLayer, PaintingTransparencyClipBox, RootOfTransparencyClipBox, paintingInfo.paintBehavior);
3664 paginatedLayer->collectFragments(enclosingPaginationFragments, paintingInfo.rootLayer, paintingInfo.paintDirtyRect, ExcludeCompositedPaginatedLayers,
3665 (paintFlags & PaintLayerFlag::TemporaryClipRects) ? TemporaryClipRects : PaintingClipRects, IgnoreOverlayScrollbarSize,
3666 (paintFlags & PaintLayerFlag::PaintingOverflowContents) ? IgnoreOverflowClip : RespectOverflowClip, offsetOfPaginationLayerFromRoot, &transformedExtent);
3667
3668 for (const auto& fragment : enclosingPaginationFragments) {
3669 // Apply the page/column clip for this fragment, as well as any clips established by layers in between us and
3670 // the enclosing pagination layer.
3671 LayoutRect clipRect = fragment.backgroundRect.rect();
3672
3673 // Now compute the clips within a given fragment
3674 if (parent() != paginatedLayer) {
3675 offsetOfPaginationLayerFromRoot = toLayoutSize(paginatedLayer->convertToLayerCoords(paintingInfo.rootLayer, toLayoutPoint(offsetOfPaginationLayerFromRoot)));
3676
3677 ClipRectsContext clipRectsContext(paginatedLayer, (paintFlags & PaintLayerFlag::TemporaryClipRects) ? TemporaryClipRects : PaintingClipRects,
3678 IgnoreOverlayScrollbarSize, (paintFlags & PaintLayerFlag::PaintingOverflowContents) ? IgnoreOverflowClip : RespectOverflowClip);
3679 LayoutRect parentClipRect = backgroundClipRect(clipRectsContext).rect();
3680 parentClipRect.move(fragment.paginationOffset + offsetOfPaginationLayerFromRoot);
3681 clipRect.intersect(parentClipRect);
3682 }
3683
3684 OptionSet<PaintBehavior> paintBehavior = PaintBehavior::Normal;
3685 if (paintFlags.contains(PaintLayerFlag::PaintingOverflowContents))
3686 paintBehavior.add(PaintBehavior::CompositedOverflowScrollContent);
3687
3688 parent()->clipToRect(context, paintingInfo, paintBehavior, clipRect);
3689 paintLayerByApplyingTransform(context, paintingInfo, paintFlags, fragment.paginationOffset);
3690 parent()->restoreClip(context, paintingInfo, clipRect);
3691 }

3694void RenderLayer::paintBackgroundForFragments(const LayerFragments& layerFragments, GraphicsContext& context, GraphicsContext& contextForTransparencyLayer,
3695 const LayoutRect& transparencyPaintDirtyRect, bool haveTransparency, const LayerPaintingInfo& localPaintingInfo, OptionSet<PaintBehavior> paintBehavior,
3696 RenderObject* subtreePaintRootForRenderer)
3697{
3698 for (const auto& fragment : layerFragments) {
3699 if (!fragment.shouldPaintContent)
3700 continue;
3701
3702 // Begin transparency layers lazily now that we know we have to paint something.
3703 if (haveTransparency)
3704 beginTransparencyLayers(contextForTransparencyLayer, localPaintingInfo, transparencyPaintDirtyRect);
3705
3706 if (localPaintingInfo.clipToDirtyRect) {
3707 // Paint our background first, before painting any child layers.
3708 // Establish the clip used to paint our background.
3709 clipToRect(context, localPaintingInfo, paintBehavior, fragment.backgroundRect, DoNotIncludeSelfForBorderRadius); // Background painting will handle clipping to self.
3710 }
3711
3712 // Paint the background.
3713 // FIXME: Eventually we will collect the region from the fragment itself instead of just from the paint info.
3714 PaintInfo paintInfo(context, fragment.backgroundRect.rect(), PaintPhase::BlockBackground, paintBehavior, subtreePaintRootForRenderer, nullptr, nullptr, &localPaintingInfo.rootLayer->renderer(), this);
3715 renderer().paint(paintInfo, toLayoutPoint(fragment.layerBounds.location() - renderBoxLocation() + localPaintingInfo.subpixelOffset));
3716
3717 if (localPaintingInfo.clipToDirtyRect)
3718 restoreClip(context, localPaintingInfo, fragment.backgroundRect);
3719 }

3722void RenderLayer::paintForegroundForFragments(const LayerFragments& layerFragments, GraphicsContext& context, GraphicsContext& contextForTransparencyLayer,
3723 const LayoutRect& transparencyPaintDirtyRect, bool haveTransparency, const LayerPaintingInfo& localPaintingInfo, OptionSet<PaintBehavior> paintBehavior,
3724 RenderObject* subtreePaintRootForRenderer)
3725{
3726 // Begin transparency if we have something to paint.
3727 if (haveTransparency) {
3728 for (const auto& fragment : layerFragments) {
3729 if (fragment.shouldPaintContent && !fragment.foregroundRect.isEmpty()) {
3730 beginTransparencyLayers(contextForTransparencyLayer, localPaintingInfo, transparencyPaintDirtyRect);
3731 break;
3732 }
3733 }
3734 }
3735
3736 OptionSet<PaintBehavior> localPaintBehavior;
3737 if (localPaintingInfo.paintBehavior & PaintBehavior::ForceBlackText)
3738 localPaintBehavior = PaintBehavior::ForceBlackText;
3739 else if (localPaintingInfo.paintBehavior & PaintBehavior::ForceWhiteText)
3740 localPaintBehavior = PaintBehavior::ForceWhiteText;
3741 else
3742 localPaintBehavior = paintBehavior;
3743
3744 // FIXME: It's unclear if this flag copying is necessary.
3745 if (localPaintingInfo.paintBehavior & PaintBehavior::ExcludeSelection)
3746 localPaintBehavior.add(PaintBehavior::ExcludeSelection);
3747
3748 if (localPaintingInfo.paintBehavior & PaintBehavior::Snapshotting)
3749 localPaintBehavior.add(PaintBehavior::Snapshotting);
3750
3751 if (localPaintingInfo.paintBehavior & PaintBehavior::TileFirstPaint)
3752 localPaintBehavior.add(PaintBehavior::TileFirstPaint);
3753
3754 if (localPaintingInfo.paintBehavior & PaintBehavior::CompositedOverflowScrollContent)
3755 localPaintBehavior.add(PaintBehavior::CompositedOverflowScrollContent);
3756
3757 // Optimize clipping for the single fragment case.
3758 bool shouldClip = localPaintingInfo.clipToDirtyRect && layerFragments.size() == 1 && layerFragments[0].shouldPaintContent && !layerFragments[0].foregroundRect.isEmpty();
3759 ClipRect clippedRect;
3760 if (shouldClip) {
3761 clippedRect = layerFragments[0].foregroundRect;
3762 clipToRect(context, localPaintingInfo, localPaintBehavior, clippedRect);
3763 }
3764
3765 // We have to loop through every fragment multiple times, since we have to repaint in each specific phase in order for
3766 // interleaving of the fragments to work properly.
3767 bool selectionOnly = localPaintingInfo.paintBehavior.contains(PaintBehavior::SelectionOnly);
3768 bool selectionAndBackgroundsOnly = localPaintingInfo.paintBehavior.contains(PaintBehavior::SelectionAndBackgroundsOnly);
3769
3770 if (!selectionOnly)
3771 paintForegroundForFragmentsWithPhase(PaintPhase::ChildBlockBackgrounds, layerFragments, context, localPaintingInfo, localPaintBehavior, subtreePaintRootForRenderer);
3772
3773 if (selectionOnly || selectionAndBackgroundsOnly)
3774 paintForegroundForFragmentsWithPhase(PaintPhase::Selection, layerFragments, context, localPaintingInfo, localPaintBehavior, subtreePaintRootForRenderer);
3775 else {
3776 paintForegroundForFragmentsWithPhase(PaintPhase::Float, layerFragments, context, localPaintingInfo, localPaintBehavior, subtreePaintRootForRenderer);
3777 paintForegroundForFragmentsWithPhase(PaintPhase::Foreground, layerFragments, context, localPaintingInfo, localPaintBehavior, subtreePaintRootForRenderer);
3778 paintForegroundForFragmentsWithPhase(PaintPhase::ChildOutlines, layerFragments, context, localPaintingInfo, localPaintBehavior, subtreePaintRootForRenderer);
3779 }
3780
3781 if (shouldClip)
3782 restoreClip(context, localPaintingInfo, clippedRect);
3783}

3889
3890bool RenderLayer::hitTest(const HitTestRequest& request, const HitTestLocation& hitTestLocation, HitTestResult& result)
3891{
3892 ASSERT(isSelfPaintingLayer() || hasSelfPaintingLayerDescendant());
3893 ASSERT(!renderer().view().needsLayout());
3894
3895 ASSERT(!isRenderFragmentedFlow());
3896 LayoutRect hitTestArea = renderer().view().documentRect();
3897 if (!request.ignoreClipping()) {
3898 const auto& settings = renderer().settings();
3899 if (settings.visualViewportEnabled() && settings.clientCoordinatesRelativeToLayoutViewport()) {
3900 auto& frameView = renderer().view().frameView();
3901 LayoutRect absoluteLayoutViewportRect = frameView.layoutViewportRect();
3902 auto scaleFactor = frameView.frame().frameScaleFactor();
3903 if (scaleFactor > 1)
3904 absoluteLayoutViewportRect.scale(scaleFactor);
3905 hitTestArea.intersect(absoluteLayoutViewportRect);
3906 } else
3907 hitTestArea.intersect(renderer().view().frameView().visibleContentRect(ScrollableArea::LegacyIOSDocumentVisibleRect));
3908 }
3909
3910 RenderLayer* insideLayer = hitTestLayer(this, nullptr, request, result, hitTestArea, hitTestLocation, false);
3911 if (!insideLayer) {
3912 // We didn't hit any layer. If we are the root layer and the mouse is -- or just was -- down,
3913 // return ourselves. We do this so mouse events continue getting delivered after a drag has
3914 // exited the WebView, and so hit testing over a scrollbar hits the content document.
3915 if (!request.isChildFrameHitTest() && (request.active() || request.release()) && isRenderViewLayer()) {
3916 renderer().updateHitTestResult(result, downcast<RenderView>(renderer()).flipForWritingMode(hitTestLocation.point()));
3917 insideLayer = this;
3918 }
3919 }
3920
3921 // Now determine if the result is inside an anchor - if the urlElement isn't already set.
3922 Node* node = result.innerNode();
3923 if (node && !result.URLElement())
3924 result.setURLElement(node->enclosingLinkEventParentOrSelf());
3925
3926 // Now return whether we were inside this layer (this will always be true for the root
3927 // layer).
3928 return insideLayer;
3929}

3934 if (Element* e = r->element())
3935 return e;
3936 }
3937 return nullptr;
3938}

3940RenderLayer* RenderLayer::enclosingFragmentedFlowAncestor() const
3941{
3942 RenderLayer* curr = parent();
3943 for (; curr && !curr->isRenderFragmentedFlow(); curr = curr->parent()) {
3944 if (curr->isStackingContext() && curr->isComposited()) {
3945 // We only adjust the position of the first level of layers.
3946 return nullptr;
3947 }
3948 }
3949 return curr;
3950}

3952// Compute the z-offset of the point in the transformState.
3953// This is effectively projecting a ray normal to the plane of ancestor, finding where that
3954// ray intersects target, and computing the z delta between those two points.
3955static double computeZOffset(const HitTestingTransformState& transformState)
3956{
3957 // We got an affine transform, so no z-offset
3958 if (transformState.m_accumulatedTransform.isAffine())
3959 return 0;
3960
3961 // Flatten the point into the target plane
3962 FloatPoint targetPoint = transformState.mappedPoint();
3963
3964 // Now map the point back through the transform, which computes Z.
3965 FloatPoint3D backmappedPoint = transformState.m_accumulatedTransform.mapPoint(FloatPoint3D(targetPoint));
3966 return backmappedPoint.z();
3967}
3968
3969Ref<HitTestingTransformState> RenderLayer::createLocalTransformState(RenderLayer* rootLayer, RenderLayer* containerLayer,
3970 const LayoutRect& hitTestRect, const HitTestLocation& hitTestLocation,
3971 const HitTestingTransformState* containerTransformState,
3972 const LayoutSize& translationOffset) const
3973{
3974 RefPtr<HitTestingTransformState> transformState;
3975 LayoutSize offset;
3976 if (containerTransformState) {
3977 // If we're already computing transform state, then it's relative to the container (which we know is non-null).
3978 transformState = HitTestingTransformState::create(*containerTransformState);
3979 offset = offsetFromAncestor(containerLayer);
3980 } else {
3981 // If this is the first time we need to make transform state, then base it off of hitTestLocation,
3982 // which is relative to rootLayer.
3983 transformState = HitTestingTransformState::create(hitTestLocation.transformedPoint(), hitTestLocation.transformedRect(), FloatQuad(hitTestRect));
3984 offset = offsetFromAncestor(rootLayer);
3985 }
3986 offset += translationOffset;
3987
3988 RenderObject* containerRenderer = containerLayer ? &containerLayer->renderer() : nullptr;
3989 if (renderer().shouldUseTransformFromContainer(containerRenderer)) {
3990 TransformationMatrix containerTransform;
3991 renderer().getTransformFromContainer(containerRenderer, offset, containerTransform);
3992 transformState->applyTransform(containerTransform, HitTestingTransformState::AccumulateTransform);
3993 } else {
3994 transformState->translate(offset.width(), offset.height(), HitTestingTransformState::AccumulateTransform);
3995 }
3996
3997 return transformState.releaseNonNull();
3998}
