4000
4001static bool isHitCandidate(const RenderLayer* hitLayer, bool canDepthSort, double* zOffset, const HitTestingTransformState* transformState)
4002{
4003 if (!hitLayer)
4004 return false;
4005
4006 // The hit layer is depth-sorting with other layers, so just say that it was hit.
4007 if (canDepthSort)
4008 return true;
4009
4010 // We need to look at z-depth to decide if this layer was hit.
4011 if (zOffset) {
4012 ASSERT(transformState);
4013 // This is actually computing our z, but that's OK because the hitLayer is coplanar with us.
4014 double childZOffset = computeZOffset(*transformState);
4015 if (childZOffset > *zOffset) {
4016 *zOffset = childZOffset;
4017 return true;
4018 }
4019 return false;
4020 }
4021
4022 return true;
4023}
4024
4025// hitTestLocation and hitTestRect are relative to rootLayer.
4026// A 'flattening' layer is one preserves3D() == false.
4027// transformState.m_accumulatedTransform holds the transform from the containing flattening layer.
4028// transformState.m_lastPlanarPoint is the hitTestLocation in the plane of the containing flattening layer.
4029// transformState.m_lastPlanarQuad is the hitTestRect as a quad in the plane of the containing flattening layer.
4030//
4031// If zOffset is non-null (which indicates that the caller wants z offset information),
4032// *zOffset on return is the z offset of the hit point relative to the containing flattening layer.
4033RenderLayer* RenderLayer::hitTestLayer(RenderLayer* rootLayer, RenderLayer* containerLayer, const HitTestRequest& request, HitTestResult& result,
4034 const LayoutRect& hitTestRect, const HitTestLocation& hitTestLocation, bool appliedTransform,
4035 const HitTestingTransformState* transformState, double* zOffset)
4036{
4037 updateLayerListsIfNeeded();
4038
4039 if (!isSelfPaintingLayer() && !hasSelfPaintingLayerDescendant())
4040 return nullptr;
4041
4042 // The natural thing would be to keep HitTestingTransformState on the stack, but it's big, so we heap-allocate.
4043
4044 // Apply a transform if we have one.
4045 if (transform() && !appliedTransform) {
4046 if (enclosingPaginationLayer(IncludeCompositedPaginatedLayers))
4047 return hitTestTransformedLayerInFragments(rootLayer, containerLayer, request, result, hitTestRect, hitTestLocation, transformState, zOffset);
4048
4049 // Make sure the parent's clip rects have been calculated.
4050 if (parent()) {
4051 ClipRectsContext clipRectsContext(rootLayer, RootRelativeClipRects, IncludeOverlayScrollbarSize);
4052 ClipRect clipRect = backgroundClipRect(clipRectsContext);
4053 // Test the enclosing clip now.
4054 if (!clipRect.intersects(hitTestLocation))
4055 return nullptr;
4056 }
4057
4058 return hitTestLayerByApplyingTransform(rootLayer, containerLayer, request, result, hitTestRect, hitTestLocation, transformState, zOffset);
4059 }
4060
4061 // Ensure our lists and 3d status are up-to-date.
4062 update3DTransformedDescendantStatus();
4063
4064 RefPtr<HitTestingTransformState> localTransformState;
4065 if (appliedTransform) {
4066 // We computed the correct state in the caller (above code), so just reference it.
4067 ASSERT(transformState);
4068 localTransformState = const_cast<HitTestingTransformState*>(transformState);
4069 } else if (transformState || has3DTransformedDescendant() || preserves3D()) {
4070 // We need transform state for the first time, or to offset the container state, so create it here.
4071 localTransformState = createLocalTransformState(rootLayer, containerLayer, hitTestRect, hitTestLocation, transformState);
4072 }
4073
4074 // Check for hit test on backface if backface-visibility is 'hidden'
4075 if (localTransformState && renderer().style().backfaceVisibility() == BackfaceVisibility::Hidden) {
4076 std::optional<TransformationMatrix> invertedMatrix = localTransformState->m_accumulatedTransform.inverse();
4077 // If the z-vector of the matrix is negative, the back is facing towards the viewer.
4078 if (invertedMatrix && invertedMatrix.value().m33() < 0)
4079 return nullptr;
4080 }
4081
4082 RefPtr<HitTestingTransformState> unflattenedTransformState = localTransformState;
4083 if (localTransformState && !preserves3D()) {
4084 // Keep a copy of the pre-flattening state, for computing z-offsets for the container
4085 unflattenedTransformState = HitTestingTransformState::create(*localTransformState);
4086 // This layer is flattening, so flatten the state passed to descendants.
4087 localTransformState->flatten();
4088 }
4089
4090 // The following are used for keeping track of the z-depth of the hit point of 3d-transformed
4091 // descendants.
4092 double localZOffset = -std::numeric_limits<double>::infinity();
4093 double* zOffsetForDescendantsPtr = nullptr;
4094 double* zOffsetForContentsPtr = nullptr;
4095
4096 bool depthSortDescendants = false;
4097 if (preserves3D()) {
4098 depthSortDescendants = true;
4099 // Our layers can depth-test with our container, so share the z depth pointer with the container, if it passed one down.
4100 zOffsetForDescendantsPtr = zOffset ? zOffset : &localZOffset;
4101 zOffsetForContentsPtr = zOffset ? zOffset : &localZOffset;
4102 } else if (zOffset) {
4103 zOffsetForDescendantsPtr = nullptr;
4104 // Container needs us to give back a z offset for the hit layer.
4105 zOffsetForContentsPtr = zOffset;
4106 }
4107
4108 // This variable tracks which layer the mouse ends up being inside.
4109 RenderLayer* candidateLayer = nullptr;
4110#if ASSERT_ENABLED
4111 LayerListMutationDetector mutationChecker(*this);
4112#endif
4113
4114 auto offsetFromRoot = offsetFromAncestor(rootLayer);
4115 // FIXME: We need to correctly hit test the clip-path when we have a RenderInline too.
4116 if (auto* rendererBox = this->renderBox(); rendererBox && !rendererBox->hitTestClipPath(hitTestLocation, toLayoutPoint(offsetFromRoot - toLayoutSize(renderBoxLocation()))))
4117 return nullptr;
4118
4119 // Begin by walking our list of positive layers from highest z-index down to the lowest z-index.
4120 auto* hitLayer = hitTestList(positiveZOrderLayers(), rootLayer, request, result, hitTestRect, hitTestLocation,
4121 localTransformState.get(), zOffsetForDescendantsPtr, zOffset, unflattenedTransformState.get(), depthSortDescendants);
4122 if (hitLayer) {
4123 if (!depthSortDescendants)
4124 return hitLayer;
4125 candidateLayer = hitLayer;
4126 }
4127
4128 // Now check our overflow objects.
4129 hitLayer = hitTestList(normalFlowLayers(), rootLayer, request, result, hitTestRect, hitTestLocation,
4130 localTransformState.get(), zOffsetForDescendantsPtr, zOffset, unflattenedTransformState.get(), depthSortDescendants);
4131 if (hitLayer) {
4132 if (!depthSortDescendants)
4133 return hitLayer;
4134 candidateLayer = hitLayer;
4135 }
4136
4137 // Collect the fragments. This will compute the clip rectangles for each layer fragment.
4138 LayerFragments layerFragments;
4139 collectFragments(layerFragments, rootLayer, hitTestRect, IncludeCompositedPaginatedLayers, RootRelativeClipRects, IncludeOverlayScrollbarSize, RespectOverflowClip, offsetFromRoot);
4140
4141 LayoutPoint localPoint;
4142 if (canResize() && m_scrollableArea && m_scrollableArea->hitTestResizerInFragments(layerFragments, hitTestLocation, localPoint)) {
4143 renderer().updateHitTestResult(result, localPoint);
4144 return this;
4145 }
4146
4147 // Next we want to see if the mouse pos is inside the child RenderObjects of the layer. Check
4148 // every fragment in reverse order.
4149 if (isSelfPaintingLayer()) {
4150 // Hit test with a temporary HitTestResult, because we only want to commit to 'result' if we know we're frontmost.
4151 HitTestResult tempResult(result.hitTestLocation());
4152 bool insideFragmentForegroundRect = false;
4153 if (hitTestContentsForFragments(layerFragments, request, tempResult, hitTestLocation, HitTestDescendants, insideFragmentForegroundRect)
4154 && isHitCandidate(this, false, zOffsetForContentsPtr, unflattenedTransformState.get())) {
4155 if (request.resultIsElementList())
4156 result.append(tempResult, request);
4157 else
4158 result = tempResult;
4159 if (!depthSortDescendants)
4160 return this;
4161 // Foreground can depth-sort with descendant layers, so keep this as a candidate.
4162 candidateLayer = this;
4163 } else if (insideFragmentForegroundRect && request.resultIsElementList())
4164 result.append(tempResult, request);
4165 }
4166
4167 // Now check our negative z-index children.
4168 hitLayer = hitTestList(negativeZOrderLayers(), rootLayer, request, result, hitTestRect, hitTestLocation,
4169 localTransformState.get(), zOffsetForDescendantsPtr, zOffset, unflattenedTransformState.get(), depthSortDescendants);
4170 if (hitLayer) {
4171 if (!depthSortDescendants)
4172 return hitLayer;
4173 candidateLayer = hitLayer;
4174 }
4175
4176 // If we found a layer, return. Child layers, and foreground always render in front of background.
4177 if (candidateLayer)
4178 return candidateLayer;
4179
4180 if (isSelfPaintingLayer()) {
4181 HitTestResult tempResult(result.hitTestLocation());
4182 bool insideFragmentBackgroundRect = false;
4183 if (hitTestContentsForFragments(layerFragments, request, tempResult, hitTestLocation, HitTestSelf, insideFragmentBackgroundRect)
4184 && isHitCandidate(this, false, zOffsetForContentsPtr, unflattenedTransformState.get())) {
4185 if (request.resultIsElementList())
4186 result.append(tempResult, request);
4187 else
4188 result = tempResult;
4189 return this;
4190 }
4191 if (insideFragmentBackgroundRect && request.resultIsElementList())
4192 result.append(tempResult, request);
4193 }
4194
4195 return nullptr;
4196}
4197
4198bool RenderLayer::hitTestContentsForFragments(const LayerFragments& layerFragments, const HitTestRequest& request, HitTestResult& result,
4199 const HitTestLocation& hitTestLocation, HitTestFilter hitTestFilter, bool& insideClipRect) const
4200{
4201 if (layerFragments.isEmpty())
4202 return false;
4203
4204 for (int i = layerFragments.size() - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
4205 const LayerFragment& fragment = layerFragments.at(i);
4206 if ((hitTestFilter == HitTestSelf && !fragment.backgroundRect.intersects(hitTestLocation))
4207 || (hitTestFilter == HitTestDescendants && !fragment.foregroundRect.intersects(hitTestLocation)))
4208 continue;
4209 insideClipRect = true;
4210 if (hitTestContents(request, result, fragment.layerBounds, hitTestLocation, hitTestFilter))
4211 return true;
4212 }
4213
4214 return false;
4215}
4216
4217RenderLayer* RenderLayer::hitTestTransformedLayerInFragments(RenderLayer* rootLayer, RenderLayer* containerLayer, const HitTestRequest& request, HitTestResult& result,
4218 const LayoutRect& hitTestRect, const HitTestLocation& hitTestLocation, const HitTestingTransformState* transformState, double* zOffset)
4219{
4220 LayerFragments enclosingPaginationFragments;
4221 LayoutSize offsetOfPaginationLayerFromRoot;
4222 RenderLayer* paginatedLayer = enclosingPaginationLayer(IncludeCompositedPaginatedLayers);
4223 LayoutRect transformedExtent = transparencyClipBox(*this, paginatedLayer, HitTestingTransparencyClipBox, RootOfTransparencyClipBox);
4224 paginatedLayer->collectFragments(enclosingPaginationFragments, rootLayer, hitTestRect, IncludeCompositedPaginatedLayers,
4225 RootRelativeClipRects, IncludeOverlayScrollbarSize, RespectOverflowClip, offsetOfPaginationLayerFromRoot, &transformedExtent);
4226
4227 for (int i = enclosingPaginationFragments.size() - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
4228 const LayerFragment& fragment = enclosingPaginationFragments.at(i);
4229
4230 // Apply the page/column clip for this fragment, as well as any clips established by layers in between us and
4231 // the enclosing pagination layer.
4232 LayoutRect clipRect = fragment.backgroundRect.rect();
4233
4234 // Now compute the clips within a given fragment
4235 if (parent() != paginatedLayer) {
4236 offsetOfPaginationLayerFromRoot = toLayoutSize(paginatedLayer->convertToLayerCoords(rootLayer, toLayoutPoint(offsetOfPaginationLayerFromRoot)));
4237
4238 ClipRectsContext clipRectsContext(paginatedLayer, RootRelativeClipRects, IncludeOverlayScrollbarSize);
4239 LayoutRect parentClipRect = backgroundClipRect(clipRectsContext).rect();
4240 parentClipRect.move(fragment.paginationOffset + offsetOfPaginationLayerFromRoot);
4241 clipRect.intersect(parentClipRect);
4242 }
4243
4244 if (!hitTestLocation.intersects(clipRect))
4245 continue;
4246
4247 RenderLayer* hitLayer = hitTestLayerByApplyingTransform(rootLayer, containerLayer, request, result, hitTestRect, hitTestLocation,
4248 transformState, zOffset, fragment.paginationOffset);
4249 if (hitLayer)
4250 return hitLayer;
4251 }
4252
4253 return nullptr;
4254}
4255
4256RenderLayer* RenderLayer::hitTestLayerByApplyingTransform(RenderLayer* rootLayer, RenderLayer* containerLayer, const HitTestRequest& request, HitTestResult& result,
4257 const LayoutRect& hitTestRect, const HitTestLocation& hitTestLocation, const HitTestingTransformState* transformState, double* zOffset,
4258 const LayoutSize& translationOffset)
4259{
4260 // Create a transform state to accumulate this transform.
4261 Ref<HitTestingTransformState> newTransformState = createLocalTransformState(rootLayer, containerLayer, hitTestRect, hitTestLocation, transformState, translationOffset);
4262
4263 // If the transform can't be inverted, then don't hit test this layer at all.
4264 if (!newTransformState->m_accumulatedTransform.isInvertible())
4265 return nullptr;
4266
4267 // Compute the point and the hit test rect in the coords of this layer by using the values
4268 // from the transformState, which store the point and quad in the coords of the last flattened
4269 // layer, and the accumulated transform which lets up map through preserve-3d layers.
4270 //
4271 // We can't just map hitTestLocation and hitTestRect because they may have been flattened (losing z)
4272 // by our container.
4273 FloatPoint localPoint = newTransformState->mappedPoint();
4274 FloatQuad localPointQuad = newTransformState->mappedQuad();
4275 LayoutRect localHitTestRect = newTransformState->boundsOfMappedArea();
4276 HitTestLocation newHitTestLocation;
4277 if (hitTestLocation.isRectBasedTest())
4278 newHitTestLocation = HitTestLocation(localPoint, localPointQuad);
4279 else
4280 newHitTestLocation = HitTestLocation(flooredLayoutPoint(localPoint));
4281
4282 // Now do a hit test with the root layer shifted to be us.
4283 return hitTestLayer(this, containerLayer, request, result, localHitTestRect, newHitTestLocation, true, newTransformState.ptr(), zOffset);
4284}
4285
4286bool RenderLayer::hitTestContents(const HitTestRequest& request, HitTestResult& result, const LayoutRect& layerBounds, const HitTestLocation& hitTestLocation, HitTestFilter hitTestFilter) const
4287{
4288 ASSERT(isSelfPaintingLayer() || hasSelfPaintingLayerDescendant());
4289
4290 if (!renderer().hitTest(request, result, hitTestLocation, toLayoutPoint(layerBounds.location() - renderBoxLocation()), hitTestFilter)) {
4291 // It's wrong to set innerNode, but then claim that you didn't hit anything, unless it is
4292 // a rect-based test.
4293 ASSERT(!result.innerNode() || (request.resultIsElementList() && result.listBasedTestResult().size()));
4294 return false;
4295 }
4296
4297 // For positioned generated content, we might still not have a
4298 // node by the time we get to the layer level, since none of
4299 // the content in the layer has an element. So just walk up
4300 // the tree.
4301 if (!result.innerNode() || !result.innerNonSharedNode()) {
4302 Element* e = enclosingElement();
4303 if (!result.innerNode())
4304 result.setInnerNode(e);
4305 if (!result.innerNonSharedNode())
4306 result.setInnerNonSharedNode(e);
4307 }
4308
4309 return true;
4310}
4311
4312RenderLayer* RenderLayer::hitTestList(LayerList layerIterator, RenderLayer* rootLayer,
4313 const HitTestRequest& request, HitTestResult& result,
4314 const LayoutRect& hitTestRect, const HitTestLocation& hitTestLocation,
4315 const HitTestingTransformState* transformState,
4316 double* zOffsetForDescendants, double* zOffset,
4317 const HitTestingTransformState* unflattenedTransformState,
4318 bool depthSortDescendants)
4319{
4320 if (layerIterator.begin() == layerIterator.end())
4321 return nullptr;
4322
4323 if (!hasSelfPaintingLayerDescendant())
4324 return nullptr;
4325
4326 RenderLayer* resultLayer = nullptr;
4327
4328 for (auto iter = layerIterator.rbegin(); iter != layerIterator.rend(); ++iter) {
4329 auto* childLayer = *iter;
4330
4331 HitTestResult tempResult(result.hitTestLocation());
4332 auto* hitLayer = childLayer->hitTestLayer(rootLayer, this, request, tempResult, hitTestRect, hitTestLocation, false, transformState, zOffsetForDescendants);
4333
4334 // If it is a list-based test, we can safely append the temporary result since it might had hit
4335 // nodes but not necessarily had hitLayer set.
4336 ASSERT(!result.isRectBasedTest() || request.resultIsElementList());
4337 if (request.resultIsElementList())
4338 result.append(tempResult, request);
4339
4340 if (isHitCandidate(hitLayer, depthSortDescendants, zOffset, unflattenedTransformState)) {
4341 resultLayer = hitLayer;
4342 if (!request.resultIsElementList())
4343 result = tempResult;
4344 if (!depthSortDescendants)
4345 break;
4346 }
4347 }
4348
4349 return resultLayer;
4350}
4351
4352Ref<ClipRects> RenderLayer::updateClipRects(const ClipRectsContext& clipRectsContext)
4353{
4354 ClipRectsType clipRectsType = clipRectsContext.clipRectsType;
4355 ASSERT(clipRectsType < NumCachedClipRectsTypes);
4356 if (m_clipRectsCache) {
4357 if (auto* clipRects = m_clipRectsCache->getClipRects(clipRectsType, clipRectsContext.respectOverflowClip)) {
4358 ASSERT(clipRectsContext.rootLayer == m_clipRectsCache->m_clipRectsRoot[clipRectsType]);
4359 ASSERT(m_clipRectsCache->m_scrollbarRelevancy[clipRectsType] == clipRectsContext.overlayScrollbarSizeRelevancy);
4360
4361#ifdef CHECK_CACHED_CLIP_RECTS
4362 // This code is useful to check cached clip rects, but is too expensive to leave enabled in debug builds by default.
4363 ClipRectsContext tempContext(clipRectsContext);
4364 tempContext.clipRectsType = TemporaryClipRects;
4365 Ref<ClipRects> tempClipRects = ClipRects::create();
4366 calculateClipRects(tempContext, tempClipRects);
4367 ASSERT(tempClipRects.get() == *clipRects);
4368#endif
4369 return *clipRects; // We have the correct cached value.
4370 }
4371 }
4372
4373 if (!m_clipRectsCache)
4374 m_clipRectsCache = makeUnique<ClipRectsCache>();
4375#if ASSERT_ENABLED
4376 m_clipRectsCache->m_clipRectsRoot[clipRectsType] = clipRectsContext.rootLayer;
4377 m_clipRectsCache->m_scrollbarRelevancy[clipRectsType] = clipRectsContext.overlayScrollbarSizeRelevancy;
4378#endif
4379
4380 RefPtr<ClipRects> parentClipRects;
4381 // For transformed layers, the root layer was shifted to be us, so there is no need to
4382 // examine the parent. We want to cache clip rects with us as the root.
4383 if (clipRectsContext.rootLayer != this && parent())
4384 parentClipRects = this->parentClipRects(clipRectsContext);
4385
4386 auto clipRects = ClipRects::create();
4387 calculateClipRects(clipRectsContext, clipRects);
4388
4389 if (parentClipRects && *parentClipRects == clipRects) {
4390 m_clipRectsCache->setClipRects(clipRectsType, clipRectsContext.respectOverflowClip, parentClipRects.copyRef());
4391 return parentClipRects.releaseNonNull();
4392 }
4393 m_clipRectsCache->setClipRects(clipRectsType, clipRectsContext.respectOverflowClip, clipRects.copyRef());
4394 return clipRects;
4395}
4396
4397ClipRects* RenderLayer::clipRects(const ClipRectsContext& context) const
4398{
4399 ASSERT(context.clipRectsType < NumCachedClipRectsTypes);
4400 if (!m_clipRectsCache)
4401 return nullptr;
4402 return m_clipRectsCache->getClipRects(context.clipRectsType, context.respectOverflowClip);
4403}
4404
4405bool RenderLayer::clipCrossesPaintingBoundary() const
4406{
4407 return parent()->enclosingPaginationLayer(IncludeCompositedPaginatedLayers) != enclosingPaginationLayer(IncludeCompositedPaginatedLayers)
4408 || parent()->enclosingCompositingLayerForRepaint() != enclosingCompositingLayerForRepaint();
4409}
4410
4411void RenderLayer::calculateClipRects(const ClipRectsContext& clipRectsContext, ClipRects& clipRects) const
4412{
4413 if (!parent()) {
4414 // The root layer's clip rect is always infinite.
4415 clipRects.reset();
4416 return;
4417 }
4418
4419 ClipRectsType clipRectsType = clipRectsContext.clipRectsType;
4420 bool useCached = clipRectsType != TemporaryClipRects;
4421
4422 // For transformed layers, the root layer was shifted to be us, so there is no need to
4423 // examine the parent. We want to cache clip rects with us as the root.
4424 RenderLayer* parentLayer = clipRectsContext.rootLayer != this ? parent() : nullptr;
4425
4426 // Ensure that our parent's clip has been calculated so that we can examine the values.
4427 if (parentLayer) {
4428 if (useCached && parentLayer->clipRects(clipRectsContext))
4429 clipRects = *parentLayer->clipRects(clipRectsContext);
4430 else {
4431 ClipRectsContext parentContext(clipRectsContext);
4432 parentContext.overlayScrollbarSizeRelevancy = IgnoreOverlayScrollbarSize; // FIXME: why?
4433
4434 if ((parentContext.clipRectsType != TemporaryClipRects && parentContext.clipRectsType != AbsoluteClipRects) && clipCrossesPaintingBoundary())
4435 parentContext.clipRectsType = TemporaryClipRects;
4436
4437 parentLayer->calculateClipRects(parentContext, clipRects);
4438 }
4439 } else
4440 clipRects.reset();
4441
4442 // A fixed object is essentially the root of its containing block hierarchy, so when
4443 // we encounter such an object, we reset our clip rects to the fixedClipRect.
4444 if (renderer().isFixedPositioned()) {
4445 clipRects.setPosClipRect(clipRects.fixedClipRect());
4446 clipRects.setOverflowClipRect(clipRects.fixedClipRect());
4447 clipRects.setFixed(true);
4448 } else if (renderer().isInFlowPositioned())
4449 clipRects.setPosClipRect(clipRects.overflowClipRect());
4450 else if (renderer().isAbsolutelyPositioned())
4451 clipRects.setOverflowClipRect(clipRects.posClipRect());
4452
4453 // Update the clip rects that will be passed to child layers.
4454#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
4455 if (renderer().hasClipOrOverflowClip() && (clipRectsContext.respectOverflowClip == RespectOverflowClip || this != clipRectsContext.rootLayer)) {
4456#else
4457 if ((renderer().hasOverflowClip() && (clipRectsContext.respectOverflowClip == RespectOverflowClip || this != clipRectsContext.rootLayer)) || renderer().hasClip()) {
4458#endif
4459 // This layer establishes a clip of some kind.
4460 LayoutPoint offset;
4461 if (!m_hasTransformedAncestor && canUseOffsetFromAncestor())
4462 offset = toLayoutPoint(offsetFromAncestor(clipRectsContext.rootLayer, AdjustForColumns));
4463 else
4464 offset = LayoutPoint(renderer().localToContainerPoint(FloatPoint(), &clipRectsContext.rootLayer->renderer()));
4465
4466 if (clipRects.fixed() && &clipRectsContext.rootLayer->renderer() == &renderer().view())
4467 offset -= toLayoutSize(renderer().view().frameView().scrollPositionForFixedPosition());
4468
4469 if (renderer().hasOverflowClip()) {
4470 ClipRect newOverflowClip = downcast<RenderBox>(renderer()).overflowClipRectForChildLayers(offset, nullptr, clipRectsContext.overlayScrollbarSizeRelevancy);
4471 newOverflowClip.setAffectedByRadius(renderer().style().hasBorderRadius());
4472 clipRects.setOverflowClipRect(intersection(newOverflowClip, clipRects.overflowClipRect()));
4473 if (renderer().isPositioned())
4474 clipRects.setPosClipRect(intersection(newOverflowClip, clipRects.posClipRect()));
4475 }
4476 if (renderer().hasClip()) {
4477 LayoutRect newPosClip = downcast<RenderBox>(renderer()).clipRect(offset, nullptr);
4478 clipRects.setPosClipRect(intersection(newPosClip, clipRects.posClipRect()));
4479 clipRects.setOverflowClipRect(intersection(newPosClip, clipRects.overflowClipRect()));
4480 clipRects.setFixedClipRect(intersection(newPosClip, clipRects.fixedClipRect()));
4481 }
4482 } else if (renderer().hasOverflowClip() && transform() && renderer().style().hasBorderRadius())
4483 clipRects.setOverflowClipRectAffectedByRadius();
4484
4485 LOG_WITH_STREAM(ClipRects, stream << "RenderLayer " << this << " calculateClipRects " << clipRectsContext << " computed " << clipRects);
4486}
4487
4488Ref<ClipRects> RenderLayer::parentClipRects(const ClipRectsContext& clipRectsContext) const
4489{
4490 ASSERT(parent());
4491
4492 auto temporaryParentClipRects = [&](const ClipRectsContext& clipContext) {
4493 auto parentClipRects = ClipRects::create();
4494 parent()->calculateClipRects(clipContext, parentClipRects);
4495 return parentClipRects;
4496 };
4497
4498 if (clipRectsContext.clipRectsType == TemporaryClipRects)
4499 return temporaryParentClipRects(clipRectsContext);
4500
4501 if (clipRectsContext.clipRectsType != AbsoluteClipRects && clipCrossesPaintingBoundary()) {
4502 ClipRectsContext tempClipRectsContext(clipRectsContext);
4503 tempClipRectsContext.clipRectsType = TemporaryClipRects;
4504 return temporaryParentClipRects(tempClipRectsContext);
4505 }
4506
4507 return parent()->updateClipRects(clipRectsContext);
4508}
4509
4510static inline ClipRect backgroundClipRectForPosition(const ClipRects& parentRects, PositionType position)
4511{
4512 if (position == PositionType::Fixed)
4513 return parentRects.fixedClipRect();
4514
4515 if (position == PositionType::Absolute)
4516 return parentRects.posClipRect();
4517
4518 return parentRects.overflowClipRect();
4519}
4520
4521ClipRect RenderLayer::backgroundClipRect(const ClipRectsContext& clipRectsContext) const
4522{
4523 ASSERT(parent());
4524 auto parentRects = parentClipRects(clipRectsContext);
4525 ClipRect backgroundClipRect = backgroundClipRectForPosition(parentRects, renderer().style().position());
4526 RenderView& view = renderer().view();
4527 // Note: infinite clipRects should not be scrolled here, otherwise they will accidentally no longer be considered infinite.
4528 if (parentRects->fixed() && &clipRectsContext.rootLayer->renderer() == &view && !backgroundClipRect.isInfinite())
4529 backgroundClipRect.moveBy(view.frameView().scrollPositionForFixedPosition());
4530
4531 LOG_WITH_STREAM(ClipRects, stream << "RenderLayer " << this << " backgroundClipRect with context " << clipRectsContext << " returning " << backgroundClipRect);
4532 return backgroundClipRect;
4533}
4534
4535void RenderLayer::calculateRects(const ClipRectsContext& clipRectsContext, const LayoutRect& paintDirtyRect, LayoutRect& layerBounds,
4536 ClipRect& backgroundRect, ClipRect& foregroundRect, const LayoutSize& offsetFromRoot) const
4537{
4538 if (clipRectsContext.rootLayer != this && parent()) {
4539 backgroundRect = backgroundClipRect(clipRectsContext);
4540 backgroundRect.intersect(paintDirtyRect);
4541 } else
4542 backgroundRect = paintDirtyRect;
4543
4544 LayoutSize offsetFromRootLocal = offsetFromRoot;
4545
4546 layerBounds = LayoutRect(toLayoutPoint(offsetFromRootLocal), size());
4547
4548 foregroundRect = backgroundRect;
4549
4550 // Update the clip rects that will be passed to child layers.
4551 if (renderer().hasClipOrOverflowClip()) {
4552 // This layer establishes a clip of some kind.
4553 if (renderer().hasOverflowClip()) {
4554 if (this != clipRectsContext.rootLayer || clipRectsContext.respectOverflowClip == RespectOverflowClip) {
4555 foregroundRect.intersect(downcast<RenderBox>(renderer()).overflowClipRect(toLayoutPoint(offsetFromRootLocal), nullptr, clipRectsContext.overlayScrollbarSizeRelevancy));
4556 foregroundRect.setAffectedByRadius(true);
4557 } else if (transform() && renderer().style().hasBorderRadius())
4558 foregroundRect.setAffectedByRadius(true);
4559 }
4560
4561 if (renderer().hasClip()) {
4562 // Clip applies to *us* as well, so update the damageRect.
4563 LayoutRect newPosClip = downcast<RenderBox>(renderer()).clipRect(toLayoutPoint(offsetFromRootLocal), nullptr);
4564 backgroundRect.intersect(newPosClip);
4565 foregroundRect.intersect(newPosClip);
4566 }
4567
4568 // If we establish a clip at all, then make sure our background rect is intersected with our layer's bounds including our visual overflow,
4569 // since any visual overflow like box-shadow or border-outset is not clipped by overflow:auto/hidden.
4570 if (renderBox()->hasVisualOverflow()) {
4571 // FIXME: Does not do the right thing with CSS regions yet, since we don't yet factor in the
4572 // individual region boxes as overflow.
4573 LayoutRect layerBoundsWithVisualOverflow = renderBox()->visualOverflowRect();
4574 renderBox()->flipForWritingMode(layerBoundsWithVisualOverflow); // Layers are in physical coordinates, so the overflow has to be flipped.
4575 layerBoundsWithVisualOverflow.move(offsetFromRootLocal);
4576 if (this != clipRectsContext.rootLayer || clipRectsContext.respectOverflowClip == RespectOverflowClip)
4577 backgroundRect.intersect(layerBoundsWithVisualOverflow);
4578 } else {
4579 // Shift the bounds to be for our region only.
4580 LayoutRect bounds = renderBox()->borderBoxRectInFragment(nullptr);
4581
4582 bounds.move(offsetFromRootLocal);
4583 if (this != clipRectsContext.rootLayer || clipRectsContext.respectOverflowClip == RespectOverflowClip)
4584 backgroundRect.intersect(bounds);
4585 }
4586 }
4587}
4588
4589LayoutRect RenderLayer::childrenClipRect() const
4590{
4591 // FIXME: border-radius not accounted for.
4592 // FIXME: Regions not accounted for.
4593 RenderLayer* clippingRootLayer = clippingRootForPainting();
4594 LayoutRect layerBounds;
4595 ClipRect backgroundRect;
4596 ClipRect foregroundRect;
4597 ClipRectsContext clipRectsContext(clippingRootLayer, TemporaryClipRects);
4598 // Need to use temporary clip rects, because the value of 'dontClipToOverflow' may be different from the painting path (<rdar://problem/11844909>).
4599 calculateRects(clipRectsContext, LayoutRect::infiniteRect(), layerBounds, backgroundRect, foregroundRect, offsetFromAncestor(clipRectsContext.rootLayer));
4600 if (foregroundRect.rect().isInfinite())
4601 return renderer().view().unscaledDocumentRect();
4602
4603 auto absoluteClippingRect = clippingRootLayer->renderer().localToAbsoluteQuad(FloatQuad(foregroundRect.rect())).enclosingBoundingBox();
4604 return intersection(absoluteClippingRect, renderer().view().unscaledDocumentRect());
4605}
4606
4607LayoutRect RenderLayer::clipRectRelativeToAncestor(RenderLayer* ancestor, LayoutSize offsetFromAncestor, const LayoutRect& constrainingRect) const
4608{
4609 LayoutRect layerBounds;
4610 ClipRect backgroundRect;
4611 ClipRect foregroundRect;
4612 auto clipRectType = !m_enclosingPaginationLayer || m_enclosingPaginationLayer == ancestor ? PaintingClipRects : TemporaryClipRects;
4613 ClipRectsContext clipRectsContext(ancestor, clipRectType);
4614 calculateRects(clipRectsContext, constrainingRect, layerBounds, backgroundRect, foregroundRect, offsetFromAncestor);
4615 return backgroundRect.rect();
4616}
4617
4618LayoutRect RenderLayer::selfClipRect() const
4619{
4620 // FIXME: border-radius not accounted for.
4621 // FIXME: Regions not accounted for.
4622 RenderLayer* clippingRootLayer = clippingRootForPainting();
4623 LayoutRect clipRect = clipRectRelativeToAncestor(clippingRootLayer, offsetFromAncestor(clippingRootLayer), renderer().view().documentRect());
4624 return clippingRootLayer->renderer().localToAbsoluteQuad(FloatQuad(clipRect)).enclosingBoundingBox();
4625}
4626
4627LayoutRect RenderLayer::localClipRect(bool& clipExceedsBounds) const
4628{
4629 clipExceedsBounds = false;
4630 // FIXME: border-radius not accounted for.
4631 // FIXME: Regions not accounted for.
4632 RenderLayer* clippingRootLayer = clippingRootForPainting();
4633 LayoutSize offsetFromRoot = offsetFromAncestor(clippingRootLayer);
4634 LayoutRect clipRect = clipRectRelativeToAncestor(clippingRootLayer, offsetFromRoot, LayoutRect::infiniteRect());
4635 if (clipRect.isInfinite())
4636 return clipRect;
4637
4638 if (renderer().hasClip()) {
4639 // CSS clip may be larger than our border box.
4640 LayoutRect cssClipRect = downcast<RenderBox>(renderer()).clipRect({ }, nullptr);
4641 clipExceedsBounds = !cssClipRect.isEmpty() && (clipRect.width() < cssClipRect.width() || clipRect.height() < cssClipRect.height());
4642 }
4643
4644 clipRect.move(-offsetFromRoot);
4645 return clipRect;
4646}

4678
4679bool RenderLayer::intersectsDamageRect(const LayoutRect& layerBounds, const LayoutRect& damageRect, const RenderLayer* rootLayer, const LayoutSize& offsetFromRoot, const std::optional<LayoutRect>& cachedBoundingBox) const
4680{
4681 // Always examine the canvas and the root.
4682 // FIXME: Could eliminate the isDocumentElementRenderer() check if we fix background painting so that the RenderView
4683 // paints the root's background.
4684 if (isRenderViewLayer() || renderer().isDocumentElementRenderer())
4685 return true;
4686
4687 if (damageRect.isInfinite())
4688 return true;
4689
4690 if (damageRect.isEmpty())
4691 return false;
4692
4693 // If we aren't an inline flow, and our layer bounds do intersect the damage rect, then we can return true.
4694 if (!renderer().isRenderInline() && layerBounds.intersects(damageRect))
4695 return true;
4696
4697 // Otherwise we need to compute the bounding box of this single layer and see if it intersects
4698 // the damage rect. It's possible the fragment computed the bounding box already, in which case we
4699 // can use the cached value.
4700 if (cachedBoundingBox)
4701 return cachedBoundingBox->intersects(damageRect);
4702
4703 return boundingBox(rootLayer, offsetFromRoot).intersects(damageRect);
4704}
4705
4706LayoutRect RenderLayer::localBoundingBox(OptionSet<CalculateLayerBoundsFlag> flags) const
4707{
4708 // There are three special cases we need to consider.
4709 // (1) Inline Flows. For inline flows we will create a bounding box that fully encompasses all of the lines occupied by the
4710 // inline. In other words, if some <span> wraps to three lines, we'll create a bounding box that fully encloses the
4711 // line boxes of all three lines (including overflow on those lines).
4712 // (2) Left/Top Overflow. The width/height of layers already includes right/bottom overflow. However, in the case of left/top
4713 // overflow, we have to create a bounding box that will extend to include this overflow.
4714 // (3) Floats. When a layer has overhanging floats that it paints, we need to make sure to include these overhanging floats
4715 // as part of our bounding box. We do this because we are the responsible layer for both hit testing and painting those
4716 // floats.
4717 LayoutRect result;
4718 if (renderer().isInline() && is<RenderInline>(renderer()))
4719 result = downcast<RenderInline>(renderer()).linesVisualOverflowBoundingBox();
4720 else if (is<RenderTableRow>(renderer())) {
4721 auto& tableRow = downcast<RenderTableRow>(renderer());
4722 // Our bounding box is just the union of all of our cells' border/overflow rects.
4723 for (RenderTableCell* cell = tableRow.firstCell(); cell; cell = cell->nextCell()) {
4724 LayoutRect bbox = cell->borderBoxRect();
4725 result.unite(bbox);
4726 LayoutRect overflowRect = tableRow.visualOverflowRect();
4727 if (bbox != overflowRect)
4728 result.unite(overflowRect);
4729 }
4730 } else {
4731 RenderBox* box = renderBox();
4732 ASSERT(box);
4733 if (!(flags & DontConstrainForMask) && box->hasMask()) {
4734 result = box->maskClipRect(LayoutPoint());
4735 box->flipForWritingMode(result); // The mask clip rect is in physical coordinates, so we have to flip, since localBoundingBox is not.
4736 } else
4737 result = box->visualOverflowRect();
4738 }
4739 return result;
4740}
4741
4742LayoutRect RenderLayer::boundingBox(const RenderLayer* ancestorLayer, const LayoutSize& offsetFromRoot, OptionSet<CalculateLayerBoundsFlag> flags) const
4743{
4744 LayoutRect result = localBoundingBox(flags);
4745 if (renderer().view().frameView().hasFlippedBlockRenderers()) {
4746 if (renderer().isBox())
4747 renderBox()->flipForWritingMode(result);
4748 else
4749 renderer().containingBlock()->flipForWritingMode(result);
4750 }
4751
4752 PaginationInclusionMode inclusionMode = ExcludeCompositedPaginatedLayers;
4753 if (flags & UseFragmentBoxesIncludingCompositing)
4754 inclusionMode = IncludeCompositedPaginatedLayers;
4755
4756 const RenderLayer* paginationLayer = nullptr;
4757 if (flags.containsAny({ UseFragmentBoxesExcludingCompositing, UseFragmentBoxesIncludingCompositing }))
4758 paginationLayer = enclosingPaginationLayerInSubtree(ancestorLayer, inclusionMode);
4759
4760 const RenderLayer* childLayer = this;
4761 bool isPaginated = paginationLayer;
4762 while (paginationLayer) {
4763 // Split our box up into the actual fragment boxes that render in the columns/pages and unite those together to
4764 // get our true bounding box.
4765 result.move(childLayer->offsetFromAncestor(paginationLayer));
4766
4767 auto& enclosingFragmentedFlow = downcast<RenderFragmentedFlow>(paginationLayer->renderer());
4768 result = enclosingFragmentedFlow.fragmentsBoundingBox(result);
4769
4770 childLayer = paginationLayer;
4771 paginationLayer = paginationLayer->parent()->enclosingPaginationLayerInSubtree(ancestorLayer, inclusionMode);
4772 }
4773
4774 if (isPaginated) {
4775 result.move(childLayer->offsetFromAncestor(ancestorLayer));
4776 return result;
4777 }
4778
4779 result.move(offsetFromRoot);
4780 return result;
4781}

4783bool RenderLayer::getOverlapBoundsIncludingChildrenAccountingForTransformAnimations(LayoutRect& bounds, OptionSet<CalculateLayerBoundsFlag> additionalFlags) const
4784{
4785 // The animation will override the display transform, so don't include it.
4786 auto boundsFlags = additionalFlags | (defaultCalculateLayerBoundsFlags() - IncludeSelfTransform);
4787
4788 bounds = calculateLayerBounds(this, LayoutSize(), boundsFlags);
4789
4790 LayoutRect animatedBounds = bounds;
4791 if (auto* timeline = renderer().documentTimeline()) {
4792 if (timeline->computeExtentOfAnimation(renderer(), animatedBounds)) {
4793 bounds = animatedBounds;

4795 }
4796 }
4797
4798 return false;

4820
4821LayoutRect RenderLayer::calculateLayerBounds(const RenderLayer* ancestorLayer, const LayoutSize& offsetFromRoot, OptionSet<CalculateLayerBoundsFlag> flags) const
4822{
4823 if (!isSelfPaintingLayer())
4824 return LayoutRect();
4825
4826 // FIXME: This could be improved to do a check like hasVisibleNonCompositingDescendantLayers() (bug 92580).
4827 if ((flags & ExcludeHiddenDescendants) && this != ancestorLayer && !hasVisibleContent() && !hasVisibleDescendant())
4828 return LayoutRect();
4829
4830 if (isRenderViewLayer()) {
4831 // The root layer is always just the size of the document.
4832 return renderer().view().unscaledDocumentRect();
4833 }
4834
4835 LayoutRect boundingBoxRect = localBoundingBox(flags);
4836 if (renderer().view().frameView().hasFlippedBlockRenderers()) {
4837 if (is<RenderBox>(renderer()))
4838 downcast<RenderBox>(renderer()).flipForWritingMode(boundingBoxRect);
4839 else
4840 renderer().containingBlock()->flipForWritingMode(boundingBoxRect);
4841 }
4842
4843 if (renderer().isDocumentElementRenderer()) {
4844 // If the root layer becomes composited (e.g. because some descendant with negative z-index is composited),
4845 // then it has to be big enough to cover the viewport in order to display the background. This is akin
4846 // to the code in RenderBox::paintRootBoxFillLayers().
4847 const FrameView& frameView = renderer().view().frameView();
4848 boundingBoxRect.setWidth(std::max(boundingBoxRect.width(), frameView.contentsWidth() - boundingBoxRect.x()));
4849 boundingBoxRect.setHeight(std::max(boundingBoxRect.height(), frameView.contentsHeight() - boundingBoxRect.y()));
4850 }
4851
4852 LayoutRect unionBounds = boundingBoxRect;
4853
4854 if (flags & UseLocalClipRectIfPossible) {
4855 bool clipExceedsBounds = false;
4856 LayoutRect localClipRect = this->localClipRect(clipExceedsBounds);
4857 if (!localClipRect.isInfinite() && !clipExceedsBounds) {
4858 if ((flags & IncludeSelfTransform) && paintsWithTransform(PaintBehavior::Normal))
4859 localClipRect = transform()->mapRect(localClipRect);
4860
4861 localClipRect.move(offsetFromAncestor(ancestorLayer));
4862 return localClipRect;
4863 }
4864 }
4865
4866 // FIXME: should probably just pass 'flags' down to descendants.
4867 auto descendantFlags = defaultCalculateLayerBoundsFlags() | (flags & ExcludeHiddenDescendants) | (flags & IncludeCompositedDescendants);
4868
4869 const_cast<RenderLayer*>(this)->updateLayerListsIfNeeded();
4870
4871 if (RenderLayer* reflection = reflectionLayer()) {
4872 if (!reflection->isComposited()) {
4873 LayoutRect childUnionBounds = reflection->calculateLayerBounds(this, reflection->offsetFromAncestor(this), descendantFlags);
4874 unionBounds.unite(childUnionBounds);
4875 }
4876 }
4877
4878 ASSERT(isStackingContext() || !positiveZOrderLayers().size());
4879
4880#if ASSERT_ENABLED
4881 LayerListMutationDetector mutationChecker(const_cast<RenderLayer&>(*this));
4882#endif
4883
4884 auto computeLayersUnion = [this, &unionBounds, flags, descendantFlags] (const RenderLayer& childLayer) {
4885 if (!(flags & IncludeCompositedDescendants) && (childLayer.isComposited() || childLayer.paintsIntoProvidedBacking()))
4886 return;
4887 LayoutRect childBounds = childLayer.calculateLayerBounds(this, childLayer.offsetFromAncestor(this), descendantFlags);
4888 // Ignore child layer (and behave as if we had overflow: hidden) when it is positioned off the parent layer so much
4889 // that we hit the max LayoutUnit value.
4890 unionBounds.checkedUnite(childBounds);
4891 };
4892
4893 for (auto* childLayer : negativeZOrderLayers())
4894 computeLayersUnion(*childLayer);
4895
4896 for (auto* childLayer : positiveZOrderLayers())
4897 computeLayersUnion(*childLayer);
4898
4899 for (auto* childLayer : normalFlowLayers())
4900 computeLayersUnion(*childLayer);
4901
4902 if (flags.contains(IncludeFilterOutsets) || (flags.contains(IncludePaintedFilterOutsets) && paintsWithFilters()))
4903 unionBounds += filterOutsets();
4904
4905 if ((flags & IncludeSelfTransform) && paintsWithTransform(PaintBehavior::Normal)) {
4906 TransformationMatrix* affineTrans = transform();
4907 boundingBoxRect = affineTrans->mapRect(boundingBoxRect);
4908 unionBounds = affineTrans->mapRect(unionBounds);
4909 }
4910 unionBounds.move(offsetFromRoot);
4911 return unionBounds;
4912}

4997
4998bool RenderLayer::backgroundIsKnownToBeOpaqueInRect(const LayoutRect& localRect) const
4999{
5000 if (!isSelfPaintingLayer() && !hasSelfPaintingLayerDescendant())
5001 return false;
5002
5003 if (paintsWithTransparency(PaintBehavior::Normal))
5004 return false;
5005
5006 if (renderer().isDocumentElementRenderer()) {
5007 // Normally the document element doens't have a layer. If it does have a layer, its background propagates to the RenderView
5008 // so this layer doesn't draw it.
5009 return false;
5010 }
5011
5012 // We can't use hasVisibleContent(), because that will be true if our renderer is hidden, but some child
5013 // is visible and that child doesn't cover the entire rect.
5014 if (renderer().style().visibility() != Visibility::Visible)
5015 return false;
5016
5017 if (paintsWithFilters() && renderer().style().filter().hasFilterThatAffectsOpacity())
5018 return false;
5019
5020 // FIXME: Handle simple transforms.
5021 if (paintsWithTransform(PaintBehavior::Normal))
5022 return false;
5023
5024 // FIXME: Remove this check.
5025 // This function should not be called when layer-lists are dirty.
5026 // It is somehow getting triggered during style update.
5027 if (zOrderListsDirty() || normalFlowListDirty())
5028 return false;
5029
5030 // Table painting is special; a table paints its sections.
5031 if (renderer().isTablePart())
5032 return false;
5033
5034 // FIXME: We currently only check the immediate renderer,
5035 // which will miss many cases.
5036 if (renderer().backgroundIsKnownToBeOpaqueInRect(localRect))
5037 return true;
5038
5039 // We can't consult child layers if we clip, since they might cover
5040 // parts of the rect that are clipped out.
5041 if (renderer().hasOverflowClip())
5042 return false;
5043
5044 return listBackgroundIsKnownToBeOpaqueInRect(positiveZOrderLayers(), localRect)
5045 || listBackgroundIsKnownToBeOpaqueInRect(negativeZOrderLayers(), localRect)
5046 || listBackgroundIsKnownToBeOpaqueInRect(normalFlowLayers(), localRect);
5047}
5048
5049bool RenderLayer::listBackgroundIsKnownToBeOpaqueInRect(const LayerList& list, const LayoutRect& localRect) const
5050{
5051 if (list.begin() == list.end())
5052 return false;
5053
5054 for (auto iter = list.rbegin(); iter != list.rend(); ++iter) {
5055 const auto* childLayer = *iter;
5056 if (childLayer->isComposited())
5057 continue;
5058
5059 if (!childLayer->canUseOffsetFromAncestor())
5060 continue;
5061
5062 LayoutRect childLocalRect(localRect);
5063 childLocalRect.move(-childLayer->offsetFromAncestor(this));
5064
5065 if (childLayer->backgroundIsKnownToBeOpaqueInRect(childLocalRect))
5066 return true;
5067 }
5068 return false;
5069}

5154static bool styleHasSmoothingTextMode(const RenderStyle& style)
5155{

5159
5160// Constrain the depth and breadth of the search for performance.
5161static const unsigned maxRendererTraversalCount = 200;
5162
5163static void determineNonLayerDescendantsPaintedContent(const RenderElement& renderer, unsigned& renderersTraversed, RenderLayer::PaintedContentRequest& request)
5164{
5165 for (const auto& child : childrenOfType<RenderObject>(renderer)) {
5166 if (++renderersTraversed > maxRendererTraversalCount) {
5167 request.makeStatesUndetermined();
5168 return;
5169 }
5170
5171 if (is<RenderText>(child)) {
5172 const auto& renderText = downcast<RenderText>(child);
5173 if (!renderText.hasRenderedText())
5174 continue;
5175
5176 if (renderer.style().userSelect() != UserSelect::None)
5177 request.setHasPaintedContent();
5178
5179 if (!renderText.text().isAllSpecialCharacters<isHTMLSpace>()) {
5180 request.setHasPaintedContent();
5181
5182 if (request.needToDetermineSubpixelAntialiasedTextState() && styleHasSmoothingTextMode(child.style()))
5183 request.setHasSubpixelAntialiasedText();
5184 }
5185
5186 if (request.isSatisfied())
5187 return;
5188 }
5189
5190 if (!is<RenderElement>(child))
5191 continue;
5192
5193 const RenderElement& renderElementChild = downcast<RenderElement>(child);
5194
5195 if (is<RenderLayerModelObject>(renderElementChild) && downcast<RenderLayerModelObject>(renderElementChild).hasSelfPaintingLayer())
5196 continue;
5197
5198 if (hasVisibleBoxDecorationsOrBackground(renderElementChild)) {
5199 request.setHasPaintedContent();
5200 if (request.isSatisfied())
5201 return;
5202 }
5203
5204 if (is<RenderReplaced>(renderElementChild)) {
5205 request.setHasPaintedContent();
5206
5207 if (is<RenderImage>(renderElementChild) && request.needToDetermineSubpixelAntialiasedTextState()) {
5208 auto& imageRenderer = downcast<RenderImage>(renderElementChild);
5209 // May draw text if showing alt text, or image is an SVG image or PDF image.
5210 if ((imageRenderer.isShowingAltText() || imageRenderer.hasNonBitmapImage()) && styleHasSmoothingTextMode(child.style()))
5211 request.setHasSubpixelAntialiasedText();
5212 }
5213
5214 if (request.isSatisfied())
5215 return;
5216 }
5217
5218 determineNonLayerDescendantsPaintedContent(renderElementChild, renderersTraversed, request);
5219 if (request.isSatisfied())
5220 return;
5221 }
5222}
5223
5224bool RenderLayer::hasNonEmptyChildRenderers(PaintedContentRequest& request) const
5225{
5226 unsigned renderersTraversed = 0;
5227 determineNonLayerDescendantsPaintedContent(renderer(), renderersTraversed, request);
5228 return request.probablyHasPaintedContent();
5229}

5235
5236bool RenderLayer::hasVisibleBoxDecorations() const
5237{
5238 if (!hasVisibleContent())
5239 return false;
5240
5241 return hasVisibleBoxDecorationsOrBackground() || (m_scrollableArea && m_scrollableArea->hasOverflowControls());
5242}
5243
5244bool RenderLayer::isVisuallyNonEmpty(PaintedContentRequest* request) const
5245{
5246 ASSERT(!m_visibleDescendantStatusDirty);
5247
5248 if (!hasVisibleContent() || !renderer().style().opacity())
5249 return false;
5250
5251 if (renderer().isRenderReplaced() || (m_scrollableArea && m_scrollableArea->hasOverflowControls())) {
5252 if (!request)
5253 return true;
5254
5255 request->setHasPaintedContent();
5256 if (request->isSatisfied())
5257 return true;
5258 }
5259
5260 if (hasVisibleBoxDecorationsOrBackground()) {
5261 if (!request)
5262 return true;
5263
5264 request->setHasPaintedContent();
5265 if (request->isSatisfied())
5266 return true;
5267 }
5268
5269 PaintedContentRequest localRequest;
5270 if (!request)
5271 request = &localRequest;
5272
5273 return hasNonEmptyChildRenderers(*request);
5274}
5275
5276void RenderLayer::styleChanged(StyleDifference diff, const RenderStyle* oldStyle)
5277{
5278 setIsNormalFlowOnly(shouldBeNormalFlowOnly());
5279
5280 if (setIsCSSStackingContext(shouldBeCSSStackingContext())) {
5281#if ENABLE(CSS_COMPOSITING)
5282 if (parent()) {
5283 if (isCSSStackingContext()) {
5284 if (!hasNotIsolatedBlendingDescendantsStatusDirty() && hasNotIsolatedBlendingDescendants())
5285 parent()->dirtyAncestorChainHasBlendingDescendants();
5286 } else {
5287 if (hasNotIsolatedBlendingDescendantsStatusDirty())
5288 parent()->dirtyAncestorChainHasBlendingDescendants();
5289 else if (hasNotIsolatedBlendingDescendants())
5290 parent()->updateAncestorChainHasBlendingDescendants();
5291 }
5292 }
5293#endif
5294 }
5295
5296 updateLayerScrollableArea();
5297
5298 // FIXME: RenderLayer already handles visibility changes through our visibility dirty bits. This logic could
5299 // likely be folded along with the rest.
5300 if (oldStyle) {
5301 bool visibilityChanged = oldStyle->visibility() != renderer().style().visibility();
5302 if (oldStyle->usedZIndex() != renderer().style().usedZIndex() || visibilityChanged) {
5303 dirtyStackingContextZOrderLists();
5304 if (isStackingContext())
5305 dirtyZOrderLists();
5306 }
5307
5308 // Visibility is input to canUseCompositedScrolling().
5309 if (visibilityChanged && m_scrollableArea)
5310 m_scrollableArea->computeHasCompositedScrollableOverflow();
5311 }
5312
5313 if (m_scrollableArea) {
5314 m_scrollableArea->createOrDestroyMarquee();
5315 m_scrollableArea->updateScrollbarsAfterStyleChange(oldStyle);
5316 }
5317 // Overlay scrollbars can make this layer self-painting so we need
5318 // to recompute the bit once scrollbars have been updated.
5319 updateSelfPaintingLayer();
5320
5321 if (!hasReflection() && m_reflection)
5322 removeReflection();
5323 else if (hasReflection()) {
5324 if (!m_reflection)
5325 createReflection();
5326 else
5327 m_reflection->setStyle(createReflectionStyle());
5328 }
5329
5330 // FIXME: Need to detect a swap from custom to native scrollbars (and vice versa).
5331 if (m_scrollableArea)
5332 m_scrollableArea->updateAllScrollbarRelatedStyle();
5333
5334 updateDescendantDependentFlags();
5335 updateTransform();
5336#if ENABLE(CSS_COMPOSITING)
5337 updateBlendMode();
5338#endif
5339 updateFiltersAfterStyleChange();
5340
5341 compositor().layerStyleChanged(diff, *this, oldStyle);
5342
5343 updateFilterPaintingStrategy();
5344
5345#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY) && ENABLE(TOUCH_EVENTS)
5346 if (diff == StyleDifference::RecompositeLayer || diff >= StyleDifference::LayoutPositionedMovementOnly)
5347 renderer().document().invalidateRenderingDependentRegions();
5348#else
5349 UNUSED_PARAM(diff);
5350#endif
5351}

5380
5381RenderStyle RenderLayer::createReflectionStyle()
5382{
5383 auto newStyle = RenderStyle::create();
5384 newStyle.inheritFrom(renderer().style());
5385
5386 // Map in our transform.
5387 TransformOperations transform;
5388 switch (renderer().style().boxReflect()->direction()) {
5389 case ReflectionDirection::Below:
5390 transform.operations().append(TranslateTransformOperation::create(Length(0, LengthType::Fixed), Length(100., LengthType::Percent), TransformOperation::TRANSLATE));
5391 transform.operations().append(TranslateTransformOperation::create(Length(0, LengthType::Fixed), renderer().style().boxReflect()->offset(), TransformOperation::TRANSLATE));
5392 transform.operations().append(ScaleTransformOperation::create(1.0, -1.0, ScaleTransformOperation::SCALE));
5393 break;
5394 case ReflectionDirection::Above:
5395 transform.operations().append(ScaleTransformOperation::create(1.0, -1.0, ScaleTransformOperation::SCALE));
5396 transform.operations().append(TranslateTransformOperation::create(Length(0, LengthType::Fixed), Length(100., LengthType::Percent), TransformOperation::TRANSLATE));
5397 transform.operations().append(TranslateTransformOperation::create(Length(0, LengthType::Fixed), renderer().style().boxReflect()->offset(), TransformOperation::TRANSLATE));
5398 break;
5399 case ReflectionDirection::Right:
5400 transform.operations().append(TranslateTransformOperation::create(Length(100., LengthType::Percent), Length(0, LengthType::Fixed), TransformOperation::TRANSLATE));
5401 transform.operations().append(TranslateTransformOperation::create(renderer().style().boxReflect()->offset(), Length(0, LengthType::Fixed), TransformOperation::TRANSLATE));
5402 transform.operations().append(ScaleTransformOperation::create(-1.0, 1.0, ScaleTransformOperation::SCALE));
5403 break;
5404 case ReflectionDirection::Left:
5405 transform.operations().append(ScaleTransformOperation::create(-1.0, 1.0, ScaleTransformOperation::SCALE));
5406 transform.operations().append(TranslateTransformOperation::create(Length(100., LengthType::Percent), Length(0, LengthType::Fixed), TransformOperation::TRANSLATE));
5407 transform.operations().append(TranslateTransformOperation::create(renderer().style().boxReflect()->offset(), Length(0, LengthType::Fixed), TransformOperation::TRANSLATE));
5408 break;
5409 }
5410 newStyle.setTransform(transform);
5411
5412 // Map in our mask.
5413 newStyle.setMaskBoxImage(renderer().style().boxReflect()->mask());
5414
5415 // Style has transform and mask, so needs to be stacking context.
5416 newStyle.setUsedZIndex(0);
5417
5418 return newStyle;
5419}

5459void RenderLayer::updateFiltersAfterStyleChange()
5460{
5461 if (!hasFilter()) {
5462 clearLayerFilters();
5463 return;
5464 }
5465
5466 // Add the filter as a client to this renderer, unless we are a RenderLayer accommodating
5467 // an SVG. In that case it takes care of its own resource management for filters.
5468 if (renderer().style().filter().hasReferenceFilter() && !renderer().isSVGRoot()) {
5469 ensureLayerFilters();
5470 m_filters->updateReferenceFilterClients(renderer().style().filter());
5471 } else if (m_filters)

5473}

5476{

5478 bool hadScrollableArea = scrollableArea();
5479 clearLayerScrollableArea();
5480
5481 if (hadScrollableArea && renderer().settings().asyncOverflowScrollingEnabled())
5482 setNeedsCompositingConfigurationUpdate();
5483 return;
5484 }
5485
5486 ensureLayerScrollableArea();
5487}
5488
5489void RenderLayer::updateFilterPaintingStrategy()
5490{
5491 // RenderLayerFilters is only used to render the filters in software mode,
5492 // so we always need to run updateFilterPaintingStrategy() after the composited
5493 // mode might have changed for this layer.
5494 if (!paintsWithFilters()) {
5495 // Don't delete the whole filter info here, because we might use it
5496 // for loading SVG reference filter files.
5497 if (m_filters)
5498 m_filters->setFilter(nullptr);
5499
5500 // Early-return only if we *don't* have reference filters.
5501 // For reference filters, we still want the FilterEffect graph built
5502 // for us, even if we're composited.
5503 if (!renderer().style().filter().hasReferenceFilter())
5504 return;
5505 }
5506
5507 ensureLayerFilters();
5508 m_filters->buildFilter(renderer(), page().deviceScaleFactor(), renderer().settings().acceleratedFiltersEnabled() ? RenderingMode::Accelerated : RenderingMode::Unaccelerated);
5509}

5563bool RenderLayer::invalidateEventRegion(EventRegionInvalidationReason reason)
5564{
5565#if ENABLE(ASYNC_SCROLLING)
5566 auto* compositingLayer = enclosingCompositingLayerForRepaint();
5567
5568 auto shouldInvalidate = [&] {
5569 if (!compositingLayer)
5570 return false;
5571
5572 if (reason == EventRegionInvalidationReason::NonCompositedFrame)
5573 return true;
5574
5575 return compositingLayer->backing()->maintainsEventRegion();
5576 };
5577
5578 if (!shouldInvalidate())
5579 return false;
5580
5581 LOG_WITH_STREAM(EventRegions, stream << this << " invalidateEventRegion for reason " << reason << " invalidating in compositing layer " << compositingLayer);
5582
5583 compositingLayer->backing()->setNeedsEventRegionUpdate();
5584
5585 if (reason == EventRegionInvalidationReason::NonCompositedFrame) {
5586 auto& view = renderer().view();
5587 LOG_WITH_STREAM(EventRegions, stream << " calling setNeedsEventRegionUpdateForNonCompositedFrame on " << view);
5588 view.setNeedsEventRegionUpdateForNonCompositedFrame();
5589 auto visibleDebugOverlayRegions = OptionSet<DebugOverlayRegions>::fromRaw(renderer().settings().visibleDebugOverlayRegions());
5590 if (visibleDebugOverlayRegions.containsAny({ DebugOverlayRegions::TouchActionRegion, DebugOverlayRegions::EditableElementRegion, DebugOverlayRegions::WheelEventHandlerRegion }))
5591 view.setNeedsRepaintHackAfterCompositingLayerUpdateForDebugOverlaysOnly();
5592 view.compositor().scheduleCompositingLayerUpdate();
5593 }
5594 return true;
5595#else
5596 UNUSED_PARAM(reason);
5597 return false;
5598#endif
5599}

5721
5722static void outputPaintOrderTreeRecursive(TextStream& stream, const WebCore::RenderLayer& layer, const char* prefix, unsigned depth = 0)
5723{
5724 stream << (layer.isCSSStackingContext() ? "S" : (layer.isForcedStackingContext() ? "F" : (layer.isOpportunisticStackingContext() ? "P" : "-")));
5725 stream << (layer.isNormalFlowOnly() ? "N" : "-");
5726 stream << (layer.renderer().hasOverflowClip() ? "O" : "-");
5727 stream << (layer.isTransparent() ? "A" : "-");
5728 stream << (layer.hasBlendMode() ? "B" : "-");
5729 stream << (layer.isolatesBlending() ? "I" : "-");
5730 stream << (layer.renderer().hasTransformRelatedProperty() ? "T" : "-");
5731 stream << (layer.hasFilter() ? "F" : "-");
5732 stream << (layer.renderer().isFixedPositioned() ? "X" : "-");
5733 stream << (layer.behavesAsFixed() ? "x" : "-");
5734 stream << (layer.isComposited() ? "C" : "-");
5735
5736 auto compositedPaintingDestinationString = [&layer]() {
5737 if (layer.paintsIntoProvidedBacking())
5738 return "p";
5739
5740 if (!layer.isComposited())
5741 return "-";
5742
5743 if (layer.backing()->hasBackingSharingLayers())
5744 return "P";
5745
5746 if (layer.backing()->paintsIntoCompositedAncestor())
5747 return "a";
5748
5749 return "-";
5750 };
5751
5752 stream << compositedPaintingDestinationString();
5753 stream << (layer.hasCompositingDescendant() ? "c" : "-");
5754 stream << (layer.hasCompositedScrollingAncestor() ? "s" : "-");
5755 stream << (layer.hasTransformedAncestor() ? "t" : "-");
5756
5757 stream << " ";
5758
5759 stream << (layer.zOrderListsDirty() ? "z" : "-");
5760 stream << (layer.normalFlowListDirty() ? "n" : "-");
5761
5762 stream << " ";
5763
5764 stream << (layer.hasDescendantNeedingCompositingRequirementsTraversal() ? "t" : "-");
5765 stream << (layer.hasDescendantNeedingUpdateBackingOrHierarchyTraversal() ? "b" : "-");
5766 stream << (layer.descendantsNeedCompositingRequirementsTraversal() ? "r" : "-");
5767 stream << (layer.subsequentLayersNeedCompositingRequirementsTraversal() ? "s" : "-");
5768 stream << (layer.descendantsNeedUpdateBackingAndHierarchyTraversal() ? "h" : "-");
5769 stream << (layer.needsCompositingPaintOrderChildrenUpdate() ? "o" : "-");
5770
5771 stream << " ";
5772
5773 stream << (layer.needsPostLayoutCompositingUpdate() ? "l" : "-");
5774 stream << (layer.needsCompositingGeometryUpdate() ? "g" : "-");
5775 stream << (layer.childrenNeedCompositingGeometryUpdate() ? "k" : "-");
5776 stream << (layer.needsCompositingConfigurationUpdate() ? "c" : "-");
5777 stream << (layer.needsCompositingLayerConnection() ? "x" : "-");
5778 stream << (layer.needsScrollingTreeUpdate() ? "s" : "-");
5779
5780 stream << " ";
5781
5782 stream << layer.boxScrollingScope();
5783 stream << " ";
5784 stream << layer.contentsScrollingScope();
5785
5786 stream << " ";
5787
5788 outputIdent(stream, depth);
5789
5790 stream << prefix;
5791
5792 auto layerRect = layer.rect();
5793
5794 stream << &layer << " " << layerRect;
5795
5796 if (auto* scrollableArea = layer.scrollableArea())
5797 stream << " [SA " << scrollableArea << "]";
5798
5799 if (layer.isComposited()) {
5800 auto& backing = *layer.backing();
5801 stream << " (layerID " << backing.graphicsLayer()->primaryLayerID() << ")";
5802
5803 if (layer.indirectCompositingReason() != WebCore::IndirectCompositingReason::None)
5804 stream << " " << layer.indirectCompositingReason();
5805
5806 auto scrollingNodeID = backing.scrollingNodeIDForRole(WebCore::ScrollCoordinationRole::Scrolling);
5807 auto frameHostingNodeID = backing.scrollingNodeIDForRole(WebCore::ScrollCoordinationRole::FrameHosting);
5808 auto viewportConstrainedNodeID = backing.scrollingNodeIDForRole(WebCore::ScrollCoordinationRole::ViewportConstrained);
5809 auto positionedNodeID = backing.scrollingNodeIDForRole(WebCore::ScrollCoordinationRole::Positioning);
5810
5811 if (scrollingNodeID || frameHostingNodeID || viewportConstrainedNodeID || positionedNodeID) {
5812 stream << " {";
5813 bool first = true;
5814 if (scrollingNodeID) {
5815 stream << "sc " << scrollingNodeID;
5816 first = false;
5817 }
5818
5819 if (frameHostingNodeID) {
5820 if (!first)
5821 stream << ", ";
5822 stream << "fh " << frameHostingNodeID;
5823 first = false;
5824 }
5825
5826 if (viewportConstrainedNodeID) {
5827 if (!first)
5828 stream << ", ";
5829 stream << "vc " << viewportConstrainedNodeID;
5830 first = false;
5831 }
5832
5833 if (positionedNodeID) {
5834 if (!first)
5835 stream << ", ";
5836 stream << "pos " << positionedNodeID;
5837 }
5838
5839 stream << "}";
5840 }
5841 }
5842 stream << " " << layer.name();
5843 stream.nextLine();
5844
5845 const_cast<WebCore::RenderLayer&>(layer).updateLayerListsIfNeeded();
5846
5847 for (auto* child : layer.negativeZOrderLayers())
5848 outputPaintOrderTreeRecursive(stream, *child, "- ", depth + 1);
5849
5850 for (auto* child : layer.normalFlowLayers())
5851 outputPaintOrderTreeRecursive(stream, *child, "n ", depth + 1);
5852
5853 for (auto* child : layer.positiveZOrderLayers())
5854 outputPaintOrderTreeRecursive(stream, *child, "+ ", depth + 1);
5855}
